The Right to Read is a short story by Richard Stallman , the founder of the Free Software Foundation , which was first published in 1997 in Communications of the ACM .
Today We Choose Faces is a 1973 science fiction novel by Roger Zelazny .
Stranger on the Square is the third volume of Arthur Koestler 's autobiography , published posthumously in 1984 .
Smith 's Bible Dictionary , originally named A Dictionary of the Bible , was a 19th - century Bible dictionary containing upwards of four thousand entries that became named after its editor , William Smith .
The Kalām Cosmological Argument ( KCA ) is a book written by William Lane Craig .
Odds On is Michael Crichton 's first published novel .
Questionable Content ( abbreviated QC ) is a slice of life webcomic written and drawn by Jeph Jacques .
The Finer Points of Sausage Dogs is a novel by Scottish author and academic Alexander McCall Smith .
The GNU Manifesto was written by Richard Stallman and published in March 1985 in Dr. Dobb 's Journal of Software Tools as an explanation and definition of the goals of the GNU Project , and to call for participation and support developing GNU , a free software computer operating system .
Sweets and Other Stories is the 2009 debut novel by soul singer Andre Williams .
`` A Pail of Air '' is a science fiction short story by Fritz Leiber which appeared in the December 1951 issue of Galaxy Magazine and was dramatized on the radio show X Minus One in March 1956 .
Kinflicks ( 1976 ) is a novel by American writer Lisa Alther .
Flying Blind , Flying Safe is a non - fiction book about the American airline industry and Federal Aviation Administration , written by Mary Schiavo with Sabra Chartrand .
Several histories of fourth - century Greece , written in the mold of Thucydides or straying from it , have borne the conventional Latin title Hellenica .
The Analysis of Beauty is a book written by William Hogarth ( 18th century English painter , satirist , and writer ) and published in 1753 , which describes Hogarth 's theories of visual beauty and grace in a manner accessible to the common man of his day .
The Cosmic Geoids and One Other is a collection of two science fiction novellas by author John Taine ( pseudonym of Eric Temple Bell ) .
Emperor Shaka the Great is an epic poem based on the Zulu oral tradition , compiled in Zulu then translated by South African Poet Mazisi Kunene .
Yankee in Oz is a 1972 Oz novel by Ruth Plumly Thompson .
The Official Preppy Handbook ( 1980 ) is a tongue - in - cheek humor reference guide edited by Lisa Birnbach , written by Jonathan Roberts , Carol McD.
The Fool of Quality ; or , The History of Henry , Earl of Moreland ( 1765 - 70 ) , a picaresque and sentimental novel by the Irish writer Henry Brooke , is the only one of his works which has enjoyed any great reputation .
Not Happy , John is a book written by Margo Kingston , an Australian journalist and political commentator .
Goddess of Yesterday is a book by Caroline B. Cooney based on the Trojan War from Greek mythology .
The Pirates of Zan is a science fiction novel by Murray Leinster , originally serialized in Astounding Science Fiction in 1959 as `` The Pirates of Ersatz '' .
Dusklands ( 1974 ) is the debut novel by J. M. Coetzee , winner of the 2003 Nobel Prize in Literature .
The Chocolate War is a young adult novel by American author Robert Cormier .
The Interruption of Everything is a 2005 book written by Terry McMillan .
No Business of Mine is a 1947 action thriller novel written by James Hadley Chase ( under his pseudonym Raymond Marshall ) .
The 25th Hour is the 2001 debut novel by David Benioff .
Seeing Calvin Coolidge in a Dream is a 1996 book by John Derbyshire .
Bad Chili is a crime mystery novel by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
Anastasia 's Chosen Career ( 1987 ) is a young - adult novel by Lois Lowry .
`` A Pessimist Is Never Disappointed '' is an indie - rock song written by Billy Reeves for Theaudience 's eponymous album Theaudience , released as the third single on 11 May 1998 .
Morgan 's Run is a historical novel by Colleen McCullough published in 2000 about the life of an English prisoner driven to the first penal colonies in Australia in the 18th century .
Without Sorcery is a collection of science fiction and fantasy short stories by author Theodore Sturgeon .
Nada the Lily is an historical novel by English writer H. Rider Haggard , published in 1892 .
Nick and the Glimmung is a children 's science fiction novel , originally written by Philip K. Dick in 1966 , it was first published by Gollancz in 1988 .
Beside Still Waters is a nonfiction book by Gregg Easterbrook .
Buzz Aldrin , What Happened To You in All The Confusion ? ( Original title : Buzz Aldrin , hvor ble det av deg i alt mylderet ? ) is a novel by the Norwegian author Johan Harstad , published in 2005 .
Siegwart , eine Klostergeschichte ( `` Siegwart , a Tale of the Cloister '' , 1776 ) was a novel by Johann Martin Miller .
Such Interesting Neighbors is a science fiction short story by Jack Finney , first published in 1951 .
Karachi , You 're Killing Me ! is a 2014 comedy crime - thriller novel by the Pakistani journalist - writer Saba Imtiaz .
The Sickness Unto Death ( Danish : Sygdommen til Døden ) is a book written by Danish philosopher Søren Kierkegaard in 1849 under the pseudonym Anti - Climacus .
Far Lands , Other Days is a collection of fantasy , horror and mystery short stories by author E. Hoffmann Price .
Sky Coyote is a science fiction novel of The Company by Kage Baker .
Blast Off at Woomera is a young adult science fiction novel , the first in Hugh Walters ' Chris Godfrey of U.N.E.X.A. series .
Races of the Wild was written by Skip Williams and published in February 2005 .
Tuan Direktur ( literally Mr Director ) is a 1939 novel by the Indonesian Muslim cleric and writer Haji Abdul Malik Karim Amrullah ( Hamka ) .
The Edwardians ( 1930 ) is one of Vita Sackville - West 's later novels and a clear critique of the Edwardian aristocratic society as well as a reflection of her own childhood experiences .
The Essential Conan is a collection of fantasy short stories written by Robert E. Howard featuring his sword and sorcery hero Conan the Barbarian .
Othappu ( English : Scandal or Temptation ) is a Malayalam novel written by Sarah Joseph and published in 2005 .
Red Strangers is a 1939 novel by Elspeth Huxley .
Martin Sloane is Canadian author Michael Redhill 's first novel , published in 2001 by Doubleday Canada .
Urban Decay in India ( c. 300-c . 1000 ) is a book written by Ram Sharan Sharma published in 1987 by Munshiram Manoharlal , Delhi ISBN 978 - 8121500456 .
Nang Si Eba ay Likhain ( When Eve was Created ) is a Tagalog - language fictional romantic novel written by Filipino novelist Rosauro Almario in 1913 .
Die schweigsame Frau ( The Silent Woman ) , Op . 80 , is a 1935 opera in three acts by Richard Strauss with libretto by Stefan Zweig after Ben Jonson 's Epicoene , or the Silent Woman .
`` The Secret Miracle '' is a short story by Argentine writer and poet Jorge Luis Borges .
Dangerous Kiss is a 1999 novel by Jackie Collins and the fifth novel in her Santangelo novels series .
Prelude to Space is a science fiction novel written by Arthur C. Clarke in 1947 .
Fate of Worlds ( 2012 ) is the fifth and final book written in the Fleet of Worlds series , itself a subset of Larry Niven 's Known Space series .
The Keeper 's Price and Other Stories is an anthology of fantasy and science fiction short stories edited by Marion Zimmer Bradley .
Serpent Mage is the fourth book in The Death Gate Cycle series written by Margaret Weis and Tracy Hickman .
Cattail Moon ( 1994 ) is a young adult novel written by Jean Thesman .
The Ant and the Grasshopper , alternatively titled The Grasshopper and the Ant ( or Ants ) , is one of Aesop 's Fables , numbered 373 in the Perry Index .
If Nobody Speaks of Remarkable Things is British writer Jon McGregor 's first novel , which was first published by Bloomsbury in 2002 .
The Death of Artemio Cruz ( Spanish : La muerte de Artemio Cruz , pronounced : ( aɾˈtemjo ˈkɾus ) ) is a novel written in 1962 by Mexican writer Carlos Fuentes .
Summer Knight is a 2002 New York Times Bestselling contemporary fantasy novel by author Jim Butcher .
A Winter Haunting is a 2002 horror novel by American writer Dan Simmons .
The Naked Public Square is a 1984 book written by then - Lutheran pastor Richard John Neuhaus about the relationship between religion , culture , and politics in the context of 1980s American secularism .
Death of a Hero is a World War I novel by Richard Aldington .
A Constellation of Vital Phenomena is a novel written by Anthony Marra , published February 4 , 2014 by Hogarth .
The Selling of the President 1968 is a non - fiction book written by American author Joe McGinniss and published by Trident Press in October , 1969 .
Sun and Shadow ( Sol och skugga ) is a 1999 novel by Åke Edwardson , part of the Inspector Winter series .
On Heaven and Earth ( Spanish : Sobre el cielo y la tierra ) is a book that presents conversations between Argentine Cardinal Jorge Bergoglio , who later became Pope Francis , and Argentine rabbi Abraham Skorka .
`` The Bicentennial Man '' is a novelette in the Robot series by Isaac Asimov .
Songs of Kabir is a 1915 book consisting of 100 poems of Kabir , the 15th - century Indian poet and mystic , translated to English by Rabindranath Tagore .
Three Golden Rivers is an historical , young - adult novel by the American writer Olive Price .
Los autonautas de la cosmopista ( `` The Autonauts of the Cosmoroute '' ) is a book written by Julio Cortázar in collaboration with Carol Dunlop , who died shortly before it was published .
Portuguese Irregular Verbs is a short comic novel by Alexander McCall Smith , and the first of McCall Smith 's Professor Dr von Igelfeld novels .
The Philobiblon is a collection of essays concerning the acquisition , preservation , and organization of books written by the mediaeval bibliophile Richard de Bury shortly before his death in 1345 .
Hermsprong : or , Man As He Is Not is a 1796 philosophical novel by Robert Bage .
Father Malachy 's Miracle is a 1931 novel by the Scottish writer Bruce Marshall .
`` Politics and the English Language '' ( 1946 ) is an essay by George Orwell that criticises the `` ugly and inaccurate '' written English of his time and examines the connection between political orthodoxies and the debasement of language .
Norse Code is the first novel by science fiction and fantasy author Greg van Eekhout .
The Whispering Road is a children 's book by Livi Michael , published in 2005 .
De doctrina christiana ( English : On Christian Doctrine or On Christian Teaching ) is a theological text written by St. Augustine of Hippo .
The Corsair is a tale in verse by Lord Byron published in 1814 ( see 1814 in poetry ) , which was extremely popular and influential in its day , selling ten thousand copies on its first day of sale .
The Sneetches and Other Stories is a collection of stories by American author Dr. Seuss , published in 1961 .
The Sword of the Dawn is a novel by British author Michael Moorcock , and was first published in 1968 .
The Spring of the Moonstone ' and its Finnish original , Kuukiven kevät ( Finnish : The Spring of the Moonstone ) is a historical novel by Finnish author Kaari Utrio .
World 's Best Science Fiction : 1969 is an anthology of science fiction short stories edited by Donald A. Wollheim and Terry Carr , the fifth volume in a series of seven .
Personal Reminiscences of Henry Irving is the third book of nonfiction by Bram Stoker ( the author of Dracula ) , published in 1906 .
A Teaspoon Every Four Hours is a comedy play written by Jackie Mason and Mike Mortman which was produced on Broadway in 1969 .
The Pergamon World Atlas ( in English , 1968 ) was originally prepared by the Polish Army Topographical Service .
In Secret Tibet ( In disguise amongst lamas , robbers , and wise men ) is a travel book by author Theodore Illion , first published in English in 1937 .
A Morgadinha dos Canaviais is a Portuguese romance novel by Júlio Dinis , published in 1868 .
The Rise of Scourge is an original English - language manga book written by Erin Hunter and Dan Jolley as part of the Warriors series .
Invasion from 2500 is a science fiction novel written by Ted White and Terry Carr in 1964 under the pseudonym Norman Edwards and published by Monarch Books , in August 1964 ,
The Loch is a science fiction novel and Legal thriller by Steve Alten , and was first published in 2005 .
The Seven Fabulous Wonders is a fantasy series by Katherine Roberts currently comprising seven novels .
The Miocene Arrow is a post - apocalyptic novel by Sean McMullen .
Ugly To Start With ( 2011 ) is a young adult literary novel in the form of linked short stories by John Michael Cummings about the growing pains of a teenage artist in an American tourist town .
`` The Ungoverned '' is a 1985 science fiction novella by Vernor Vinge , set between his novels The Peace War and Marooned in Realtime .
Towers of Midnight by Robert Jordan and Brandon Sanderson , is the sequel to the novel The Gathering Storm , and the 13th book in the Wheel of Time series .
The Demon Spirit is the second book in the first DemonWars Saga trilogy by R. A. Salvatore .
Tribulations of a Chinaman in China ( French : Les Tribulations d'un Chinois en Chine ) is an adventure novel by Jules Verne , first published in 1879 .
The Girls Get Even is a children 's novel by Phyllis Reynolds Naylor published by Random House , originally in 1993 .
The Last Ringbearer ( Russian : Последний кольценосец ) is a 1999 fantasy book by Russian author Kirill Eskov .
Makamisa ( English : After Mass ) is an unfinished novel written by Filipino patriot and writer José Rizal .
The OMAC Project is a six issue American comic book limited series written by Greg Rucka with art by Jesus Saiz and published by DC Comics in 2005 .
New Writings in SF 16 is an anthology of science fiction short stories edited by John Carnell , the sixteenth volume in a series of thirty , of which he edited the first twenty - one .
Caravan to Vaccarès is a novel by Scottish author Alistair MacLean , originally published in 1969 with a cover by Norman Weaver .
Already Dead is a 2005 pulp - noir / horror novel by Charlie Huston and published in 2005 .
`` Murder Mysteries '' is a fantasy short story by Neil Gaiman first published in the 1992 anthology Midnight Graffiti and later collected in his collection Smoke and Mirrors .
Permutation City is a 1994 science fiction novel by Greg Egan that explores many concepts , including quantum ontology , via various philosophical aspects of artificial life and simulated reality .
`` The Soft Weapon '' is a science fiction short story written in 1967 by Larry Niven , set in his Known Space universe .
Buffalo Gals , Wo n't You Come Out Tonight is a science fiction novelette by Ursula K. Le Guin , originally published in the November 1987 issue of The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction and collected in Buffalo Gals and Other Animal Presences .
The QI Book of the Dead ( sold as The Book of the Dead in the United States ) is the fourth title in a series of books based on the intellectual British panel game QI , written by series - creator John Lloyd and head - researcher John Mitchinson .
Hingede öö ( English : All Souls ' Night or Night of Souls ) is a novel by the Estonian author Karl Ristikivi .

An Amateur Laborer is an autobiographical book by Theodore Dreiser .
Science , Order , and Creativity is a book by theoretical physicist David Bohm and physicist and writer F. David Peat .
Perfect Chemistry is the first novel in the trilogy written by author Simone Elkeles and published by Walker Books for Young Readers in 2009 and also made it on the New York Times Best Sellers List .
Stori Telling , stylized as sTORI TELLING , is a 2008 book by Tori Spelling and Hilary Liftin .
The Origin of Birds is an early synopsis of bird evolution written in 1926 by Gerhard Heilmann , a Danish artist and amateur zoologist .
The Whipping Boy is a Newbery medal - winning children 's book by Sid Fleischman , published in 1987 .
Simulacron-3 ( 1964 ) ( also published as Counterfeit World ) , by Daniel F. Galouye , is an American science fiction novel featuring an early literary description of virtual reality .
In the Shadow of Midnight is a 1994 historical novel by Canadian author Marsha Canham , the second instalment of her `` Medieval '' trilogy inspired by the Robin Hood legend set in 13th - century England .
Autobiography of a Yogi is an autobiography of Paramahansa Yogananda ( January 5 , 1893 - -March 7 , 1952 ) first published in 1946 .
PopCo ( 2004 ) is a novel by British author Scarlett Thomas .
Glass Town is a fictitious world created by siblings of the Brontë family--
Le Rose et le Vert ( French for The Pink and the Green ) is an unfinished novel by Stendhal .
Dorothy Must Die is a 2014 young adult book by Danielle Paige and her debut novel .
The Fortunes of Richard Mahony is a three - part novel by Australian writer Ethel Florence Lindesay Richardson under her pen name of Henry Handel Richardson .
On the Pope ( Du Pape ) is an 1819 book written by Savoyard philosopher Joseph de Maistre , which many consider to be his literary masterpiece .
Girls under Pressure is the second book in the Girls series , written by Dame Jacqueline Wilson , DBE , a noted English author who writes fiction for children .
The Patron Saint of Eels ( 2005 ) is a novel by Australian author Gregory Day .
`` The War Prayer , '' a short story or prose poem by Mark Twain , is a scathing indictment of war , and particularly of blind patriotic and religious fervor as motivations for war .
Faerie Tale is a supernatural thriller , falling within the subgenre of contemporary fantasy , by Raymond E. Feist , first published in 1988 .
The Intelligent Man 's Guide to Science is a general guide to the sciences written by Isaac Asimov .
The Female Man is a feminist science fiction novel written by Joanna Russ .
The Beauty Queen of Leenane is a 1996 black comedy by Irish playwright Martin McDonagh which was premiered by the Druid Theatre Company in Galway , Ireland .
Two Leaves and a Bud is a novel by Mulk Raj Anand first published in 1937 .
The Form of Presbyterial Church Government is a document drawn up by the Westminster Assembly dealing with Presbyterian polity .
The Crossovers is a comic book series created in 2003 by Robert Rodi ( writer ) , Mauricet ( penciller # 1 - 6 ) and Ernie Colón ( inker ) , and published by CrossGen .
The Supernaturalist is a science fiction novel by Irish author Eoin Colfer .
`` The Long Rain '' is a short story by science fiction author Ray Bradbury .
Cubitus was created by the Belgian cartoonist Dupa , and features Cubitus , a large anthropomorphic dog , who lives with his owner Semaphore .
The Story of Egmo is a popular ebook and audiobook by Ben Cormack originally available in late 2006 .

The Defenestration of Ermintrude Inch is a science fiction short story by Arthur C. Clarke anthologized in Tales from the White Hart .
`` The TNT Punch '' is a Sailor Steve Costigan short story by Robert E. Howard .
The Lost Father is a novel written by American novelist Mona Simpson .
The Broken Sword is a fantasy novel written by Poul Anderson , originally published in 1954 .
O Cabeleira ( English : Cabeleira ) is a 1876 Regionalist novel by Brazilian Romantic author Franklin Távora .
The Devil and Sonny Liston is a biography of world heavyweight champion boxer Sonny Liston by Nick Tosches .
The Sevenwaters Trilogy is a historical fantasy series by Juliet Marillier which was first published as a series of three novels between 1999 and 2001 , and then later extended .
The Worm Ouroboros is a heroic high fantasy novel by Eric Rücker Eddison , first published in 1922 .
What Katy Did is an 1872 children 's book written by Sarah Chauncey Woolsey under her pen name Susan Coolidge .
The Castle of Indolence is a poem written by James Thomson , a Scottish poet of the 18th century , in 1748 .
Suburbia Highschool ( also known as Sub High ) is a German comic written and illustrated by David Füleki and first published by Delfinium Prints in 2008 .
White Niggers of America ( French : Les Nègres blancs d'Amérique ) is a work of non - fiction literature written by Pierre Vallières , a leader of the Front de libération du Québec .

The Raw Youth ( Russian : Подросток , Podrostok ) , also published as The Adolescent or An Accidental Family , is a novel by Russian writer Fyodor Dostoyevsky , first published in 1875 .

Achille Talon is a Franco - Belgian comics series featuring an eponymous main character , created by Greg ( the pseudonym of Michel Regnier ) .
An April Shroud is a crime novel written by Reginald Hill , it is also the fourth novel in the Dalziel and Pascoe series .
The Stoic is a novel by Theodore Dreiser , first published in 1947 .
Critica Botanica ( `` Critique of botany '' , Leiden , July , 1737 ) was written by Swedish botanist , physician , zoologist and naturalist Carl Linnaeus ( 1707 - -1778 ) .
Vinyl Cafe Diaries ( 2003 ) is Stuart McLean 's fourth volume of stories that first aired on the CBC Radio program The Vinyl Cafe .
Lily 's Crossing is a young adult novel by the American author Patricia Reilly Giff published in 1997 .
Asimov 's Mysteries , published in 1968 , is a collection of 14 short stories by Isaac Asimov , almost all of them science fiction mysteries ( although , as Asimov admits in the introduction , some are only borderline ) .
Horrible Science is a sister series of books to Horrible Histories , written by Nick Arnold ( with the exception of Evolve or Die , which is written by Phil Gates ) , illustrated by Tony de Saulles and published in the UK and India by Scholastic .
This Bleeding City is a 2010 novel by British author Alex Preston and his debut novel .
The Wolves in the Walls is a book by Neil Gaiman and Dave McKean , published in 2003 , in the United States by HarperCollins , and in the United Kingdom by Bloomsbury .
Why Paint Cats is a comedy book written by New Zealand author Burton Silver and illustrator Heather Busch .
Secrets of the Alchemist Dar is a book written by Michael Stadther and published in September 2006 by the author 's company , Treasure Trove , Inc. The book 's story is about fairies and other imaginary creatures .
Barsoom is a fictional representation of the planet Mars created by American pulp fiction author Edgar Rice Burroughs .
Dead By Sunset is a 1995 true crime nonfiction book by author Ann Rule .
The Festival of San Joaquin is a 1997 novel and the third from Belizean - American Zee Edgell .
That Feeling , You Can Only Say What It Is in French ( referring to déjà vu ) is a short story by Stephen King .
Burden of Desire ( 1992 ) is a large mass - market book based on the Halifax Explosion of 1917 written by Canadian - born journalist Robert MacNeil .
Łaski 's Statutes were drawn up by Chancellor and Primate Jan Łaski ( hence they are named for him ) and consolidated nearly all the legislation that had earlier appeared in Poland .
A Sorrow Beyond Dreams ( German : Wunschloses Unglück ) is a 1972 semi - autobiographical novella by the Austrian writer Peter Handke .
Silent Coup is a book written by Len Colodny and Robert Gettlin , in which they contend that former Nixon White House counsel John Dean orchestrated the 1972 Watergate burglary at Democratic National Committee headquarters to protect his future wife Maureen Biner by removing information linking her to a call - girl ring that worked for the DNC .
Blood Knot is an early play by South African playwright , actor , and director Athol Fugard .
A Clean Breast is film director Russ Meyer 's self - published three volume autobiography .
Elizabeth Appleton is a novel by John O'Hara first published in 1963 .
The Manticore is the second novel in Robertson Davies ' Deptford Trilogy .
All Star Batman & Robin , the Boy Wonder is an American comic book series written by Frank Miller and penciled by Jim Lee .
The Hawk in the Rain is a collection of poems by the British poet Ted Hughes .
The Foundation series is a science fiction series by Isaac Asimov .
Siberia , Siberia ( Russian : Сибирь , Сибирь ... ) is a non - fiction book by the Russian writer Valentin Rasputin .
The Worthing Chronicle ( 1983 ) is a science fiction novel by Orson Scott Card set in the Worthing series .
The Gentleman from San Francisco ( Господин из Сан-Франциско , Gospodin iz San Frantsisco ) is a short story by a Nobel Prize - winning Russian author Ivan Bunin , written in 1915 and published the same year in Moscow , in the 5th volume of Slovo ( Word ) anthology .
Gideon 's Trumpet is a book by Anthony Lewis describing the story behind Gideon v. Wainwright , in which the Supreme Court of the United States ruled that criminal defendants have the right to an attorney even if they can not afford it .
A Dream Play ( Swedish : Ett drömspel ) was written in 1901 by the Swedish playwright August Strindberg .
A Scanner Darkly is a BSFA Award - winning 1977 science fiction novel by American writer Philip K. Dick .
The Reckoners is a young adult fantasy series written by American author Brandon Sanderson .
The Dark Path is the second novel in the series by Walter H. Hunt .
Unstrange Minds is a nonfiction book by anthropologist Roy Richard Grinker about the rise in autism diagnoses throughout the world over the last twenty years .
Viajero , Spanish for `` The Wanderer '' or `` The Traveller '' , is a 1993 English - language novel written by multi - award winning Filipino author F. Sionil José .
The Future of the American Negro , a book written in 1899 by American educator Booker T. Washington , set forth his ideas regarding the history of enslaved and freed African - American people and their need for education to advance themselves .
The Scar is the second Bas - Lag novel , and third overall , written by China Miéville , a self - described `` weird fiction '' writer from London , England .
The Dissolution of Nicholas Dee is a 1993 American novel by Matthew Stadler .
Room 13 is a children 's novel written by the acclaimed award winning children 's author Robert Swindells .
Farthest Reach is a 2005 fantasy novel by Richard Baker , set in the Dungeons & Dragons Forgotten Realms fictional universe .
`` Feludar Goendagiri ( English title ' ' Danger in Darjeeling `` ) '' is a short story written by Satyajit Ray featuring private detective Feluda .
The Paradise Bargain is an historical , romance novel by the American writer Betina Krahn .
High Hunt is the first published novel of David Eddings , first copyrighted in 1973 by a private publisher , its copyright was renewed in 1993 in New York and then in 1994 by Del Rey books in London .
Marx 's Theory of Ideology is a 1982 book about Karl Marx by Bhikhu Parekh .
How to Talk Dirty and Influence People is an autobiography by Lenny Bruce , an American satirist and comedian , who died in 1966 at age 40 of a drug overdose .
`` Young Goodman Brown '' is a short story published in 1835 by American writer Nathaniel Hawthorne .
Jurgen , A Comedy of Justice is a fantasy book by James Branch Cabell , the eighth among his fifty - two books , which gained fame ( or notoriety ) shortly after its publication in 1919 .
Pure Drivel is a collection of stories by Steve Martin , published in 1998 , many of which first appeared in The New Yorker .
Certain Personal Matters is an 1897 collection of essays selected by H. G. Wells from among the many short essays and ephemeral pieces he had written since 1893 .
A Storyteller in Zion ( 1993 ) is a collection of short stories and articles by Orson Scott Card .
The Blood Doctor is a novel by British writer Ruth Rendell , written under the pseudonym Barbara Vine .
The Proofreaders ' Page and Other Uncollected Items was an attempt to collect as many uncollected works by Fredric Brown as possible .
Love is a Mix Tape is an autobiography memoir by Rob Sheffield .
The Dalek Factor is an original novella written by Simon Clark and based on the long - running British science fiction television series Doctor Who .
Les Aventures de Tanguy et Laverdure is a Franco - Belgian comics series created by Jean - Michel Charlier and Albert Uderzo , about the two pilots Michel Tanguy and Ernest Laverdure , and their adventures in the French Air Force .
An Inspector Calls is a play written by English dramatist J. B. Priestley , first performed in 1945 in the Soviet Union and in 1946 in the UK .
The Return of John MacNab was the second novel by Scottish writer Andrew Greig .
`` Grotto of the Dancing Deer '' is one of Clifford D. Simak 's later short stories .
My Friend Walter is a children 's fiction novel by Michael Morpurgo .
The Family Arsenal is a novel by Paul Theroux originally published in 1976 .
First Among Sequels is an alternate history , comic fantasy novel by the British author Jasper Fforde .
Our Ancestors ( Italian : I Nostri Antenati ) is the name of Italo Calvino 's `` heraldic trilogy '' that comprises The Cloven Viscount ( 1952 ) , The Baron in the Trees ( 1957 ) , and The Nonexistent Knight ( 1959 ) .
The Reconstruction of Religious Thought in Islam is a compilation of lectures delivered by Muhammad Iqbal on Islamic philosophy and published in 1930 .
The 13-Storey Treehouse is a 2011 book written by author Andy Griffiths and illustrated by Terry Denton , and a stage play based on the book .
Sorcery ! is a single - player four - part adventure gamebook series written by Steve Jackson and illustrated by John Blanche .
The Very Persistent Gappers of Frip is short story writer George Saunders 's first children 's book .
The Dream Room ( German : Die Traumbude ) was Erich Maria Remarque 's first novel .
Professor Dowell 's Head is a 1925 science fiction novel by Russian author Alexander Belyayev .
Ruled Britannia is an alternate history novel by Harry Turtledove , first published in hardcover by New American Library in 2002 .
The Ganymede Takeover is a 1967 science fiction novel by Philip K. Dick and Ray Nelson .
LETTERS is an epistolary novel by the American writer John Barth , published in 1979 .
Man Equals Man ( German : Mann ist Mann ) , or A Man 's a Man , is a play by the German modernist playwright Bertolt Brecht .
Beyond the Fringe was a British comedy stage revue written and performed by Peter Cook , Dudley Moore , Alan Bennett , and Jonathan Miller .
A Sword from Red Ice is the third book in the Sword of Shadows fantasy series by J. V. Jones .
Desert of the Heart is a 1964 lesbian - themed novel written by Jane Rule .
The Rise of Theodore Roosevelt ( 1979 ) is a biography of United States President Theodore Roosevelt by Edmund Morris and published by Coward , McCann & Geoghegan when the author was forty years old .
The Private Memoirs and Confessions of a Justified Sinner , ( Full title , The Private Memoirs and Confessions of a Justified Sinner : Written by Himself : With a detail of curious traditionary facts and other evidence by the editor ) is a novel by the Scottish author James Hogg , published anonymously in 1824 .
Letter to a Christian Nation is a book by Sam Harris , written in response to feedback he received following the publication of his first book The End of Faith .
Kathabeejam ( The Germ of a Story ) is a one - act play written by Malayalam language author Vaikom Muhammad Basheer .
`` Herman Wouk Is Still Alive '' is a 6,500-word short story by American author Stephen King .
The Man Who Japed is a science fiction novel written by Philip K. Dick , first published in 1956 .
Turtle in Paradise is a 2010 Newbery Honor Book by Jennifer L. Holm .
The Bushbabies is a children 's novel by Canadian author William Stevenson published in 1965 .
Lost Cities and Vanished Civilizations is a 1962 book by Robert Silverberg that deals with the then - current archaeology studies of six past civilizations .
The Stars , Like Dust is a 1951 science fiction mystery book by writer Isaac Asimov .
Donovan 's Brain is a 1942 science fiction novel by Curt Siodmak .
The Witch of Portobello ( Portuguese : A Bruxa de Portobello ) is a fiction work by Brazilian writer Paulo Coelho published in 2007 , about a woman born in Transylvania to a Romani mother in a gypsy tribe without wedlock .
Lion of Ireland , by the American - Irish author Morgan Llywelyn , is a novel about the life of the Irish hero and High King Brian Boru .
The Widow and Her Hero is a novel by the Australian author Thomas Keneally set in Australia during World War II .
What Katy Did Next ( 1886 ) is a children 's book by Sarah Chauncey Woolsey , working under the pen name Susan Coolidge .
God and the New Physics is a 1984 scientific book written by English scientist Paul Davies .
A story by French writer Octave Mirbeau , Les Mémoires de mon ami was first published serially in Le Journal between November 27 , 1898 and April 30 , 1899 , in the midst of the Dreyfus Affair .
Smiley Versus Karla ( 1982 ) , by John le Carré , originally published as The Quest for Karla , is an omnibus edition of three novels concerning George Smiley 's fight against Karla , his counterpart in Moscow Centre ( the Soviet KGB ) .
Other Earths ( 2009 ) is an alternate history , science fiction anthology of all - new stories being edited by Nick Gevers and Jay Lake .
Pettson and Findus ( Swedish : Pettson och Findus ) is a series of children 's books written and illustrated by Swedish author Sven Nordqvist .
The Dinosauria is an extensive book on dinosaurs , compiled by David B. Weishampel , Peter Dodson , and Halszka Osmólska .
A Land Remembered is a best - selling novel written by author Patrick D. Smith , and published in 1984 by Pineapple Press .
Where Reincarnation and Biology Intersect is a 1997 book by psychiatrist Ian Stevenson , published by Praeger .
Getting Rid of Bradley is a contemporary romance novel written by Jennifer Crusie and first published in 1994 , with a reissue in 2008 .
The Brave Little Toaster Goes to Mars is the name of both a children 's book by Thomas M. Disch , as well as the film made from same .
Self - Constitution ( full title : Self - Constitution : Agency , Identity , and Integrity ) is a philosophical book by Christine Korsgaard , in which the author sets out to demonstrate how people determine their own actions .
Antidosis ( Ancient Greek ἀντίδοσις ) , is the title of a speech treatise by the ancient Greek rhetorician , Isocrates .
The Face of Fear is a novel by best - selling author Dean Koontz , first published in 1977 .
For Your Eye Alone , published by McClelland and Stewart in 2000 , is a collection of letters written by Canadian novelist Robertson Davies .
Surf na crvenom talasu ( in English Surfing on the red wave ) is a novel by Aleksandar Đuričić published by Ukronija in 2007 .
Spring in Fialta is a short story written by Vladimir Nabokov in 1936 , originally as Весна в Фиальте ( Vesna v Fial'te ) in Russian , during his exile in Berlin .
Italian Shoes is a 2006 novel by Swedish writer Henning Mankell .
Gentleman Junkie and Other Stories of the Hung - Up Generation is an early collection of short stories by Harlan Ellison , originally published in paperback in 1961 .
The Craft of Research is a book by Wayne C. Booth , Gregory G. Colomb , and Joseph M. Williams .
The Broken Bubble is an early mainstream novel by noted science fiction author Philip K. Dick .
Johnny 's in the Basement is a children 's novel by the author Louis Sachar , the author of the National Book Award and Newbery Medal winning novel , Holes .
Why Truth Matters is a book by Ophelia Benson and Jeremy Stangroom published by Continuum Books in 2006 .
The Butterfly Kid is a science fiction novel by Chester Anderson originally released in 1967 .
The Law of Peoples is American philosopher John Rawls ' work on international relations .
The Devil in a Forest is a short novel by American writer Gene Wolfe about the conflict between Christianity and an earlier Pagan religion in Europe during the Middle Ages .
The Breathing Method is a novella by Stephen King which was released as part of his Different Seasons collection in 1982 .
Time of Trial is a young adult historical novel by Hester Burton , first published in 1963 .
Whylah Falls is a long narrative poem ( or `` verse novel '' ) by George Elliott Clarke , published in book form in 1990 .
The Facetiae is an anthology of jokes by Poggio Bracciolini ( 1380 - -1459 ) , first published in 1470 .
Silent to the Bone ( 2000 ) is a novel by E. L. Konigsburg for the `` middle ages '' or for young adults .
The Jesus Factor is a 1970 conspiracy theory thriller novel by Edwin Corley based on the Manhattan Project of World War II and the bombing of Hiroshima and Nagasaki .
Bad Planet is an American six - issue comic book limited series by action film actor Thomas Jane and Steve Niles that started in 2005 .
Savage Season is a crime novel by American author Joe R. Lansdale , published in 1990 .
John Gabriel Borkman is the second - to - last play of the Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen , written in 1896 .
The Human Stain ( 2000 ) is a novel by Philip Roth set in late 1990s rural New England .
The Sublime Object of Ideology ( 1989 ) is a book by Slovenian philosopher and cultural theorist Slavoj Žižek .
Paris in the Twentieth Century ( French : Paris au XXe siècle ) is a science fiction novel by Jules Verne .
Bertram Cope 's Year is a 1919 novel by Henry Blake Fuller , sometimes called the first American homosexual novel .
The Peshawar Lancers is an alternate history , steampunk , post - apocalyptic fiction adventure novel by S. M. Stirling , with its point of divergence occurring in 1878 when the Earth is struck by a devastating meteor shower .
Deaf Sentence ( 2008 ) is a novel by British author David Lodge .
The Great White Hope is a 1967 play written by Howard Sackler , later adapted in 1970 for a film of the same name .
The Tale of Little Pig Robinson is a children 's book written and illustrated by Beatrix Potter as part of the Peter Rabbit series .
The Vanished Man is a forensic crime mystery by Jeffery Deaver featuring the quadriplegic criminalist Lincoln Rhyme and his partner Amelia Sachs .
Betsy Zane , the Rose of Fort Henry is a historical fiction book , written by award - winning author Lynda Durrant in 2000 .
Dr. Freud Will See You Now , Mrs. Hitler is a alternate history play written by British comedy writing duo Laurence Marks and Maurice Gran .
Who Stole the American Dream ? is a non - fiction book by American author and journalist Hedrick Smith published in 2012 by Random House .
The English Girl , the thirteenth title in Daniel Silva 's Gabriel Allon series was released in July 2013 .
Viking Warrior is a young adult historical novel written by Judson Roberts in 2006 .
Taxa Innocentiana was a decree issued by Pope Innocent XI on 1 Oct. , 1678 , regulating the fees that might be demanded or accepted by episcopal chancery offices for various acts , instruments , or writings .
The Ars Amatoria ( English : The Art of Love ) is an instructional elegy series in three books by Ancient Roman poet Ovid .
A Short History of Christianity is a non - fiction book on the history of the Christian religion written by Australian historian Geoffrey Blainey .
Paedagogus ( Greek : Παιδαγωγός , `` Pedagogue '' ) is the second in the great trilogy of Clement of Alexandria .
Man , The Unknown ( L'Homme , cet inconnu ) is a best - selling 1935 book by Alexis Carrel where he endeavours to outline a comprehensive account what is known and more importantly unknown of the human body and human life .
The Post - Birthday World is a novel by Lionel Shriver published in 2007 , some four years after her previous novel , the award winning We Need To Talk About Kevin .
Homer Price is the title character of a pair of children 's books written by Robert McCloskey .
The People 's Choice from Washington to Harding is a book by Herbert Agar , published by Houghton Mifflin , 1933 .
Incredibly Alice is a novel by Phyllis Reynolds Naylor which was published in 2011 .
The Last Don is a novel by Mario Puzo , best known as the author of The Godfather .
Guard of Honor is a Pulitzer Prize - winning novel by James Gould Cozzens published during 1948 .
The Big Jump is a science fiction novel by Leigh Brackett , centered on the first manned expedition to Barnard 's Star .
Against Meidias ( Ancient Greek : Κατὰ Μειδίου ) is one of the most famous judicial orations of the prominent Athenian statesman and orator Demosthenes .
The Museum of Eterna 's Novel ( original Spanish - language title : Museo de la Novela de la Eterna ) is an avant - garde experimental novel by the Argentine writer Macedonio Fernández .
Russia in the Shadows is the title of the book by H. G. Wells published early in 1921 , which includes a series of articles previously printed in The Sunday Express in connection with Wells 's second visit to Russia ( after a previous trip in January 1914 to St. Petersburg and Moscow ) in September and October 1920 .
The Graveyard Game is the fourth installment in the series of science fiction time travel novels by Kage Baker concerning the exploits of The Company .
Kittyhawk Down is a crime novel by Garry Disher published in 2003 .
Shorter Views is a 2000 collection of essays on race , sexuality , science fiction , and the art of writing by author , professor , and critic Samuel R. Delany .
Crystal Express is a collection of science fiction and fantasy stories by cyberpunk author Bruce Sterling .
Ancient Ruins and Archaeology is a 1964 science book by L. Sprague de Camp and Catherine Crook de Camp , one of their most popular works .
The Art of Noises ( Italian : L'arte dei Rumori ) is a Futurist manifesto , written by Luigi Russolo in a 1913 letter to friend and Futurist composer Francesco Balilla Pratella .
The Masters of Solitude , is a 1978 science fiction novel written by Marvin Kaye and Parke Godwin .
The Red City ( 1909 ) is a historical novel by the American writer Silas Weir Mitchell .
The Way To Cook ( 1989 , Knopf ) is a cookbook and series of instructional videos written by the television personality and cooking teacher Julia Child ;
Hanns and Rudolf is a dual biography of Hanns Alexander and Rudolf Höss by British / American journalist Thomas Harding .
H4 The Throne of Bloodstone was written by Douglas Niles and Michael Dobson , with a cover by Keith Parkinson , and was published by TSR in 1988 as a 96-page book .
The Body of Jonah Boyd is a novel by David Leavitt , published in 2004 , that depicts various consequences of the theft of a manuscript .
I , Me , Mine is an autobiographic work by George Harrison , published in 1980 as a hand - bound , limited edition book by Genesis Publications , with a mixture of printed text and multi - colour facsimiles of Harrison 's handwritten lyrics .
The Fudge Family in Paris is an 1818 epistolary verse novel by Thomas Moore .
Will They Ever Trust Us Again ? is a supplementary book by Michael Moore published after his documentary Fahrenheit 9/11 was in theaters and released on DVD .
Alternate Tyrants is a 1997 Tor alternate history anthology , edited by Mike Resnick .
Jacob the Liar is a novel written by the East German Jewish author Jurek Becker published in 1969 .
Brothers of Earth is a 1976 science fiction novel by science fiction and fantasy author C. J. Cherryh .
A Zoo in My Luggage by British naturalist Gerald Durrell is the story of Durrell 's 1957 animal collecting trip to British Cameroon , the northwestern corner of present - day Cameroon .
The Joy of Music is Leonard Bernstein 's first book , originally published in 1959 by Simon & Schuster .
Tales of the Slayers is a Dark Horse Comics Buffy the Vampire Slayer graphic novel that consists of multiple stories written by Joss Whedon , Amber Benson , and others which tell of different members of the Slayer line .
The Python License is a deprecated computer software license created by the Corporation for National Research Initiatives ( CNRI ) .
Tarzan and the Foreign Legion is a novel written by Edgar Rice Burroughs , the twenty - second in his series of books about the title character Tarzan .
The Witling is a 1976 science fiction novel by Vernor Vinge , about a planet populated by a race of nearly - human aliens who have the ability to teleport with their minds .
Ends is a collection of science fiction stories and poems by Gordon R. Dickson .
Gandhi Behind the Mask of Divinity is a book by US Army Colonel G. B. Singh .
`` The Vampyre '' is a short work of prose fiction written in 1819 by John William Polidori .
Le Cousin Pons ( French pronunciation : ​(lə kuzɛ̃ pɔ̃s ) ) is one of the last of the 94 works of Honoré de Balzac 's Comédie humaine , which are in both novel and short story form .

The Bride of Abydos is a poem written by Lord Byron in 1813 .
Den vilda bebin is a children 's book series about a wild baby , written by Barbro Lindgren and illustrated by Eva Eriksson .

Pellucidar is a fictional Hollow Earth invented by Tarzan creator Edgar Rice Burroughs for a series of action adventure stories .
`` The Balloon - Hoax '' is the title used in collections and anthologies of a newspaper article written by Edgar Allan Poe , first published in 1844 .

The Secret Hour is a science - fiction fantasy novel written by Scott Westerfeld .

The Bellarosa Connection is a 1989 novella by the American author Saul Bellow .

The Passion of Ayn Rand is a biography of Ayn Rand by writer and lecturer Barbara Branden , a former friend and business associate .
Calculating Space is the title of MIT 's English translation of Konrad Zuse 's 1969 book Rechnender Raum ( literally : `` space that is computing '' ) , the first book on digital physics .
No Thoroughfare is a stage play and novel by Charles Dickens and Wilkie Collins , both released in December 1867 .

The Dreamseller saga consists of three novels written by Augusto Cury -- doctor , psychiatrist , psychotherapist and publishing phenomenon in Brazil .

( subtitled Trick Questions , Zen - Like Riddles , Insanely Difficult Puzzles , and Other Devious Interviewing Techniques ) is a 2012 business book by Pulitzer Prize - nominated science writer , William Poundstone , describing details of the methods used and questions asked of job applicants to Google .

The Rangoon Man is the 240th novel in the long - running Nick Carter - Killmaster series .
The Permanent Instruction of the Alta Vendita ( commonly called the Alta Vendita ) is a document , originally published in Italian in the 19th century , purportedly produced by the highest lodge of the Italian Carbonari and written by `` Piccolo Tigre , '' codename for Giuseppe Mazzini .
De Historia Stirpium Commentarii Insignes ( Notable Commentaries on the History of Plants ) is a book by Leonhart Fuchs on herbal plants published in Basel in 1542 .
Capturez un Marsupilami ! , written and drawn by André Franquin , is a comic album containing adventures and short gags of the Marsupilami .
The Pedagogical Poem ( Педагогическая поэма , Pedagogicheskaya poema ) , translated into English as Road to Life , is a novel by Anton Makarenko , written in 1925 - 1935 and published in three parts in 1933 - 1935 .
Raymonda ( Russian : Раймонда ) is a ballet in three acts , four scenes with an apotheosis , choreographed by Marius Petipa , with music by Alexander Glazunov , his opus 57 .
The Shadowhunter 's Codex is a companion novel as part of Cassandra Clare 's The Shadowhunter Chronicles .
Simplicius Simplicissimus ( German : Der abenteuerliche Simplicissimus Teutsch ) is a picaresque novel of the lower Baroque style , written in 1668 by Hans Jakob Christoffel von Grimmelshausen and probably published the same year ( although bearing the date 1669 ) .
The Scandal of Scientology is a critical exposé book about the Church of Scientology , written by Paulette Cooper and published by Tower Publications , in 1971 .

The Beggar is a 1965 novella by Naguib Mahfouz about the failure to find meaning in existence .

Twelfth Grade Kills is the final novel in Zac Brewer 's , formerly Heather Brewer , Vladimir Tod series .

Anathem is a speculative fiction novel by Neal Stephenson , published in 2008 .

My Laugh Comes Last is a 1977 thriller novel written by James Hadley Chase .

A Gamut of Games is an innovative book of games written by Sid Sackson and first published in 1969 .
Dream Dancer is a 1980 novel by Janet Morris , the first in her Kerrion Space trilogy .
Visit to Godenholm ( German : Besuch auf Godenholm ) is a 1952 novella by the German writer Ernst Jünger .
Codex on the Flight of Birds is a relatively short codex of circa 1505 by Leonardo da Vinci .
Racism Explained to My Daughter ( by Tahar Ben Jelloun , 1998 , ISBN 88 - 7754 - 206 - 3 ) is a book in which the author , during a demonstration against an immigration law in Paris , answers his daughter 's questions about the reasons for racism .
People of the Fire is a 1991 historical fiction novel written by husband - and - wife co - authors W. Michael Gear & Kathleen O'Neal Gear .
Ritournelle de la faim ( The Same Old Story of Hunger , or The Refrain of Hunger ) is a novel written in French by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio .
On the Way Home is the diary of an American farm wife , Laura Ingalls Wilder , during her 1894 migration with husband Almanzo Wilder and seven - year - old daughter Rose from De Smet , South Dakota , to Mansfield , Missouri , where they settled permanently .
The Scarlatti Inheritance is the first of 27 thriller novels written ( the last four of them left in the form of manuscripts , later finalized by ghost writers ) by American author Robert Ludlum .
Theatrical Novel ( also A Dead Man 's Memoir ) is an unfinished novel by Mikhail Bulgakov .
The Butterfly 's Evil Spell ( El maleficio de la mariposa ) was the first play by the twentieth - century Spanish dramatist Federico García Lorca .
Det brinner ! ( It burns ! ) is a 1999 young adult novel written by Laura Trenter .
Textbook of Biochemistry , first published in 1928 , is scientific textbook authored by Alexander Thomas Cameron .
Lirael ( called Lirael : Daughter of the Clayr in some regions ) is a fantasy novel by Garth Nix , first published in 2001 .
The Genius of America ( 1923 ) is book written by Stuart Sherman .
A Farewell to Arms is a novel by Ernest Hemingway set during the Italian campaign of World War I. The book , published in 1929 , is a first - person account of American Frederic Henry , serving as a Lieutenant ( `` Tenente '' ) in the ambulance corps of the Italian Army .
Ten Days in a Mad - House is a book by newspaper reporter Nellie Bly .
The Piano Lesson is a 1990 play by American playwright August Wilson .
Inexcusable is a 2005 novel written by Chris Lynch in the young adult genre .
Johan Padan and the Discovery of the Americas is a one - man play by Dario Fo , recipient of the 1997 Nobel Prize in Literature .
End This Depression Now ! is a non - fiction book by Paul Krugman , an American economist and Nobel laureate .
To Light a Candle is the 2004 second fantasy novel of Mercedes Lackey and James Mallory 's Obsidian Trilogy .
`` The Shobies ' Story '' is a 1990 science fiction novella by American writer Ursula K. Le Guin , describing the story of the first human crew to participate in a newly invented faster - than - light mode of space travel .
Hell Has Harbour Views is a 2001 novel written by Richard Beasley .
The Honorary Consul is a British thriller novel by Graham Greene , published in 1973 .
The Entropy Tango is a novel by British fantasy and science fiction writer Michael Moorcock .
Blue of Noon ( French : Le Bleu du Ciel ) is an erotic novella by Georges Bataille .
My Prison Without Bars is Pete Rose 's autobiography , published by Rodale Press on January 8 , 2004 .
The Hollow Chest is a novel that was published in 1941 by Phoebe Atwood Taylor writing as Alice Tilton .
Legende sau basmele românilor ( `` Legends or Romanian Fairy - tales '' ) is a collection , in several volumes , of Romanian folktales , first published in 1872 by Petre Ispirescu .
The History of the Dividing Line Betwixt Virginia and North Carolina is an account by William Byrd II of the surveying of the border between the Colony of Virginia and the Province of North Carolina in 1728 .
I , Alex Cross is the 16th novel in the Alex Cross series by James Patterson .
Alec Forbes of Howglen is a novel by George MacDonald , first published in 1865 and is primarily concerned with Scottish country life .
Crusade in Jeans ( 1973 ) is a children 's novel written by Thea Beckman .
Neglected People ( Oboydyonnye , Обойдённые ) is a 1865 novel by Nikolai Leskov .
The Whiskey Rebels is an historical novel by American writer David Liss , inspired by events in the early history of the United States .
The Stone Angel , first published in 1964 by McClelland and Stewart , is perhaps the best - known of Margaret Laurence 's series of novels set in the fictitious town of Manawaka , Manitoba .
An Inland Voyage ( 1878 ) is a travelogue by Robert Louis Stevenson about a canoeing trip through France and Belgium in 1876 .
The Dragon of Despair is a 2004 fantasy novel , third of six in Jane Lindskold 's wolf series .
The Book of Folly is a 1972 collection of poetry by American writer Anne Sexton .
The General Scholium is an essay written by Isaac Newton , appended to his work of Philosophiæ Naturalis Principia Mathematica , known as the Principia .
Support and Defend is a political thriller novel in the Tom Clancy universe by Mark Greaney published on July 22 , 2014 by Putnam Adult .
A World Out of Time is a science fiction novel by Larry Niven and published in 1976 .
Missing Soluch ( Persian : جای خالی سلوچ‎ Ja - ye Khali - ye Soluch ; 1979 ) is a novel by Iranian author Mahmoud Dowlatabadi , translated from the Persian by Kamran Rastegar in 2007 .
Chitta Lahu ( Punjabi : ਚਿੱਟਾ ਲਹੂ ) is a Punjabi novel written by Punjabi novelist Nanak Singh .
The Opposite House is a novel by British author Helen Oyeyemi first published by Penguin Books in 2007 .
It 's Me , Eddie is the first novel by Russian writer and politician Eduard Limonov .
Beyond the Rocks is a 1906 novel by Elinor Glyn .
And Thereby Hangs a Tale ( ISBN 9780230531451 ) is British author Jeffrey Archer 's sixth collection of short stories .
The Forever King is a fantasy book written by Molly Cochran and Warren Murphy , the authors of Grandmaster , which reached # 3 on The New York Times bestseller list .
The Road to Mars is a 1999 science fiction comedic novel by Eric Idle .
The Rivers and Beacon - Hills of Gondor is a historical - etymological essay written by J. R. R. Tolkien sometime after June 1969 .
The Bugis is a book written by Christian Pelras about the Bugis people produced in 1996 and published in the United States in 1997 by Blackwell Publishing .
The Growth of Biological Thought ( 992 pages , Belknap Press , ISBN 0674364465 ) is a book written by Ernst Mayr , first published in 1982 .
The Flying Classroom ( German : Das Fliegende Klassenzimmer ) is a 1933 novel for children written by the German writer Erich Kästner .
Facing the Flag or For the Flag ( French : Face au drapeau ) is an 1896 patriotic novel by Jules Verne .
Uncle and the Battle for Badgertown ( 1973 ) is a children 's novel written by J. P. Martin , the last of his Uncle series of six books .
De Cive ( `` On the citizen '' ) is one of Thomas Hobbes 's major works .
Good Girls Do n't Wear Trousers ( Italian : Volevo i pantaloni ) is an autobiographical novel by Lara Cardella .
Ekattorer Dingulee ( Bengali : একাত্তরের দিনগুলি , English : Of Blood and Fire ( translator Mustafizur Rahman ) ) is an autobiographical book by Martyr - Mother Jahanara Imam based on her experiences of the liberation war of Bangladesh in 1971 .
The Defence of a Fool ( French : Le Plaidoyer d'un fou ) is an autobiographical novel by the Swedish writer August Strindberg .
Homage to Catalonia is George Orwell 's personal account of his experiences and observations in the Spanish Civil War .
Reading Writing ( French : En lisant en écrivant ) is a 1980 book by the French writer Julien Gracq .
The Tale of Mrs. Tiggy - Winkle is a children 's book written and illustrated by Beatrix Potter .

Hijo de ladrón ( Spanish : Son of a thief ) is a Chilean novel , written by Manuel Rojas .
Elämä lyhyt , Rytkönen pitkä ( `` Life short , Rytkönen long '' ) is a 1991 Finnish novel by Arto Paasilinna , While farcical throughout , from the title 's twist on the original saying onwards , it has a somewhat elegiac mood , with a constant undercurrent of tragedy leavened by humor .
`` The Creek of the Four Graves '' is a poem by Australian writer Charles Harpur that was first published in three parts in The Weekly Register of Politics , Facts and General Literature on 9 August , 16 August and 23 August 1845 .
The Westminster Shorter Catechism is a catechism written in 1646 and 1647 by the Westminster Assembly , a synod of English and Scottish theologians and laymen intended to bring the Church of England into greater conformity with the Church of Scotland .
The Peasants ( Polish : Chłopi ) is a novel written by Nobel Prize - winning Polish author Władysław Reymont in four parts between 1904 and 1909 .
Samuels bok ( lit . Samuel 's Book ) is a 1982 novel by Swedish author Sven Delblanc .
After the First Death ( 1979 ) is a suspense novel for young adults by American author Robert Cormier .
The Tragedy of the Moon is a collection of seventeen nonfiction science essays written by Isaac Asimov .
The Journeyer is a historical novel about Marco Polo , written by Gary Jennings and first published in 1984 .
Vespers in Vienna is a 1947 novel by Scottish writer Bruce Marshall .
Kit and Kitty : a story of west Middlesex is a three - volume novel by R. D. Blackmore published in 1890 .
The Two Towers is the second volume of J. R. R. Tolkien 's high fantasy novel The Lord of the Rings .
The Charlie Madigan series is a collection of urban fantasy novels by author Kelly Gay .
Ecclesiam suam is an encyclical of Pope Paul VI on the Catholic Church given at St. Peter 's , Rome , on the Feast of the Transfiguration , 6 August 1964 , the second year of his Pontificate .
This Alien Shore is a science fiction novel by the American author Celia S. Friedman .
Each In His Own Way ( Italian : Ciascuno a suo modo ( tʃaˈskuːno a ˈsuːo ˈmɔːdo ) ) is a 1924 play by Luigi Pirandello .
O mar na Lajinha is a Capeverdean novel published in 2004 by Germano Almeida .
My Friend Flicka is a 1941 novel by Mary O'Hara , about Ken McLaughlin , the son of a Wyoming rancher , and his horse Flicka .
Singularity 7 is a four - issue comic book mini - series created , written , and illustrated by Ben Templesmith .
Freedom and the Law is Italian jurist and philosopher Bruno Leoni 's most popular work .
The Valley of Horses is an historical fiction novel by Jean M. Auel .
The Seed of Earth is a science fiction novel by Robert Silverberg , originally published as an Ace Double in 1962 .
The Accumulation of Capital ( full title : The Accumulation of Capital : A Contribution to an Economic Explanation of Imperialism , Die Akkumulation des Kapitals : Ein Beitrag zur ökonomischen Erklärung des Imperialismus ) is the principal book length work of Rosa Luxemburg first published in 1913 .
The Complete Book of Running is a 1977 non - fiction book written by Jim Fixx .
Angry Candy is a 1988 collection of short stories by Harlan Ellison that is loosely organized around the theme of death .
The Mighty Miss Malone is a 2012 children 's novel by author Christopher Paul Curtis and is a followup to his 2000 book Bud , Not Buddy .
The Labyrinth of Solitude ( Spanish : El laberinto de la soledad ) is a book - length essay by Octavio Paz , first published in 1950 .
A Stir of Echoes is a 1958 novel by Richard Matheson that served as the inspiration for the 1999 film , Stir of Echoes .
The Cactaceae is a monograph on plants of the cactus family written by the American botanists Nathaniel Lord Britton and Joseph Nelson Rose and published in multiple volumes between 1919 and 1923 .
The Bone Garden is a 2007 novel written by Tess Gerritsen , loosely part of the Jane Rizzoli / Maura Isles series .
Natasha and Other Stories ( ISBN 0 - 374 - 28141 - 6 ) is a collection of short stories by Canadian author David Bezmozgis .
Black Seconds ( Norwegian : Svarte sekunder , 2002 ) is a novel by Norwegian writer Karin Fossum , the sixth in the Inspector Konrad Sejer series .
Alida 's Song is the sequel to The Cookcamp by Gary Paulsen .
The Dangerous Transmission is the title of a Hardy Boys Digest novel , credited to Franklin W. Dixon .
Gone Too Far ! is a 2007 play written by British playwright Bola Agbaje .
Voyage au pays des arbres is a novel written in French by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio .
The Golden Fleece and the Heroes Who Lived Before Achilles is a children 's book by Padraic Colum , a retelling of Greek myths .
The Old Men at the Zoo is a novel written by Angus Wilson , first published in 1961 by Secker and Warburg , and by Penguin books in 1964 .
The surviving Hellenica is an important work of the Greek writer Xenophon and one of the principal sources for the final seven years of the Peloponnesian War not covered by Thucydides , and the war 's aftermath .
`` A Nasty Story '' ( Russian : Скверный анекдот , Skverny anekdot ) , also translated as `` A Disgraceful Affair '' , as well as `` A Most Unfortunate Incident '' and `` An Unpleasant Predicament '' , is a satirical short story by Fyodor Dostoyevsky concerning the escapades of a Russian civil servant .
Brother Odd is a novel by Dean Koontz , published in 2006 .
The Liberty Project is an American comic book series created by writer Kurt Busiek and artist James W. Fry .
Poor Fellow My Country is a Miles Franklin Award winning novel by Australian author Xavier Herbert .
The Divine Invasion is a BSFA Award nominated 1981 science fiction book by Philip K. Dick .
Lord Loss is the first novel in the Demonata series written by best - selling teenage horror author Darren Shan .
Kundalatha ( or Kundalata , Malayalam : കുന്ദലത ) is a novel by Appu Nedungadi , published in 1887 .
Muhammad at Medina is a book about early Islam written by the non - Muslim Islamic scholar , professor William Montgomery Watt .
Letters to a Philosophical Unbeliever ( 1780 ) is a multi - volume series of books on metaphysics by eighteenth - century British polymath Joseph Priestley .
Space Apprentice , also known as Probationers ( Russian title : Стажёры , Stazhory ) , is one of the early novels of Russian science fiction writers Arkady and Boris Strugatsky .
`` Lost in the Andes ! '' is a Donald Duck story written by Carl Barks in April 1949 .
Liberty Meadows is a comic strip and comic book created , written and illustrated by Frank Cho .
Betsy and the Great World ( 1952 ) is the ninth volume in the Betsy - Tacy series of children 's fiction by Maud Hart Lovelace .
A Death in the Small Hours , by Charles Finch , is a novel set in England during the Victorian era .
Doctor Sally is a short novel by P.G. Wodehouse , first published in the United Kingdom on April 7 , 1932 by Methuen & Co. , London .
The Law of Nines is a thriller / speculative fiction novel by American author Terry Goodkind .
When Dad Married Fury is a 2012 play by David Williamson .
Final Blackout is a dystopic science fiction novel by author L. Ron Hubbard .
The History and Adventures of an Atom , by Tobias Smollett , is a novel that savagely satirises English politics during the Seven Years ' War .
History of Materialism and Critique of its Present Importance ( German : Geschichte des Materialismus und Kritik seiner Bedeutung in der Gegenwart ) is a philosophical work by Friedrich Albert Lange , originally written in German and published in October 1865 ( although the year of publication was given as 1866 ) .
Grandfather Stories is a book of 23 historical tales by journalist and novelist Samuel Hopkins Adams .
Pretties is a 2005 science fiction novel and the second book of the Uglies Trilogy written by Scott Westerfeld .
Faith Healer is a play by Brian Friel about the life of the faith healer Francis Hardy as monologued through the shifting memories of Hardy , his wife , Grace , and stage manager , Teddy .
The Clue in the Diary is the seventh volume in the Nancy Drew Mystery Stories series , and was first published in 1932 under the pseudonym Carolyn Keene .
Pamphilia to Amphilanthus is a sonnet sequence by the English Renaissance poet Lady Mary Wroth , first published as part of The Countess of Montgomery 's Urania in 1621 , but subsequently published separately .
The Morning Gift is a bestselling novel by the English author Eva Ibbotson , based on her own experience as a refugee .
Unto a Good Land ( Swedish : Invandrarna ) is a novel by Vilhelm Moberg from 1952 .
An Experiment in Criticism is a 1961 book by C. S. Lewis in which he proposes that the quality of books should be measured not by how they are written , but by how they are read .
The Horsecatcher is a 1957 adolescent novel by author Mari Sandoz .
A Cold Heart is a mystery novel by American author Jonathan Kellerman
The Commentariolus ( Little Commentary ) is Nicolaus Copernicus 's 40-page outline of an early version of his revolutionary heliocentric theory of the universe .
When Heaven Fell is a 1995 military science fiction novel by William Barton .
Ludzie bezdomni ( Homeless people ) is a book written by Stefan Żeromski in 1899 in Zakopane , Poland , published for the first time in 1900 .
Childe Harold 's Pilgrimage is a lengthy narrative poem in four parts written by Lord Byron .
Introduction to Objectivist Epistemology is a work of philosophy by Ayn Rand and Leonard Peikoff , which Rand considered her philosophical treatise .
Un gentilhomme is a novel by the French novelist and playwright Octave Mirbeau , published by Flammarion in 1920 , after his death .
Moonfleet is a tale of smuggling by the English novelist J. Meade Falkner , first published in 1898 .
The Seven Hills is a 2005 alternate history novel by American writer John Maddox Roberts , a sequel to his 2002 novel Hannibal 's Children .
Der Stechlin is a novel by Theodor Fontane written between 1895 and 1897 , and first published in the literary journal Über Land und Meer .
`` The Concentration City '' is a dystopian short story by British author J. G. Ballard , first published , under the title `` Build - Up '' in New Worlds volume 19 number 55 in January 1957 .
