Jade Boho Sayo ( born 30 August 1986 ) , commonly known as Jade , is a Spanish - born Equatorial Guinean professional footballer who plays as a striker for Reading of England 's FA WSL .
Paula Vázquez Picallo ( born 26 November 1974 ) , popularly known as Paula Vázquez , is a Spanish television presenter , also known for her modelling career in the fashion industry as well as her acting .
Isabel Coixet Castillo ( Catalan pronunciation : ( izəˈβɛɫ kuˈʃɛt ) ; born 9 April 1960 ) is a Spanish film director .
Joseph Decaisne ( 7 March 1807 -- January 1882 ) was a French botanist and agronomist .
Salvatore Fiume ( 23 October 1915 -- 3 June 1997 ) was an Italian painter , sculptor , architect , writer and stage designer .
Luigi Salerno ( 1924 - -1992 ) was an Italian historian of Italian art and historiographer .
Alexander Pope ( 21 May 1688 -- 30 May 1744 ) was an 18th - century English poet .
Hanna Hellquist ( real name : Hanna Victoria Hellqvist , born 24 July 1980 in Karlstad ) is a Swedish journalist , TV host and writer .
Modest Ilyich Tchaikovsky ( Russian : Моде́ст Ильи́ч Чайко́вский ; 13 May ( O.S. 1 May ) 1850 - -15 January ( O.S. 2 January ) 1916 ) was a Russian dramatist , opera librettist and translator .
Jean Ribault ( 1520 -- October 12 , 1565 ) was a French naval officer , navigator , and a colonizer of what would become the southeastern United States .
Léon Gustave Schlumberger ( 17 October 1844 -- 9 May 1929 ) was a French historian and numismatist who specialised in the era of the crusades and the Byzantine Empire .
José del Campillo y Cossío ( February 13 , 1693 in Alles , Peñamellera Alta , Asturias -- April 11 , 1743 in Madrid ) , was a Spanish statesman .
Louis - Vincent Thomas ( 20 May 1922 -- 22 January 1994 ) was a French sociologist , anthropologist , ethnologist , and scholar whose specialty was Africa .
Jean Désiré Gustave Courbet ( French : ( ɡystav kuʁbɛ ) ; 10 June 1819 -- 31 December 1877 ) was a French painter who led the Realist movement in 19th - century French painting .
Friedrich Christian Delius ( born 1943 ) is an acclaimed German writer .
Konstantine Gamsakhurdia ( Georgian : კონსტანტინე გამსახურდია ) ( May 3 , 1893 -- July 17 , 1975 ) was a Georgian writer and public figure , who , along with Mikheil Javakhishvili , is considered to be one of the most influential Georgian novelists of the 20th century .
August Friedrich Müller ( 15 December 1684 -- 1 May 1761 ) was a German legal scholar and logician .
Antonio Citterio ( 1950 , Meda - ) is an Italian architect , furniture designer and industrial designer who lives and works in Milan .
Eugen Kapp ( 13 May 1908 -- 29 October 1996 ) was an Estonian composer and music educator .
Wenzel Anton , Prince of Kaunitz - Rietberg ( Czech : Václav Antonín z Kounic a Rietbergu , German : Wenzel Anton Fürst von Kaunitz - Rietberg ) ( 2 February 1711 -- 27 June 1794 ) was a diplomat and statesman of the Holy Roman Empire .
Ricciotto Canudo ( 2 January 1877 -- 1923 ) was an early Italian film theoretician who lived primarily in France .
María Teresa Táboas Veleiro ( born 1961 in Mexico City , Mexico ) is an architect , professor and Galician politician .
Wang Jingwei ( Wang Ching - wei ; 4 May 1883 -- 10 November 1944 ) ; born as Wang Zhaoming ( Wang Chao - ming ) , but widely known by his pen name `` Jingwei '' , was a Chinese politician .
Sarah Bowdich Lee ( née Wallis ) ( 10 Sep 1791 - 22 Sep 1856 ) was an English author , illustrator , traveller , zoologist , botanist , and pteridologist .
Abílio Manuel Guerra Junqueiro ( September 17 , 1850 -- July 7 , 1923 ) was a Portuguese top civil servant , member of the Portuguese House of Representatives , journalist , author , and poet .
Michael Reeves ( 17 October 1943 -- 11 February 1969 ) was an English film director and screenwriter .
Bella Fromm ( 20 December 1890 -- 9 February 1972 ) was a German journalist and author of Jewish origin , who lived in exile in the United States from 1938 .
Luis Bayón Herrera ( 23 September 1889 -- 30 March 1956 ) was a Spanish film director and screenwriter who worked in Argentine film of the 1940s and 1950s .
Bernardo de Alderete ( 1565 - -1645 ) was a Spanish erudite and writer .
Íngrid Coronado Fritz ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ˈiŋɡɾið koɾoˈnaðo ) ; born July 12 , 1974 in Mexico City , Mexico ) is a well - known Mexican television personality .
Ambrosio de Benavides Medina Liñán y Torres ( January 20 , 1718 -- April 27 , 1787 ) was a Spanish colonial administrator who served as Royal Governor of Puerto Rico , Royal Governor of Charcas and Royal Governor of Chile .
Hubert Knoblauch ( born March 21 , 1959 ) is a German sociologist , he is known for his work on Sociology of knowledge , Sociology of Religion , Qualitative research and Videography .
Batya Gur ( Hebrew : בתיה גור‎ , 1 September 1947 -- 19 May 2005 ) was an Israeli writer .
Edward Capern ( 21 January 1819 -- 5 June 1894 ) , was an English poet , best known for The Devonshire Melodist and Wayside Warbles .
Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay , alternatively spelt as Sarat Chandra Chatterjee , ( 15 September 1876 -- 16 January 1938 ) , was a Bengali novelist and short story writer of early 20th century .
François Hinard ( 27 September 1941 -- 19 September 2008 ) was a French historian specialising in Ancient Rome .
Carmen Blanco ( Lugo , Galicia , Spain , 1954 ) is a Spanish feminist writer and activist .
Francesco Mario Pagano ( 8 December 1748 -- 29 October 1799 ) was an Italian jurist , author , thinker , and the founder of the Neapolitan school of law .
John Dee ( 13 July 1527 -- 1608 or 1609 ) was an English mathematician , astronomer , astrologer , occult philosopher , imperialist , and adviser to Queen Elizabeth I. He devoted much of his life to the study of alchemy , divination , and Hermetic philosophy .
Don Pedro de Alberni , sometimes known as Pere d'Alberní i Teixidor in Catalan ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ˈpeɾə ðəɫβərˈni ) ) ( Tortosa , January 30 , 1747 -- Monterrey , New Spain , March 11 , 1802 ) was a Spanish soldier who served the Spanish Crown for almost all his life .
Léon Serpollet ( 4 October 1858 - 1 February 1907 ) was a French industrialist and pioneer of steam automobiles , under the Gardner - Serpollet brand .
Robert Jaulin ( 7 March 1928 , Le Cannet , Alpes - Maritimes -- 21 November 1996 , Grosrouvre ) was a French ethnologist .
Giuseppe Penone ( born 3 April 1947 ) is an Italian artist .
Otto Gutfreund ( August 1889 -- 2 June 1927 ) , also written Oto Gutfreund , was a Czech - Czechoslovak sculptor .
Sukanta Bhattacharya ( Bengali : সুকান্ত ভট্টাচার্য ) ( Bhôṭṭācharjo ) ( 15 August 1926 -- 13 May 1947 ) was a Bengali poet and playwright .
Andri Snær Magnason is an Icelandic writer .
Julián Ribera y Tarragó ( Carcaixent , Valencia , 19 February 1858 -- 2 May 1934 , La Pobla Llarga , Valencia ) was a Spanish Arabist and academic .
Philippe Croizon ( born 1968 ) is a French athlete and the first quadruple amputee to swim across the English Channel .
Ville Ranta is a Finnish cartoonist from Oulu .
Hermann Brockhaus ( January 28 , 1806 -- January 5 , 1877 ) was a German Orientalist born in Amsterdam .
George Boole ( /ˈbuːl/ ; 2 November 1815 -- 8 December 1864 ) was an English mathematician , educator , philosopher and logician .
Aydilge Sarp ( born 1979 ) is a Turkish writer , poet and singer - songwriter .

Sistanova were a German girl group from Frankfurt am Main , which was founded in 2005 .
Miroslav Horníček ( 10 November 1918 in Plzeň -- 15 February 2003 in Liberec ) was a Czech actor , writer , director , artist and theatre theoretician .
Giacopo Belgrado , ( November 16 , 1704 in Udine -- March 26 , 1789 in Udine ) Italian Jesuit and natural philosopher .
Miquel Martí i Pol ( Catalan pronunciation : ( miˈkɛɫ mərˈti j ˈpɔɫ ) ) ( 19 March 1929 -- 11 November 2003 ) was one of the most popular Catalan poets in Catalan in the 20th century .

Feng Yuanjun ( Chinese : 冯沅君 , September 4 , 1900 -- June 17 , 1974 ) was a writer and scholar of Chinese classical literature and literary history .

Jan Łasicki ( Latin : Johannis Lasitii or Lasicius ; 1534 - -1602 ) was a Polish historian and theologian .
Carlo Castellaneta ( 8 February 1930 - 28 September 2013 ) was an Italian author and journalist .

Louise Marie - Jeanne Hersent - Mauduit ( 1784 -- 1862 ) , was a 19th - century French painter .
Eli Lotar ( January 30 , 1905 -- February 22 , 1969 ) was a French photographer and cinematographer .
Richard Rolle ( 1290/1300 - - late September 1349 ) was an English hermit , mystic , and religious writer .
Clive Barker ( born 5 October 1952 ) is an English writer , film director , and visual artist best known for his work in both fantasy and horror fiction .
Joseph Bernard ( 1866 , Vienne , Isère -- 1931 ) was a modern classical French sculptor , featured on the frontispiece of Elie Faure 's 1927 survey of modern art , `` Spirit of Forms '' .
José Miguel Monzón Navarro ( 15 May 1955 , Madrid ) , better known as El Gran Wyoming ( The Great Wyoming ) or Guayo , is a Spanish television presenter , actor , musician , director and humorist .
George Savile , 1st Marquess of Halifax PC FRS ( 11 November 1633 -- 5 April 1695 ) was an English statesman , writer , and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 , and in the House of Lords after he was raised to the peerage in 1668 .
Richard Pischel ( January 18 , 1849 - December 26 , 1908 ) was a German Indologist born in Breslau .
Sir Edmund Buckley , 1st Baronet ( 16 April 1834 -- 21 March 1910 ) was an English landowner and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1865 to 1878 .
Niccola Francesco Ippolito Baldassarre Rosellini , known simply as Ippolito Rosellini ( August 13 , 1800 -- June 4 , 1843 ) was an Italian Egyptologist .
Pietro Giannone ( 7 May 1676 -- 17 March 1748 ) was an Italian historian born in Ischitella , in the province of Foggia .
Hortensio Félix Paravicino y Arteaga ( 12 October 1580 -- 12 December 1633 ) was a Spanish preacher and poet from the noble house of Pallavicini .
Ruzha Lazarova ( Bulgarian Cyrillic , Ружа Лазарова;Sofia , 1968 ) is a Bulgarian French language writer who currently lives in Paris .
Ramon Muntaner ( Catalan pronunciation : ( rəˈmom muntəˈne ) ) ( c. 1270 -- 1336 ) was a Catalan soldier and writer who wrote the Crònica , a chronicle of his life , including his adventures as a commander in the Catalan Company .
Jean - Paul Goude ( born 8 December 1940 ) is a French graphic designer , illustrator , photographer and advertising film director .
Jean - Baptiste Lislet Geoffroy ( 23 August 1755 -- 8 February 1836 ) was a French astronomer , botanist and cartographer .
Paul Cernat ( born August 5 , 1972 in Bucharest ) is a Romanian essayist and literary critic .
Sukumaran became a popular film star in Malayalam cinema during the 1970s .
Jonas Hassen Khemiri ( born 27 December 1978 in Stockholm ) is an award - winning Swedish novelist and playwright .
Antonio Goicoechea ( 21 January 1876 , Barcelona - 11 February 1953 ) was an Alfonsine monarchist in Spain during the period of the Second Spanish Republic and the Spanish Civil War .
Manfred Karge ( born Brandenburg an der Havel , 1938 ) is a German dramatist .
Jan Costin Wagner ( Langen , b. Oct 13th 1972 - ) is a German crime fiction writer .
Jean - Paul Roux , PhD ( 5 January 1925 -- 29 June 2009 ) was a French Turkologue and a specialist of Islamic culture .
Nakatsukasa ( 中務 , 912 - -991 ) was a Japanese Waka poet from the middle Heian period .
Alexander Pendarves , MP ( baptised 11 November 1662 -- 13 March 1726 , London , England ) was an English politician of the Tory party , and a wealthy landowner .
Jan Rokita ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈjan rɔˈkʲita ) , born 18 June 1959 in Kraków ) is a Polish conservative politician , a member of the Sejm , the lower chamber of the Polish parliament .
Giuseppe Saragat ( Italian pronunciation : ( dʒuˈzɛppe ˈsaːraɡat ) ; 19 September 1898 -- 11 June 1988 ) was an Italian politician who was the fifth President of the Italian Republic from 1964 to 1971 .
Thomas Starkey ( c. 1495 - -1538 ) was an English political theorist and humanist .
Frederick William Hope ( 3 January 1797 -- 15 April 1862 ) was an English entomologist and founder of the Hope Department of Entomology at the University of Oxford .
Hannes Hólmsteinn Gissurarson ( born February 19 , 1953 in Reykjavík , Iceland ) is a professor of political science at the University of Iceland and a frequent commentator on current affairs in the Icelandic media .
Bernardino de Sahagún ( Spanish pronunciation : ( bernarˈðino ðe saaˈɣun ) ; 1499 -- October 23 , 1590 ) was a Franciscan friar , missionary priest and pioneering ethnographer who participated in the Catholic evangelization of colonial New Spain ( now Mexico ) .
Antonio Enríquez Gómez ( c. 1601 -- c. 1661 ) , Spanish dramatist , poet and novelist of Portuguese - Jewish origin , was known in the early part of his career as Enríque Enríquez de Paz .
Jacques Babinet ( French : ( babinɛ ) ; 5 March 1794 -- 21 October 1872 ) was a French physicist , mathematician , and astronomer who is best known for his contributions to optics .
Max Dauthendey ( 25 July 1867 -- 29 August 1918 ) was a German author and painter of the impressionistic period .
Simo Matavulj ( Serbian : Симо Матавуљ , 14 September 1852 -- 20 February 1908 ) was a Serbian novelist , a representative of lyric realism , especially in short prose .
Louis Doutreleau ( 1909 - 2005 ) was a French Jesuit priest closely associated over a long period with the publishing enterprise of the Sources Chrétiennes Institute in Lyons .
Leah Moore ( born 4 February 1978 ) is an English comic book writer , best known for Albion and Wild Girl .
Erhard Wittek ( 3 December 1898 -- 4 June 1981 ) , better known for his pen name Fritz Steuben , was a German author who wrote war novels and stories depicting American Indians ( particularly the life of the Shawnee chief Tecumseh ) .
Lucien Clergue ( French : ( klɛʁg ) ; August 14 , 1934 -- November 15 , 2014 ) was a French photographer .
François Marcela - Froideval ( born 10 December 1958 ) is a French role - playing game creator , video game producer , and comic scenarist Froideval had a major influence on the introduction of role - playing games in France , mainly as editor in chief of the Casus Belli role - playing magazine .
Sir William Stapleton , 4th Baronet ( c.1698 - -1740 ) was an English politician and Jacobite .
Fabrice d'Almeida was born on 15 November 1963 and is a French historian .
Mouna Noureddine ( Arabic : منى نور الدين‎ ) ( born in Tunis on January 23 , 1937 ) is a Tunisian actress .
Annette Becker ( 1953 ) is a French historian specializing in study of World War I. She is daughter of the historian Jean - Jacques Becker .
Carl Louis Ferdinand von Lindemann ( April 12 , 1852 -- March 6 , 1939 ) was a German mathematician , noted for his proof , published in 1882 , that π ( pi ) is a transcendental number , meaning it is not a root of any polynomial with rational coefficients .
Thomas Heywood ( /ˈheɪwʊd/ ; early 1570s -- 16 August 1641 ) was a prominent English playwright , actor , and author .
Georges Hanna Sabbagh ( 1877 - -1951 ) was an Egyptian and French artist .
Mihály Tompa ( September 28 , 1819 -- July 30 , 1868 ) , Hungarian lyric poet , was born in Rimaszombat , in the county of Gömör , his father being village bootmaker .
Silvia Jato ( born June 6 , 1971 in Lugo , Spain ) is a Spanish TV presenter and model .
Claudia Kohde - Kilsch ( born 11 December 1963 ) is a former German tennis player and member of the Die Linke .
Fatos Lubonja ( born 1951 ) is an Albanian writer and dissident .
Aristodemo Costoli ( 1803 - -1871 ) was an Italian sculptor who spent his entire career in the city of Florence .
Bronisław Maj ( born 19 November 1953 ) is a Polish poet , essayist , translator and academic .
Diego Buñuel is a French film - maker born in 1975 and the host and director of the National Geographic Channel series , Do n't Tell My Mother .
Antonio Ferrandis Monrabal ( 28 February 1921 -- 16 October 2000 ) was a Spanish actor , remembered especially for his character Chanquete .
John Anstis ( 29 August 1669 -- 4 March 1744 ) was an English officer of arms and antiquarian .
Philippe Dana ( born on 5 September 1959 ) is a French journalist , producer , radio and television host .
Robert Ward or from 1828 Robert Plumer Ward ( 19 March 1765 -- 13 August 1846 ) , was an English barrister , politician , and novelist .
Edwin Lascelles , 1st Baron Harewood ( 1713 , in Barbados -- 25 January 1795 ) was a wealthy West Indian plantation owner of English ancestry .
Louis de Beaufort ( 6 October 1703 -- 11 August 1795 ) was a French historian of whose life little is known .
Robert Bober ( born 1931 ) is a French film director , theater director and writer of German - Jewish origin .
Daphne Marlatt was born to English parents , Arthur and Edrys Lupprian Buckle , in Melbourne , Australia on July 11 , 1942 .
Hermann Graedener or Grädener ( 8 May 1844 -- 15 September 1929 ) was a German composer , conductor and teacher .
Mariam Petrosyan ( Armenian : Մարիամ Պետրոսյան , born 10 August 1969 ) is an Armenian painter , cartoonist and Russian - language novelist , most known as the author of the award - winning novel The House , in Which ... ( 2009 ) .
William Willy ( 1703?--65 ) , of New Park Devizes , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Francesco Mastriani ( 1819 - -1891 ) was an Italian novelist .
Robert Misrahi ( born 3 January 1926 ) is a French philosopher who specialises in Spinoza .
Franz Halder ( 30 June 1884 -- 2 April 1972 ) was a German general and the chief of the OKH General Staff from 1938 until September 1942 , when he was dismissed after frequent disagreements with Adolf Hitler .
Cornelius Cruys ( Russian : Крюйс , Корнелий Иванович ) ( 1655 -- 1727 ) was a Dutch Vice Admiral of the Imperial Russian Navy and the first commander of the Russian Baltic Fleet .
Ercole Bottrigari ( 1531 - -1612 ) was an Italian scholar , mathematician , poet , music theorist , architect , and composer .
Siegfried Zielinski is a German media theorist .
Diego Vallejo Folgueira ( born 13 February 1973 in Meira , Lugo , Spain ) is a Spanish rally co - driver .
Józef Jeżowski ( 1793 - 1855 ) was a Polish philologist and poet .
Juan Marsé Carbó ( born January 8 , 1933 in Barcelona ) is a Spanish novelist , journalist and screenwriter .
Clémence Royer ( 21 April 1830 , Nantes , Loire - Atlantique -- 6 February 1902 ) was a self - taught French scholar who lectured and wrote on economics , philosophy , science and feminism .
Charles Aldworth ( 1677 - 21 September 1714 ) was an English politician , MP for New Windsor from 1712 to 1714 .
Felix Fechenbach ( 28 January 1894 -- 7 August 1933 ) was a German - Jewish journalist , poet and political activist .
Jean Aicardi ( 8 November 1926 -- 3 August 2015 ) was a French doctor .
Luigi Fantappiè ( 15 September 1901 -- 28 July 1956 ) was an Italian mathematician , known for work in mathematical analysis and for creating the theory of analytic functionals : he was a student and follower of Vito Volterra .
Andreas Rumpf ( 3 December 1890 -- 22 June 1966 ) was a German classical archaeologist born in Potsdam .
Jean - Yves Girard ( born 1947 ) is a French logician working in proof theory .
Guy Du Faur , Seigneur de Pibrac ( 1529 - -1584 ) was a French jurist and poet .
Don Alonso Fajardo de Entenza y de Guevara , Córdoba y Velasco , Knight of Alcantara , Lord of Espinardo ( died July 1624 , in the Philippines ) was Spanish Governor - General and Captain - General of the Islands of the Philippines from 3 July 1618 until his death .
Marianne Gullestad ( 28 March 1946 -- 10 March 2008 ) was a Norwegian social anthropologist .
Friedrich Wilhelm Foerster ( 1869 - -1966 ) was a German academic , educationist , pacifist and philosopher , known for his public opposition to Nazism .
Jerzy Szaniawski ( Zegrzynek , 10 February 1886 -- 16 March 1970 , Warsaw ) was a Polish writer , playwright , and essayist ; an elected member of the prestigious Polish Academy of Literature in the interwar period .
André Courrèges ( pronounced : ( andʁe kuʁɛʒ ) ; 9 March 1923 -- 7 January 2016 ) was a French fashion designer .
Madeleine Castaing ( French pronunciation : ​(madlɛn kastɛ̃ ) ) ( 1894 - -1992 ) was a French antique dealer and interior designer of international renown .
Masayuki Fujio ( 藤尾 正行 Fujio Masayuki , January 1 , 1917 -- October 22 , 2006 ) was the Japanese Minister of Education , under the government of Yasuhiro Nakasone until 1986 .
Michael Servetus ( /sərˈviːtəs/ ; Spanish : Miguel Serveto ) , also known as Miguel Servet , Miguel Serveto , Revés , or Michel de Villeneuve ( 29 September 1509 or 1511 -- 27 October 1553 ) , was a Spanish theologian , physician , cartographer , and Renaissance humanist .
Felix Thijssen ( born November 24 , 1933 in Rijswijk ) is a Dutch author of crime novels , science fiction novels and books for children .
Claude Bébéar ( born 1935 ) is a French businessman .
Ernest Désiré Glasson ( 1839 - 1907 ) was a French academic and jurist .
Francesc Gay i Puig , better known as Cesc Gay ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ˈsɛzɡ ˈɡaj ) ; Barcelona , 1967 ) , is a Catalan - Spanish film screenwriter and film director .
Miguel Poblet i Orriols ( 18 March 1928 -- 6 April 2013 ) was a Spanish professional cyclist whose career lasted from 1944 to 1962 , during which he had over 200 professional victories .
W. C. Firebaugh was the author of two works on the history of inns and taverns , and also of a fine English translation of Petronius 's Satyricon , the fragmentary realistic novel of low life under the Roman Empire .
Louis Lapicque ( 1 August 1860 -- 6 December 1954 ) was a French neuroscientist , socialist activist , antidreyfusard and freemason who was very influential in the early 20th century .
Juan Manuel Burgos Velasco ( born 1961 , Valladolid , Spain ) is a Spanish Personalist philosopher .
Eugenio Garza Sada ( January 11 , 1892 -- September 17 , 1973 ) was an industrialist in the city of Monterrey , Mexico best known for founding the Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education ( ITESM in Spanish ) school system in the country .
Jacques Rivette ( French : ( ʒak ʁivɛt ) ; 1 March 1928 -- 29 January 2016 ) was a French film director and film critic most commonly associated with the French New Wave and Cahiers du Cinéma .
Bernhard Heinrich Overberg ( 1 May 1754 -- 1826 ) was a German Roman Catholic ecclesiastic , educator and author .
Jean Marc Gaspard Itard ( April 24 , 1774 , Oraison , Alpes - de - Haute - Provence -- July 5 , 1838 , Paris ) was a French physician born in Provence .
Victor Guérin ( 15 September 1821 , Paris - 21 September 1891 ) was a French intellectual , explorer and amateur archaeologist .
Robert Curzon , 14th Baron Zouche ( 16 March 1810 -- 2 August 1873 ) , styled The Honourable Robert Curzon between 1829 and 1870 , was an English traveller , diplomat and author , active in the Near East .
Claude Gay , often named Claudio Gay in Spanish texts , ( March 18 , 1800 -- November 29 , 1873 ) , was a French botanist , naturalist and illustrator .
Richard Bonney ( born 1947 ) is an English historian and priest .
Juan Piquer Simón ( 16 February 1935 , Valencia -- January 8 , 2011 , Valencia ) was a Spanish film director most well known for directing two cult classic horror exploitation films , Pieces ( 1982 ) and Slugs :
Franz Babinger ( January 15 , 1891 -- June 23 , 1967 ) was a well - known German orientalist and historian of the Ottoman Empire , best known for his biography of the great Ottoman emperor Mehmed II known as the Conqueror , originally published as Mehmed der Eroberer und seine Zeit .
Ephraim Stern ( Hebrew : אפרים שטרן ) ( born January 15 , 1934 ) is an Israeli archeologist and an expert , specializing in the research of the Late First Temple period ( Assyrian Age ) , the Babylonian period and the Persian period Persian Empire , .
Christina Rosenvinge Hepworth ( born May 29 , 1964 , in Madrid ) is a Spanish singer - songwriter , actress and producer , born to a Danish parents , Hans Jørgen Christian Rosenvinge , and Danish / British , mother Daphne Ankerstjerne Hepworth .
Reiner Kunze ( born 16 August 1933 , in Oelsnitz , Erzgebirge , Saxony ) is a German writer and GDR dissident .
Avraham Even - Shoshan ( Hebrew : אַבְרָהָם אֶבֶן שׁוֹשָׁן ; 1906 - -1984 ) was a Russian - born Hebrew linguist and lexicographer , compiler of the Even - Shoshan dictionary , one of the foremost dictionaries of the Hebrew language .
John Fulleylove ( 18 Aug 1845 -- 22 May 1908 ) was an English landscape artist and illustrator .
Gunther von Hagens ( born Gunther Gerhard Liebchen ; 10 January 1945 ) is a German anatomist who invented the technique for preserving biological tissue specimens called plastination .
Louis - Henri Brévière , born at Forges - les - Eaux in 1797 , was a French wood - engraver , to whom is due the honour of having revived the art of wood - engraving , which had been neglected in France since the 17th century .
Julian Stryjkowski , born Pesach Stark ( April 27 , 1905 -- August 8 , 1996 ) was a Polish journalist and writer , notable for his social prose of radical leftist leanings .
Pierre - Marie Théas ( September 14 , 1894 -- April 3 , 1977 ) was a French Roman Catholic Bishop of Montauban and Bishop of Tarbes and Lourdes .
Najem Wali ( Arabic : نجم والي‎ ; born 1956 ) is an Iraqi novelist and journalist , based in Germany .
Ramón Rubial Cavia ( 28 October 1906 -- 1999 ) was a Spanish socialist leader .
Philippe Flajolet ( French : ( flaʒɔlɛ ) ; 1 December 1948 -- 22 March 2011 ) was a French computer scientist .
Ascanio Sobrero ( October 12 , 1812 -- May 26 , 1888 ) was an Italian chemist , born in Casale Monferrato .
Prince Witold Czartoryski ( 1824 - 1865 ) was a Polish noble ( szlachcic ) .
Kató Hámán ( 2 December 1884 -- 31 August 1936 ) was a Hungarian Esperanto and Communist activist .
Peter Bichsel ( born March 24 , 1935 ) is a popular Swiss - German writer and journalist representing modern German literature .
Eugène Varlin ( 5 October 1839 -- 28 May 1871 ) was a French socialist , communard and member of the First International .
Blanco 's character , Griselda Blanco , is portrayed by Mexican actress Ana Serradilla , in the Spanish - language telenovela La Viuda Negra ( 2014 ) , an adaptation of the book La patrona de Pablo Escobar de José Guarnizo .
Renata Polverini ( Born Rome , 14 May 1962 ) is an Italian politician and trade unionist .
Jean - Baptiste Berlier ( 1841 - -1911 ) was a French engineer and inventor who was responsible for the Pneumatic tube postal system of Paris , which operated until as late as 1984 .
Umberto Mastroianni ( September 21 , 1910 in Fontana Liri -- February 25 , 1998 in Marino , Italy ) , was an Italian abstract sculptor .
James Halse ( 28 January 1769 -- 14 May 1838 ) was an English lawyer and wealthy businessman in Cornwall .
Cheikh Tidiane Gaye is a Senegalese - Italian writer .
James Bouillé ( February 14 , 1894 -- June 22 , 1945 ) was a French architect based in Brittany .
Claude Delvincourt ( 12 January 1888 -- 5 April 1954 ) was a French pianist and composer of classical music .
Šišmundo Menčetić Vlahović , known simply as Šiško Menčetić ( pronounced ( ʃîʃkɔ mɛ̂ntʃɛtitɕ ) ; Italian : Sigismondo Menze ; 1457 - -1527 ) was a Croatian poet , chiefly creating his opus in the 15th century .
Gertrude Caton Thompson ( 1 February 1888 -- 18 April 1985 ) was an influential English archaeologist at a time when participation by women in the discipline was uncommon .
Edmund Glaise - Horstenau ( also known as Edmund Glaise von Horstenau ; 27 February 1882 -- 20 July 1946 ) was an Austrian officer in the Bundesheer , last Vice - Chancellor of Austria before the 1938 Anschluss , and general in the German Wehrmacht during the Second World War .
Oronce Finé ( or Fine ; Latin : Orontius Finnaeus or Finaeus ; Italian : Oronzio Fineo ; 20 December 1494 -- 8 August 1555 ) was a French mathematician and cartographer .
Jean - Luc Lahaye ( born Jean - Luc Laheaye , 23 December 1952 , Paris ) is a French pop singer , former television host and occasional writer .

Jorge Ordaz Gargallo ( born 1946 ) is a Spanish writer and geologist .
Martin Schøyen ( born January 31 , 1940 ) is a Norwegian businessman , traveller , historian , paleographer and collector of books .
Antonio Ros de Olano ( November 9 , 1808 - July 24 , 1886 ) was a Venezuelan - born Spanish writer , politician and military officer who served in the First Carlist War and the Spanish - Moroccan War of 1859 .
Lev Ozerov ( Russian : Лев Адольфович Озеров ) ( August 10/23 , 1914 -- March 18 , 1996 ) was a Jewish - Ukrainian Soviet poet born in Kiev .

Heinrich Rose ( 6 August 1795 -- 27 January 1864 ) was a German mineralogist and analytical chemist .
Nobuteru Mori was a Japan businessman and politician who founded Showa Denko , a leading Japanese chemical engineering firm , in the 1930s .
Karl Eduard Zachariae von Lingenthal ( December 24 , 1812 -- June 3 , 1894 ) was an eminent German jurist and the son of Karl Salomo Zachariae von Lingenthal .
Hans Noever ( born 10 May 1928 ) is a German writer , film director , screenwriter and actor .
Henrik Pontoppidan ( 24 July 1857 -- 21 August 1943 ) was a Danish realist writer who shared with Karl Gjellerup the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1917 for `` his authentic descriptions of present - day life in Denmark . ''
Thomas Knowles ( 30 May 1824 -- 3 December 1883 ) was an English businessman and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1883 .
Wilhelm Ringelband ( 1921 - -1981 ) was a German theater critic and endower of the Gertrud - Eysoldt - Ring .
Jaime de Piniés ( 18 November 1917 -- 29 December 2003 ) was a Spanish diplomat who served for one year as the President of the United Nations General Assembly .
Abu Bakr Muhammad ibn al - Hasan ibn Duraid al - Azdi , often known simply as Ibn Duraid ( Arabic : ابن دريد الأزدي‎ ; 837 -- 933 CE ) , was a famous Arab poet , lexicographer and philologist during the Abbasid era .

Meera Vasudevan ( born 29 January 1982 ) is an Indian film actress and model , who has appeared in Malayalam , Tamil , Hindi and Telugu - language films .
Gorka Otxoa ( 13 January 1979 , in Irún , Gipuzkoa , Spain ) is a Spanish comedian and actor .

Bruno Pontecorvo ( Russian : Бру́но Макси́мович Понтеко́рво , Bruno Maksimovich Pontekorvo ; 22 August 1913 -- 24 September 1993 ) was an Italian nuclear physicist , an early assistant of Enrico Fermi and then the author of numerous studies in high energy physics , especially on neutrinos .

Michael Fokine ( a French transliteration Michel Fokine ; English transliteration Mikhail Fokin ; Russian : Михаи́л Миха́йлович Фо́кин , Mikhaíl Mikháylovich Fokín ) ( 23 April ( O.S. 11 April ) 1880 -- 22 August 1942 ) was a groundbreaking Russian choreographer and dancer .

Heinrich Schütz ( German : ( ʃʏʦ ) ; 18 October ( O.S. 8 October ) 1585 -- 6 November 1672 ) was a German composer and organist , generally regarded as the most important German composer before Johann Sebastian Bach and often considered to be one of the most important composers of the 17th century .
Miklós Borsos ( 13 August 13 1906 -- 27 January 1990 ) was a Hungarian sculptor and medallist .
Karl Friedrich Schimper ( 15 February 1803 -- 21 December 1867 ) was a German botanist , naturalist and poet .
Élie Halévy ( 6 September 1870 -- 21 August 1937 ) was a French philosopher and historian who wrote studies of the British utilitarians , the book of essays , Era of Tyrannies , and a history of Britain from 1815 to 1914 that influenced British historiography .
Charles Frédéric Kuhlmann ( 22 May 1803 -- 27 January 1881 ) was a French chemist who patented the reaction for converting ammonia to nitric acid , which was later used in the Ostwald process .
José Ramón Bauzà Díaz ( born November 16 , 1970 ) is a Spanish politician and the president of the Autonomous Community of the Balearic Islands from 2011 to 2015 .
Irmgard Keun ( February 6 , 1905 -- May 5 , 1982 ) was a German author noteworthy for her portrayals of life in both the Weimar Republic and the early years of the Nazi Germany era .
Heinrich Barth ( 16 February 1821 -- 25 November 1865 ) was a German explorer of Africa and scholar .
Karl Spruner von Merz ( 15 November 1803 -- 24 August 1892 ) , or Karl von Spruner as he preferred to be known , was a German cartographer and scholar .
Juan de Valdés Leal ( 4 May 1622 -- 15 October 1690 ) was a Spanish painter and etcher of the Baroque era .
Philippe Bouchet ( born 1953 ) is a French biologist whose primary scientific fields of study are malacology and taxonomy .
Luis de Olona y Gaeta ( Málaga , 1823 -- Barcelona , 1863 ) was a playwright , theater impresario and librettist of a number of Spanish zarzuelas by the mid of 19th - century Spain .
Theo Brandmüller ( 2 February 1948 in Mainz -- 26 November 2012 in Saarbrücken ) was a German contemporary classical composer , organist and teacher .
Wiesław Myśliwski ( born 25 March 1932 in Dwikozy , near Sandomierz ) is a Polish novelist .
Marius Müller - Westernhagen ( 6 December 1948 in Düsseldorf , North Rhine - Westphalia ) is a German actor and musician .
Pascalis Romanus ( or Paschal the Roman ) was a 12th - century priest , medical expert , and dream theorist , noted especially for his Latin translations of Greek texts on theology , oneirocritics , and related subjects .
Peter Lebrecht Schmidt ( born Dessau , 28 July 1933 ) is a German classical scholar .
General Wacław Jędrzejewicz ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈvat͡swaf jɛndʐɛˈjɛvʲit͡ʂ ) ; 29 January 1893 -- 30 November 1993 ) was a Polish Army officer , diplomat , politician and historian , and subsequently an American college professor .
Giacomo Luigi Ciamician ( 27 August 1857 -- 2 January 1922 ) was an Italian photochemist and senator of Armenian descent .
Wilhelm Kobelt ( February 20 , 1840 -- March 26 , 1916 ) was a German zoologist born in Alsfeld , Grand Duchy of Hesse .
Liu Bannong ( 1891 - -1934 ) or Liu Fu ( 劉復/刘复 ) was a Chinese linguist and poet .
Richard Chiswell ( 1673 -- 14 May 1751 ) was a wealthy English merchant and politician .

Francis Osborne ( 26 September 1593 -- 4 February 1659 ) was an English essayist , known for his Advice to a Son , which became a very popular book soon after the English Restoration .
Anatoly Borisovich Kuznetsov ( Russian : Анатолий Борисович Кузнецов ; December 31 , 1930 -- March 7 , 2014 ) was a Soviet and Russian actor , probably best known for his role as a Red Army soldier Fyodor Sukhov in White Sun of the Desert ( 1970 ) .
Gustav Pfizer ( 1807 - 1890 ) was a German poet and critic of the Swabian school .
Paul Pétau ( Paulus Petavius in Latin ) ( 1568 - 1614 ) was a French publisher and book collector .
Antoni Malczewski ( 3 June 1793 -- 2 May 1826 ) was an influential Polish romantic poet , known for his only work , `` a narrative poem of dire pessimism '' , Maria ( 1825 ) .
Luca Desiato ( born November 13 , 1941 in Rome ) is an Italian journalist and writer .
José María Asensio ( 1829 - -1905 ) was a Spanish historian , journalist , biographer and writer .
André Lallemand ( September 29 , 1904 -- March 24 , 1978 ) was a French astronomer and director of the Institut d'Astrophysique de Paris .
John Pell ( 1 March 1611 -- 12 December 1685 ) was an English mathematician .
Publilius Optatianus Porfirius was a Latin poet , possibly a native of Africa .
John Eric Bartholomew , OBE ( 14 May 1926 -- 28 May 1984 ) , known by his stage name Eric Morecambe , was an English comedian who together with Ernie Wise formed the award - winning double act Morecambe and Wise .
Joseph Charles Hippolyte Crosse ( 1 October 1826 in Paris - 7 August 1898 ) was a French conchologist .

Jean - François Mattéi ( French : ( ma.te.i ) ; 9 March 1941 -- 24 March 2014 ) was a French philosopher and professor of Greek philosophy and political philosophy at the University of Nice .
Vinaya Prasad ( also credited as Vinaya Prakash ) is a popular film and television actress in South India who has primarily featured in Kannada and Malayalam films besides acting in a few Tamil and Telugu language films .
Anna Kohler ( alternative spelling : Anna Köhler or Anna Koehler ) is a German - American theater actress , director and translator .
Paul Kuentz ( Born 4 May 1930 - Mulhouse , France ) is a French conductor who studied at the Paris Conservatoire from 1947 to 1950 , with Noël Gallon , Georges Hugon and Eugene Bigot .
Christian Friedrich Schönbein ( 18 October 1799 -- 29 August 1868 ) was a German - Swiss chemist who is best known for inventing the fuel cell ( 1838 ) at the same time as William Robert Grove and his discoveries of guncotton and ozone .
Dumitru Berciu ( 27 January 1907 , Bobaiţa , Mehedinţi -- 1 July 1998 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian historian and archaeologist , honorary member of the Romanian Academy .

Massimo Girotti ( 18 May 1918 -- 5 January 2003 ) was an Italian film actor whose career spanned seven decades .

Nadia Hilou ( Arabic : ناديا حلو‎ , Hebrew : נאדיה חילו‎‎ ; 5 July 1953 -- 27 February 2015 ) was an Israeli Arab social worker and politician , who served as a member of the Knesset for the Labor Party between 2006 and 2009 .

Frédéric Monod ( 1794 - 1863 ) was a French Protestant pastor .
Ludovico di Varthema , also known as Barthema and Vertomannus ( c. 1470 -- 1517 ) , was an Italian traveller , diarist and aristocrat known for being the first non - Muslim European to enter Mecca as a pilgrim .

The Yamaha Zuma 125 is a scooter introduced by Yamaha Motor Company in September 2008 .
LMS diesel shunter 7057 was built by Harland & Wolff .
The Giffard dirigible or Giffard airship was an airship built in France in 1852 by Henri Giffard , the first powered and steerable ( French : dirigeable - `` directable '' ) airship to fly .
The Saiga semi - automatic rifles are a family of Russian semi - automatic rifles manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern ( formerly Izhmash ) , which also manufactures the original AK-47 and its variants , Saiga-12 shotguns and Dragunov sniper rifle .
The Mercedes - Benz T2 was a transporter manufactured by Daimler - Benz .
The Caterpillar 345C L is a large hydraulic excavator manufactured by Caterpillar Inc. The 345C L , with 345 hp ( 257 kW ) of net flywheel power , is classified as a large excavator by Caterpillar .
The Volkswagen Transporter , based on the Volkswagen Group 's T platform , now in its sixth generation , refers to a series of vans produced over 60 years and marketed worldwide .

The TRS-80 MC-10 microcomputer is a lesser - known member of the TRS-80 line of home computers , produced by Tandy Corporation in the early 1980s and sold through their RadioShack chain of electronics stores .
Echo Ranger is a marine autonomous underwater vehicle ( AUV ) built by Boeing .
The Hudson Commodore is an automobile which was produced by the Hudson Motor Car Company of Detroit , Michigan between 1941 and 1952 .
The British Rail Class 60 is a class of Co - Co heavy freight diesel - electric locomotives built by Brush Traction .
The Tatra K5AR was an articulated tramcar built by ČKD Tatra .

The Christina River is a tributary of the Delaware River , approximately 35 miles ( 56 km ) long , in northern Delaware in the United States , also flowing through small areas of southeastern Pennsylvania and northeastern Maryland .
Krui River rises on the southern slopes of the Great Dividing Range , below Oxleys Peak , at Mount Palmer and flows generally southwest , joined by six minor tributaries before reaching its confluence with the Goulburn River near Comiala Flat .
The Macmillan River is a tributary , approximately 320 kilometres ( 200 mi ) long , of the Pelly River in the Yukon Territory of northwestern Canada .
The Weesener Bach , also called the Lutterbach , is a tributary of the river Örtze in northern Germany .
The Koyna River is a tributary of the Krishna River which originates in Mahableshwar , Satara district , western Maharashtra , India .
The Brăteni River is a tributary of the Lechinţa River in Romania .
The Impey River is a river in the Mid West of Western Australia which rises south of Mount Murchison and flows east - north - east until it merges with the Murchison River of which it is a tributary .
The Dürre Ager River flows through the Attergau area in Upper Austria from South to North and joins the Vöckla River at Timelkam .
Montour Run is a tributary of Fishing Creek in Columbia County , Pennsylvania .
The Inambari River in southeastern Peru flows 210 miles ( 340 km ) from the Cordillera Apolobamba in the Andes to the Madre de Dios River .
The Econlockhatchee River ( Econ River for short ) is a 87.7-kilometre - long ( 54.5 mi ) north - flowing blackwater tributary of the St. Johns River , the longest river in the U.S. state of Florida .
The Kasai River ( called Cassai in Angola ) is a tributary of the Congo River , located in central Africa .

Salmon Falls Creek is a tributary of the Snake River , flowing from northern Nevada into Idaho in the United States .
The Feather River is the principal tributary of the Sacramento River , in the Sacramento Valley of Northern California .
The Walhonding River is a principal tributary of the Muskingum River , 23.5 miles ( 37.8 km ) long , in east - central Ohio in the United States .

Formed by the confluence of the Coolagolite Creek and Nutleys Creek , near Bermagui South , the Bermagui River flows generally east , before reaching its mouth into the Tasman Sea of the South Pacific Ocean near Bermagui .
The Ubangi River ( /juːˈbæŋɡi/ or /uːˈbæŋɡi/ ) , also spelled Oubangui , is the largest right - bank tributary of the Congo River in the region of Central Africa .
The Tashkurgan River runs through Tashkurgan Tajik Autonomous County and is one of the tributaries of the Yarkand River in the Tarim Basin .
The Sambre is a river in northern France and in Wallonia , Belgium , left tributary of the Meuse River .
The São Gonçalo Channel ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( sɐ̃w̃ ɡõˈsalu ) ) is a navigable channel connecting two large coastal lagoons , Lagoa Mirim and Lagoa dos Patos , in the state of Rio Grande do Sul in southern Brazil .
The Breakfast Creek ( Aboriginal : Barrambin ) is a small urban stream that is a tributary of the Brisbane River , located in suburban Brisbane in the South East region of Queensland , Australia .
The Ebola River , also commonly known by its indigenous name Legbala , is the headstream of the Mongala River , a tributary of the Congo River , in northern Democratic Republic of the Congo .
The Thuli River , former name Tuli River , is a major tributary of the Shashe River in Zimbabwe .
The Athabasca River travels 1,231 km ( 765 mi ) before draining into the Peace - Athabasca Delta near Lake Athabasca south of Fort Chipewyan .
The river rises below the King Leopold Ranges and flows in a westerly direction through the Lennard River Gorge and the Windjana Gorge before merging with the Meda River .
Mammy Johnsons River rises on the southwestern slopes of the Great Dividing Range , below Winns Mountain , north northwest of Bulahdelah , and flows generally north , west and south , joined by four tributaries including Wards River , before reaching its confluence with the Karuah River north northwest of Stroud .
Shickshinny Creek ( historically known as Shickohinna ) is a tributary of the Susquehanna River in the Wyoming Valley in Luzerne County , Pennsylvania , in the United States .
The Romaine River drains into the Jacques Cartier Strait , opposite the Mingan Archipelago , that is part of the Gulf of Saint Lawrence .
Picanoc River ( pikanak or pakânâk ) is tributary of Gatineau River , flowing in the administrative region of Outaouais region of Quebec , Canada .
The Mzingwane River , formerly known Umzingwane River as or Umzingwani River is a major left - bank tributary of the Limpopo River in Zimbabwe .
The Geumho River flows through North Gyeongsang Province , South Korea , and drains into the Nakdong River .
Hinksey Stream is a branch of the River Thames to the west of the city of Oxford , England .
The Brisbane River is the longest river in the south east region of Queensland , Australia , and flows through the city of Brisbane , before emptying into Moreton Bay .
The Erdre is a river in western France , right tributary to the Loire .
The Chambly Canal is a National Historic Site of Canada in the Province of Quebec , running along the Richelieu River past Saint - Jean - sur - Richelieu , Carignan , and Chambly .
The Andelle is a river of Normandy , France , 56.8 kilometres ( 35.3 mi ) in length , flowing through the departments of Seine - Maritime and Eure .
The Wa River ( Thai : ลำน้ำว้า ) is a river of the Thai highlands in Thailand , a tributary of the Nan River , part of the Chao Phraya River basin .
Nahal Poleg is a stream in the Sharon plain in Israel that empties into the Mediterranean Sea between Netanya and the Wingate Institute .
Hawthorne Canal and Iron Cove Creek are two significant tributaries that flow into Iron Cove , where it flows into Parramatta River , before connecting with Port Jackson .
Manuel Bravo Paredes ( February 17 , 1897 - November , 1973 ) was a Chilean footballer who participated in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Safer Sali ( Albanian : Safer Sali , Serbo - Croatian : Сафер Сали ) ( born 3 June 1946 , in Veles , SFR Yugoslavia ) is a former freestyle wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics for Yugoslavia .
Walter Dick ( September 20 , 1905 in Kirkintilloch , Scotland -- July 24 , 1989 in Lafayette , California ) was a U.S. soccer forward who was a member of the U.S. national team at the 1934 FIFA World Cup .
Hastings Bwalya ( born 25 August 1985 ) is a Zambian boxer who won the 2007 All - Africa Games at junior welter , and then competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Carlos Espejo is an Argentine swimmer who competed at the 1948 Summer Olympics in the 200 m breaststroke .
Kelly Gunther ( born August 14 , 1987 ) is an American speed skater participated in the 2014 Winter Olympics .
Nurzhan Karimzhanov ( born May 30 , 1980 ) is a Kazakhstani boxer , who won the gold medal at the 2002 Asian Games in the Junior Welterweight division .
Kelly Geraghty ( born 11 July 1977 ) is an Australian synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Jeronimas Milius was elected to represent his country in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008 on 2 February 2008 collecting 11 674 votes leaving Aistė Pilvelytė with Troy on Fire close behind whose backing vocalist he was in the national final for Eurovision Song Contest 2006 .
Antoine Valois - Fortier ( born 13 March 1990 ) is a Canadian judoka who won the bronze medal in the Men 's -81 kg category at the Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics , making him the first Canadian to win a medal in Olympic Judo in twelve years and the fifth to win one in Olympic history .
Mireia García Sánchez ( born July 31 , 1981 in Viladecans , Catalonia ) is a former butterfly swimmer from Spain , who competed for her native country at 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney , Australia .
Frederick Charles Delahaye , sometimes spelled Delahay or Delahey ( March 19 , 1905 -- March 17 , 1973 ) , was a Canadian ice hockey player who competed in the 1928 Winter Olympics .
Zlatan Arnautović ( born September 2 1956 in Prijedor , Bosnia and Herzegovina , then Yugoslavia ) is a former Yugoslav handball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics and in the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Malcolm Poole ( born 6 November 1949 ) is a retired field hockey player from Australia , who was a member of the team that won the silver medal at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Peter Pospíšil ( April 24 , 1944 in Bratislava -- April 17 , 2006 in Bratislava ) was a Czechoslovak / Slovak handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Tamás Molnár ( born August 2 , 1975 in Szeged ) is a Hungarian water polo player , who played on the gold medal squads at the 2000 Summer Olympics , 2004 Summer Olympics and 2008 Olympics .
L. H. Clermont was an Olympic sport shooter who was part of the team won Haiti 's first ever Olympic medal , a bronze in team free rifle at the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Mikael Olander ( born June 11 , 1963 ) is a retired decathlete from Sweden , who finished in 17th place ( 7869 points ) at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
Robert Foquet ( born May 6 , 1905 , date of death unknown ) was a French boxer who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics and in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Malcolm Lincoln , together with a group of backing vocalists called Manpower 4 , won the competition Eesti Laul 2010 with the song `` Siren '' and represented Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 .
Pier Paolo Lucchetta ( born January 14 , 1963 ) is an Italian former volleyball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics and in the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Akira Ōta ( born 8 April 1957 in Akita ) is a Japanese former wrestler who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics , in the 1988 Summer Olympics , and in the 1992 Summer Olympics .
Godfrey Kelly ( born 21 December 1928 ) is a Bahamian former sailor who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics , in the 1964 Summer Olympics , in the 1968 Summer Olympics , and in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Ana Galindo Santolaria ( born 16 August 1973 ) is a Spanish former alpine skier who competed in the 1998 Winter Olympics and in the 2002 Winter Olympics .
Mindaugas Mizgaitis ( born October 14 , 1979 in Kaunas , Lithuania ) is a Lithuanian amateur wrestler , who won a bronze medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Giuseppe Ghedina ( 1898 -- 1986 ) was an Italian cross country skier who competed in the 1924 Winter Olympics .
Carly Dixon ( born 27 July 1973 ) is an Australian former judoka who competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics , in the 2000 Summer Olympics , and in the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Katarína Lamrichová ( née Beňušková , born October 21 , 1956 in Partizánske ) is a former Czechoslovak / Slovak handball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Gunnar Hallkvist ( January 10 , 1919 -- February 1 , 2014 ) was a Swedish speed skater who competed at the 1952 Winter Olympics in Oslo .
Konstantinos Giataganas or Konstantinos Yataganas ( 12 October 1920 -- 1997 ) was a Greek shot putter and discus thrower who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics and in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Sven Paris ( born December 17 , 1980 ) is an Italian amateur boxer who competed in the light welterweight division at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Shohei Kasahara ( born 21 July 1939 ) is a Japanese former hammer thrower who competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Teneal Attard ( born 16 March 1985 ) is an Australian field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics and 2012 Summer Olympics .
Artsem Mikhalenka ( Belarusian : Арцём Міхаленка ; born 23 January 1990 ) , born in Byelorussian SSR , USSR is a singer who represented Belarus in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 in Oslo as part of the band 3 + 2 .
Emil Beyer ( November 22 , 1876 in New York City -- October 15 , 1934 in New York City ) was an American gymnast and track and field athlete who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics .

Hugo Herrnhof ( born September 21 , 1964 in Bormio ) is a retired Italian short track speed skater who competed in the 1988 Winter Olympics , 1992 Winter Olympics and 1994 Winter Olympics .

Victoriano Alberto Zorrilla ( April 6 , 1906 -- April 23 , 1986 ) was an Argentine swimmer who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics and 1928 Summer Olympics .
Zoltán Adamik ( 20 October 1928 -- 7 December 1992 ) was a Hungarian sprinter who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Robert Haigh ( born 27 March 1945 in Adelaide , South Australia ) is a retired hockey player from Australia , who won two Olympic silver medals as a member of the national team at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City and the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Walter Marti ( born April 1 , 1910 , date of death unknown ) is a Swiss boxer who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .

Mario Lertora ( September 21 , 1897 -- March 28 , 1939 ) was an Italian artistic gymnast who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics , in the 1928 Summer Olympics , and in the 1932 Summer Olympics .
Bim Diederich ( 20 February 1922 -- 6 December 2012 ) , also known as Jean Diederich , was a professional Luxembourgian road bicycle racer , with an impressive record in the Tour de France .

Rhys Howden ( born 2 April 1987 ) is an Australian water polo player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Yvonne Tousek - Renne ( born February 23 , 1980 in Kitchener , Ontario ) is a retired artistic gymnast who competed for her native Canada in the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta and the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney .
Michelle Guerette ( born October 6 , 1980 ) is an American rower who competed in the Women 's Quadruple Sculls event at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Renáta Hiráková ( born 27 May 1971 in Košice ) is a Slovak former basketball player who competed in the 1992 Summer Olympics and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Rambo Amadeus represented Montenegro in the Eurovision Song Contest 2012 in Baku , Azerbaijan , with the song `` Euro Neuro '' .
José Luis Munguía Linares ( 28 October 1959 -- 24 March 1985 ) was a football player from El Salvador who was a non - playing squad member at the 1982 FIFA World Cup Finals in Spain .
István Mudin ( October 16 , 1881 -- July 22 , 1918 ) was a Hungarian athlete who competed at the 1906 Intercalated Games and the 1908 Summer Olympics .
Nikolaos Siranidis ( Greek : Νικόλαος Σιρανίδης ; born 26 February 1976 ) is a Greek diver who competed in the synchronised 3 metre springboard competition at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Eliecer Montes de Oca is a one time Gold medalist for baseball , winning at the 1996 Summer Olympics .
Zoltán Blum , also known as Zoltán Virág ( 3 January 1892 -- 25 December 1959 ) was a Hungarian amateur football ( soccer ) player who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Juraj Amšel ( 17 December 1924 -- 7 August 1988 ) was a Croat water polo player who competed for Yugoslavia in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Reiner Gies ( born March 12 , 1963 in Kaiserslautern , Rhineland - Palatinate ) was a German boxer who won a Light Welterweight Bronze Medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics for West Germany .
Kayoko Sugiyama ( Japanese : 杉山 加代子 ; born October 31 , 1961 ) is a Japanese former volleyball player who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Andrew Murray Charlton ( 12 August 1907 -- 10 December 1975 ) , known popularly as Boy Charlton , was an Australian freestyle swimmer of the 1920s and 1930s who won a gold medal in the 1500 m freestyle at the 1924 Summer Olympics in Paris .
Anke Möhring ( born 28 August 1969 in Magdeburg , Saxony - Anhalt ) is a former freestyle swimmer from East Germany , who won the bronze medal in the 400 m freestyle at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
Hartmut Losch ( 11 September 1943 in Angermünde -- 26 March 1997 in Neu Fahrland ) was a German athlete who competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics , in the 1968 Summer Olympics , and in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Issaka Hassane ( born January 3 , 1959 ) is a track and field sprint athlete who competed internationally for Chad Hassane represented Chad at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles .
Oyuunbilegiin Pürevbaatar ( born 23 November 1973 ) is a Mongolian former wrestler who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics and in the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Tracey Mosley ( born 25 September 1973 in Sydney , Australia ) is a softball player from Australia , who won a silver medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics and a bronze medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Simon Agoston ( born 5 April 1977 ) is a Hungarian - born triathlete from Austria , who competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .
Lisa Angell ( born Virginie Vetrano , 21 September 1968 in Paris ) is a French singer who represented France in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015 with the song `` N'oubliez pas '' .
Aleksandrs Jackēvičs ( born March 25 , 1958 in Dobele ) is a Latvian judoka who competed for the Soviet Union in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Emil Seidler ( March 13 , 1914 - date of death unknown ) was an Austrian ice hockey player who competed for the Austrian national team at the 1936 Winter Olympics in Garmisch - Partenkirchen .
Günter Haritz ( born 16 October 1948 ) is a retired road and track cyclist from West Germany , who won the gold medal in the Men 's 4.000 Team Pursuit at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich , alongside Günther Schumacher , Jürgen Colombo , and Udo Hempel .
Alexandros Vrasivanopoulos ( Greek : Αλέξανδρος Βρασιβανόπουλος , born 1890 , date of death unknown ) was a Greek sport shooter who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Johannes Gandil ( 21 May 1873 in Ringe -- 7 March 1956 in Ordrup ) was a Danish amateur footballer , who played one game as a forward for the Denmark national football team , winning a silver medal at the 1908 Summer Olympics .
Éric Koloko ( born November 1 1950 in Lille ) is a French dancer and choreographer , who was formerly a gymnast who competed at the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Abraham van Olst ( 24 September 1897 , Amsterdam -- 9 April 1964 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch water polo player who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Regina Rajchrtová ( born 5 February 1968 ) is a Czech former tennis player who competed for her native country at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul .
Marcelino Vargas ( born 1921 - date of death unknown ) is a Paraguayan football goalkeeper who played for Paraguay in the 1950 FIFA World Cup .
Lawrence Lemieux ( born November 12 , 1955 in Edmonton , Alberta ) is a Canadian sailor , who competed at the 1984 Summer Olympics in the Star Class and at the 1988 Summer Olympics in the Finn class .
Juan Carlos Bianchi ( born January 22 , 1970 in Maracay ) is a former tennis player from Venezuela , who represented his native country at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , Georgia and played collegiate tennis at the University of Alabama for the Alabama Crimson Tide .
Rolf Herings ( born 10 July 1940 ) is a German former javelin thrower who competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics and in the 1968 Summer Olympics .
Jan Schur ( born 27 November 1962 in Leipzig ) is a retired track cyclist and road cyclist from East Germany , who represented his native country at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
Herb Barten ( born January 13 , 1928 ) is an American former middle distance runner who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Hans Johnny Höglin ( born 26 February 1943 ) is a Swedish speed skater whose greatest moment was to win a gold medal in the 10000-meter event at the 1968 Winter Olympics in Grenoble , France .
Sergey Naumov ( Russian : Серге́й Нау́мов ; born 9 April 1962 ) is a Russian former water polo player who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics and in the 1992 Summer Olympics .
Curt Rottman ( 13 February 1886 , in Dresden -- 13 January 1928 , in New York City ) was an American gymnast who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Amanda Overland ( born on August 30 , 1981 in Kitchener , Ontario ) is a Canadian short track speed skater who competed in the 2006 Winter Olympics .
Jamie Lynn Corkish ( formerly Gray , née Beyerle , born May 26 , 1984 ) is an American sport shooter who won a gold medal at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Abdul Khalik Juad , also known as Abdul Kalik Mohamed Jawad , ( born November 1930 ) was a weight - lifter who represented Iraq at the 1964 Summer Olympics in Tokyo
Petra Niemann ( born 14 August 1978 ) is a German former yacht racer who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics , in the 2004 Summer Olympics , and in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Mario Chiarini ( born 7 January 1981 ) is an Italian baseball player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics .

The Indian Journal of Dental Research is a peer - reviewed open - access medical journal published by Medknow Publications on behalf of the Indian Society of Dental Research .
Child Christopher and Goldilind the Fair is a fantasy novel by William Morris , perhaps the first modern fantasy writer to unite an imaginary world with the element of the supernatural , and thus the precursor of much of present - day fantasy literature .

When Hodder & Stoughton republished The Happy Highwayman in 1963 , however , some updates were done to parts of the texts .

Tripterocalyx is a small genus of flowering plants in the four o'clock family .
Dysganus is the name given to a dubious genus of dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Austropyrgus dyerianus is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the Hydrobiidae family .
Seychelles giant day gecko ( Phelsuma sundbergi sundbergi Rendahl , 1939 ) is diurnal subspecies of geckos .
Eriogonum libertini is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Dubakella Mountain buckwheat .
Maotherium is a genus extinct symmetrodont mammal that was discovered in Early Cretaceous rocks in Liaoning Province , China , in 2003 .
Bembidion adygorum is a species of ground beetle from the Trechinae subfamily that can be found in Armenia , Georgia and Caucasus .
Pseudotriton is a genus of salamanders in the family Plethodontidae .
The underworld windowskate ( Fenestraja plutonia ) is a species of cartilaginous fish in the family Rajidae .
Jiutaisaurus is a genus of dinosaur from the Quantou Formation of China .
Copidosoma floridanum is a species of wasp in the family Encyrtidae and is primarily a parasitoid of moths in the subfamily Plusiinae .
Helogenes gouldingi is a species of whale catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in black - water tributaries of the Madeira River basin .
Aliatypus is a spider genus in the family Antrodiaetidae with species found in the United States .
Stictoleptura tripartita is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Iran , Syria and Turkey .
Stenophryneta variegata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Stenophryneta .
Eriogonum deserticola is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Colorado Desert buckwheat .
Monopis weaverella is a species of moth in the Tineidae family .
Nannoarctia takanoi ( Sonan , 1934 ) is an endemic species of moth in the family Arctiidae from Taiwan .
Cryptoparachtes fedotovi is a spider species found in Georgia and Azerbaijan .
Buceros is a genus of large Asian hornbills ( family Bucerotidae ) .
Platysaurus torquatus , the striped flat lizard or collared flat lizard , is a species of lizard in the Cordylidae family found in southeast Africa .
Erigeron rybius is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Sacramento Mountain fleabane and royal fleabane .
Taeniocrada is a genus of extinct plants of Devonian age ( 420 to 360 million years ago ) .
The Galliformes are an order of heavy - bodied ground - feeding birds that includes turkey , grouse , chicken , New World quail and Old World quail , ptarmigan , partridge , pheasant , junglefowl and the Cracidae .
Horkelia californica ( syn : Potentilla californica ) , known by the common name California horkelia , is a species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Prunus sargentii , commonly known as Sargent 's cherry or North Japanese hill cherry , is a species of cherry native to Japan , Korea , and Sakhalin ( Russia ) .
Bambusa chungii , commonly known as white bamboo or tropical blue bamboo , is a large , tall bamboo species , often found in Hong Kong , and originating in southern China and Vietnam .
Helminthoglypta nickliniana , common name `` Nicklin 's Peninsula snail '' or `` Coast Range shoulderband '' is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
Cirripectes is a large genus of combtooth blennies found throughout the Pacific and Indian oceans .
Glossodoris rufomarginata , commonly called white - margin sea slug or caramel nudibranch , is a species of colorful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Medinilla waterhousei , commonly known as Tagimaucia or Tagimoucia ( tahng - ee - mow - theea ) , is a species of flowering plant in the family Melastomataceae which is endemic to highland rainforest of the Fijian island of Taveuni .
Pythium debaryanum is a species of water mould in the family Pythiaceae .
Lottia luchuana is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lottiidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Bromelia serra is a species of plant in the Bromeliaceae family native to South America ( Brazil , French Guiana , Bolivia , Paraguay , Argentina ) .
Mochokus niloticus is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Nile and Niger River basins .
Campanula elegans is a plant species in the genus Campanula .
Eutriconodonta is an order of early mammals .
Pseudobiceros gloriosus ( common name : the glorious flatworm ) is a benthic marine flatworm species that belongs to the Pseudocerotidae family .
Lyclene reticulata is a species of lichen moths of the Erebidae family , Arctiinae subfamily .
Lepidopilum grevilleanum is a species of moss in the Daltoniaceae family .
Heuchera elegans is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name urn - flowered alumroot .
Brachyspira aalborgi is a species of bacteria , one of the causative agents of intestinal spirochetosis .
Claytonia rubra is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common name redstem springbeauty .
Beccariophoenix alfredii , also known as the High Plateau Coconut Palm , is a recently discovered species of Arecaceae ( palms ) , endemic to Madagascar .
Euprymna scolopes , also known as the Hawaiian bobtail squid , is a species of bobtail squid in the family Sepiolidae native to the central Pacific Ocean , where it occurs in shallow coastal waters off the Hawaiian Islands and Midway Island .
Banksia caleyi , commonly known as the red lantern banksia or Caley 's banksia , is a species of woody shrub of the family Proteaceae native to Western Australia .
The order Squamata , or the scaled reptiles , are the largest recent order of reptiles , comprising all lizards and snakes .
Procolophonidae is an extinct family of parareptiles from the Permian and Triassic periods .
Neptunea contraria is a left - handed species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Herina rivosecchii is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in Croatia , France , Greece , Italy , Switzerland , and Spain .
Dicromantispa electromexicana is an extinct species of mantidfly in the neuropteran family Mantispidae known from a fossil found in North America .
Coptodon is a genus of cichlids native to Africa with C. zillii also found in the Middle East .
Donax gouldii , common name the bean clam , is a species of small saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Donacidae .
Bistolida stolida , common name the stolid cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Cirripectes alleni , the Kimberley blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern Indian Ocean , around Australia .
Stygobromus is a genus of amphipod crustaceans that live in subterranean habitats .
Macradenia lutescens is a species of epiphytic orchid known by the common name longgland orchid .
Euomphalidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic marine molluscs which may be gastropods with anisostrophically coiled shells ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Ophioscincus truncatus is a species of burrowing short - limbed snake - skink that is endemic to the coastal areas and islands of New South Wales and Queensland , in Australia .
Festuca abyssinica is a species of grass which is endemic to Africa .
Lulworthia is a genus of fungi within the Lulworthiaceae family .
Rhodanthemum hosmariense ( Moroccan daisy ) is a species of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae , native to the Atlas Mountains of Morocco .
Cirsium ciliolatum is a species of thistle known by the common name Ashland thistle .
Hypsoblennius maculipinna is a species of combtooth blenny found in Ecuador .
Retortamonas is a genus of flagellate protozoa that live in the intestines of various animals .
Amphizoa lecontei is a species of aquatic beetle .
Leporacanthicus triactis is a species of armored catfish native to Colombia and Venezuela where it is found in the upper Orinoco River basin .
Aeschynomene rudis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name zigzag jointvetch .
Aldanites is an extinct cephalopod genus belonging to the ammonoid order Goniatitida .
The Altai snowcock ( Tetraogallus altaicus ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Pleurodonte nigrescens is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurodontidae .
It contains only one known species , Pillansia templemannii , endemic to Cape Province in South Africa .
Lobobunaea phaedusa is a species of very large moths in the family Saturniidae .
Lepanthes scopula is a species of orchid found from Mexico ( Oaxaca and Chiapas ) to Central America .
Argonauta oweri is an extinct species of argonautid octopus .
Scuticaria hadwenii is a species of orchid occurring from Guyana to Brazil .
At one time , the West African catshark was considered to be a subspecies of the nursehound , Scyliorhinus stellaris , but is now considered to be a separate species .
Conoplea is a genus of fungi first described by Christian Hendrik Persoon in 1801 .
Phylica polifolia ( also called Rosemary or Saint Helena Rosemary ) is a species of plant in the Rhamnaceae family .
Alienus curiosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Alienus .
Leptochilichthys is a genus of marine smelts containing four species .
Asiaceratops ( meaning `` Asian horned face '' ) is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur .
Poromitra crassiceps , commonly called the crested bigscale ( also called large - headed midnight fish , crested melamphid , or one - horned melamphaid ) is a species of deep sea fish in the ridgehead family .
Eurycorypha is a genus of insect in family Tettigoniidae , commonly known as Bush crickets .
Stipa tirsa is a species of perennial grass native to Europe and temperate Asia .
Becklespinax is a genus of large predatory theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of England .
Coccotrema is a genus of lichens in the Pertusariales order .
Eubalichthys is a genus of filefishes found in the eastern Indian Ocean waters around Australia .
Anomiopus lacordairei is a species of true dung beetle that is endemic to French Guiana , and is only known from Cayenne .
Lundellianthus is a genus of Mesoamerican flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Elaeagnus angustifolia , commonly called Russian olive , silver berry , oleaster , Persian olive , or wild olive , or commonly referred to as Senjid or Sinjid in Afghanistan and Senjed in Iran , is a species of Elaeagnus , native to western and central Asia , Afghanistan , from southern Russia and Kazakhstan to Turkey and Iran .
Pectinaria australis is one of at least ten species of polychaete worms of the family Pectinariidae .
Astragalus platytropis is a species of milkvetch known by the common name broadkeel milkvetch .
Polypedates pseudocruciger ( common names : false hour - glass tree frog or yellow tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to the southern Western Ghats , India .
Cleotrivia antillarum is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Triviidae , the false cowries or Cleotrivias .
Ghilianella beckeri is a species of assassin bug in the subfamily Emesinae found in Brazil .
Crepis biennis is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family with the common name Rough hawksbeard .
Chaetopoa is a genus of African plants in the grass family , found only in Tanzania .
Eleutherozoa is a subphylum of echinoderms .
Polystichum dudleyi is a species of fern known by the common name Dudley 's sword fern .
The Meekoceratidae is a family of ceratitid ammonites described in the Treatise,(Arkell et al . 1957 ) as being more or less involute , compressed , discoidal , smooth to weakly ornamented ; venter arched or tabulate ; sutures ceratitic with broad saddles .
Eulophota floridella is a species of snout moth in the genus Eulophota .
Cretoperipatus burmiticus is an extinct species of velvet worm that is known from Cretaceous amber approximately 100 million years old .
Sannantha virgata is a flowering shrub species in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Labeo pietschmanni is one of 103 species of fish in the genus Labeo .
The Bonthain rat ( Rattus bontanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Ectatina irrorata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ectatina .
Nerita textilis , common name the textile nerite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae .
Corticium penicillatum is a species of fungus in the class Agaricomycetes .
Neolissochilus is a genus of cyprinid fishes that occur in Asia that are often grouped with the mahseers .
Canbya aurea , common name Yellow pygmy - poppy , is a plant species endemic to the relatively cool northern deserts of the western United States .
Carlquistia is a rare North American genus of flowering plants in the aster family containing the single species Carlquistia muirii .
Amanita flavoconia , commonly known as yellow patches , yellow wart , orange Amanita , or yellow - dust Amanita , is a species of mushroom in the family Amanitaceae .
Protohippus is an extinct three - toed genus of horse .
Callionymus formosanus is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific Ocean from the South China Sea as well as around southern Japan and the Chesterfield Islands .
In 1986 Australian botanical taxonomist Donald McGillivray promoted the variety to species status , giving it the name Grevillea curviloba .
Plantago cordata is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name heartleaf plantain .
Pliosaurus ( meaning ' more lizard ' ) is an extinct genus of thalassophonean pliosaurid known from the Kimmeridgian and Tithonian stages ( Late Jurassic ) of Europe and South America .
Rhododendron mucronatum is a rhododendron species native to China , where it grows at altitudes of 2800 - -4500 meters .
Helianthus californicus is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name California sunflower .
Gossypium herbaceum , commonly known as Levant cotton , is a species of cotton native to the semi - arid regions of sub - Saharan Africa and Arabia where it still grows in the wild as a perennial shrub .
Drosera bicolor is an erect perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Carabus hummeli nevelskii is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Sakhalin , Russia .
Gobio hettitorum or the Taurus gudgeon ( also cited as dere kayasi ) is a species of gudgeon , a small freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Campanula gelida ( Czech : zvonek jesenický , pronounced ( ˈzvonɛk ˈjɛsɛɲɪtskiː ) ) is a stenoendemic , critically endangered species of perennial bellflower growing in the mountains of Hrubý Jeseník in the Czech Republic .
Brachinus is a genus of ground beetle native to the Nearctic , Palearctic , the Near East and North Africa .
Shantungosuchus is an extinct genus of Cretaceous crocodyliform found in China .
Odostomia occultidens , common name the hidden - toothed pyramid - shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Trueperella pyogenes is a species of nonmotile facultatively anaerobic Gram - positive bacteria .
Adiantum vivesii is a rare species of ferns known by the common name Puerto Rico maidenhair .
Stolephorus is a genus of fish in the Engraulidae family .
Neoregelia nivea is a plant species in the genus Neoregelia native to Brazil .
Rhus rooseae is an extinct species of flowering plant in the sumac family , Anacardiaceae , solely known from the middle Eocene sediments exposed in north central Oregon .
The Hill Mango , ( Commiphora caudata ) , also known as the Green Commiphora , is the most abundant Asian species of Commiphora of flowering plants in the frankincense and myrrh family , Burseraceae .
Parematheudes polystictella is a species of snout moth in the genus Parematheudes .
Ocotea quixos is a species of evergreen tree in the Lauraceae family , native to Ecuador and Colombia .
Carex paniculata , also called greater tussock - sedge , is a species of flowering plant in the Cyperaceae family which is 1.5 metres ( 4 ft 11 in ) high and can be found in most of Europe ( including Britain ) , Northwest Asia and North America .
Actinobacteria is a phylum of Gram - positive bacteria with high guanine and cytosine content in their DNA .
The Cimicomorpha are an infraorder of insects containing bugs .
Sepia mira is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean , specifically from the mouth of Clarence River , New South Wales ( 29 ° 19′S 153 ° 29′E ) to off Wooli ( 29 ° 49′S 153 ° 27′E ) in Australia .
Vaejovidae is a family of scorpions , comprising 17 genera , all found in Mexico and the southwestern United States :
Eleutherodactylus glanduliferoides is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Massif de la Selle , Haiti .
The Xenodiscaceae is a superfamily within the ammonoid order Ceratitida .
Chrysophyllum viridifolium , commonly known fluted milkwood , is a potentially large ( up to 20 m tall ) species of evergreen milkwood tree that occurs in East African coastal forests and in some inland forests of the tropics and subtropics .
The genus Chilonatalus of funnel - eared bats is found in South America and the Antilles .
Acanthoscelis ruficornis , Beach ground beetle is a species of ground beetle in the Scaritinae subfamily , the only species in the genus Acanthoscelis .
