Roboastra tigris is a species of sea slug , a polycerid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
Allotoma is a genus of moths in the superfamily Bombycoidea .
Coralliozetus is a genus of chaenopsid blennies mostly found in the eastern Pacific Ocean with one species ( C. cardonae ) occurring in the western Atlantic Ocean .
Quercus bicolor , the swamp white oak , is a North American species of medium - sized trees in the beech family .
Carabus hummeli middendorfi is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Russia , where it can only be found on Bolshoy Shantar Island in Primorsky Krai .
Acer circinatum ( vine maple ) is a species of maple native to western North America , from southwest British Columbia to northern California , usually within 300 kilometres ( 190 mi ) of the Pacific Ocean coast , found along the Columbia Gorge and Coastal Forest .
Chilomycterus antillarum or the Web Burrfish , Spiny Box Puffer , Bridled Burrfish or Striped Burr Fish , is a species of fish in the genus Chilomycterus native to the Western Atlantic Ocean , southern Florida , and the Bahamas to Brazil .
Penicillium jamesonlandense is a psychrotolerant species of the genus of Penicillium .
Baltocteniza is an extinct monotypic genus of trapdoor spider in the Ctenizidae subfamily Ctenizinae and at present , it contains the single species Baltocteniza kulickae .
Manefishes are perciform fishes in the family Caristiidae , which today includes 19 extant species distributed in four genera .

Anxylotoles caudatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Anxylotoles .
Latia is a genus of very small , air - breathing freshwater snails or limpets , aquatic pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Chilinoidea .

Arnoldius is a genus of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Hieracium scabrum , rough hawkweed , is a North American plant species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .

Speleogobius trigloides , also known as the Grotto goby , is a species of goby native to the Mediterranean Sea where it is known to inhabit grottoes at depths of from 8 to 25 metres ( 26 to 82 ft ) .

Molluginaceae are a family of flowering plants recognized by several taxonomists .
Bobtail squid ( order Sepiolida ) are a group of cephalopods closely related to cuttlefish .
Hydroginella wareni is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Calyptronoma plumeriana is a pinnately compound leaved palm species which is found in Cuba , Haiti and the Dominican Republic .
Papilio birchallii is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Colombia , Panama and Costa Rica .
The type species , Faxinalipterus minima was named and described in 2010 by José Fernando Bonaparte , Marina Bento Soares and César Leandro Schultz .
Callionymus russelli is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific waters off of Papua New Guinea .
Dimorphotheca cuneata , commonly known as the rain flower or white bietou , is a plant species native to South Africa ( Fynbos , Succulent Karoo , Nama Karoo , etc . ) .
Acidomonas methanolica is the only known species from the genus Acetobacter .
Togninia is a fungus genus and the type genus in the family Togniniaceae .
Penicillium grevilleicola is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from Grevillea ilicifolia .
Zosteraeschna minuscula , the friendly hawker is a species of dragonfly in family Aeshnidae .

Penicillium montanense is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces tannase .
Ecdeiocolea monostachya is a species of grass - like plant from Western Australia .

Haworthia minima is a species of Haworthia succulent plant , from the far south of the Western Cape , South Africa .
Dorycera longiceps is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Dorycera of the family Tephritidae .
Oenogenes congrualis is a species of snout moth in the genus Oenogenes .

Xenocretosuchus is a genus of probable tritylodont therapsids from the Aptian ( Early Cretaceous ) of Siberia , in the Russian Federation .
Calamintha is a genus of plants that belongs to the family Lamiaceae .
There is only one known species , Zyzyxia lundellii .
Squalius squalus , commonly known as the Italian chub , is a species of freshwater fish in the carp family Cyprinidae .
Malacoctenus zonogaster , the Belted blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from Baja California to Peru including the Galapagos Islands .
Rickettsia heilongjiangensis is a species of gram negative Alphaproteobacteria , within the spotted fever group , being carried by ticks .
Nymphon gracile is a species of sea spider first described by William Elford Leach in 1863 .
Parentucellia is a small genus of flowering plants in the broomrape family containing about four species .
Metridium senile , common name the plumose anemone or frilled anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Metridiidae .
Scapania sphaerifera is a species of plant in the Scapaniaceae family .
Crassula helmsii , known as swamp stonecrop or New Zealand pigmyweed , is an aquatic or semiterrestrial species of succulent plant in the family Crassulaceae .
Menegazzia testacea is a species of lichen found in New Zealand and Australia .
Eburiola geminata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Eburiola .
Scapanus is a genus of moles in the family Talpidae .
Sticharium dorsale , the Sand crawler , is a species of clinid endemic to the coast of southern Australia .
Neorossia leptodons is a species of bobtail squid native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean , from New South Wales ( 32 ° 08′S 153 ° 07′E ) to South Australia ( 33 ° 58′S 131 ° 22′E ) .
Sphodromantis conspicua is a species of praying mantis found in Burkina Faso and Senegal .
Coursetia is a large genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae .
Hoeneodes sinensis is a species of snout moth in the genus Hoeneodes .
Coccographis nigrorubra is a species of beetles found in Laos and more generally in Southern Asia .
Bullia pura , common name the pure plough shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
The Cronartiaceae are a family of rust fungi in the order Uredinales .
Tecticornia bibenda is a species of plant of the Salicornioideae family from Western Australia .
Tillandsia ignesiae is a bromeliad species in the genus Tillandsia .
Homo naledi is an extinct species of hominin , which anthropologists first described in 2015 and have assigned to the genus Homo .
Whatcheeria is an extinct genus of early tetrapod from the Early Carboniferous of Iowa .
Gelidocalamus is a genus of small to medium - sized bamboos in the grass family , native primarily to the mountains of eastern China , although one species ( G. kunishii ) is native to Taiwan and to the Nansei - shoto ( Ryukyu Islands ) region in Japan .
Zodarion pseudoelegans is a spider species found in Spain , France and Ibiza .
Galium arenarium or sand bedstraw is a plant species of the genus Galium .
Acropora cerealis is a species of acroporid coral found throughout the Indian and Pacific oceans , from the Red Sea and the Gulf of Aden to the Hawaiian Islands and the Johnston Atoll .
Bifidobacterium breve is a bacterial species of the Bifidobacterium genus which has probiotic properties .
Caladenia plicata , commonly known as the crab -- lipped spider orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Jaltomata antillana ( Antilles false holly ) is a plant species native to Jamaica , the Dominican Republic , Haiti , Cuba and Puerto Rico .
Scapozygoceropsis albertisi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Scapozygoceropsis .
Nyctibatrachus deccanensis ( common names : Deccan night frog , Deccan wrinkled frog ) is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family endemic to the southern Western Ghats in Tamil Nadu and Kerala states , India .
The Drepanosiphinae are a subfamily of the family Aphididae ; while a few authors have suggested treating the group as a family , this has not been adopted in the most recent classifications .
Caridina is a genus of freshwater atyid shrimp .
Pecten jacobaeus , the Mediterranean scallop , is a species of scallop , an edible saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Aegoceropsis fervida is a species of moth from the genus Aegoceropsis .
Ericameria ophitidis is a North American species of flowering shrubs in the daisy family .
Demodioides transversevittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Demodioides .
Ureaplasma canigenitalium is a species of Ureaplasma , a genus of bacteria belonging to the family Mycoplasmataceae .
Symphoricarpos acutus , the sharpleaf snowberry , is a North American species of trailing shrubs in the honeysuckle family .
Cuora serrata , originally described as Cuora galbinifrons serrata by Iverson & Mccord ( 1992 ) and later considered a distinct species by Obst & Fritz ( 1997 ) are hybrids as shown by the genetic studies of Stuart & Parham ( 2004 ) .
Plagius is a genus of Mediterranean plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
Iresine diffusa ( Juba 's bush ) is a species of plant in the Amaranthaceae family .
The Sparidae are a family of fish in the order Perciformes , commonly called sea breams and porgies ( North America ) .
Altica is a large genus of flea beetles in the subfamily Galerucinae , with about 300 species , distributed nearly worldwide .
Ictidomys parvidens is a species of squirrel in the family Sciuridae .
Allium hyalinum is a Californian species of wild onion known by the common name glassy onion .
Scaphyglottis atwoodii is a species of epiphytic orchid from Costa Rica .
Solidago kralii , common name Kral 's godenrod , is a North American plant species first described as a new species in 2003 .
Anoectochilus setaceus , the Bristly Anoectochilus , is a species of orchid native to the island of Java and Sumatra in Indonesia .
Megalancosaurus is a genus of extinct reptile from the Late Triassic period of Northern Italy , and one of the best known drepanosaurids .
Porcellio festai is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that is endemic to Italy .
Meconema is a genus of insects in the Tettigoniidae family .
Goniomonas is a genus of single - celled eukaryotes , including both freshwater and marine species .
Crocidura kegoensis , also known as the Ke Go shrew or Ke Go white - toothed shrew , is a species of shrew in the subfamily Crocidura described in 2004 .
Ceratomantis saussurii is a species of praying mantis native to Myanmar , Thailand , and Borneo .
Palpimanidae is a family of spiders , known as palp - footed spiders .
The tupelo leafminer moth ( Antispila nysaefoliella ) is a species of moth of the Heliozelidae family .
Peltorhamphus is a genus of righteye flounders native to the southwest Pacific Ocean around New Zealand and Norfolk Island ( Australia ) .
Cardites antiquatus is a species of marine bivalve molluscs , in the family Carditidae .
Achnatherum pekinense ( Chinese : 京芒草 ) is a species of flowering plant in the Poaceae family which is endemic to China where it can be found on elevation of 300 - -3,600 metres ( 980 - -11,810 ft ) and was introduced to Japan and Korea as well .
Quercus lanata or woolly - leaved oak is a species of Quercus native to southern and southeastern Asia ( Himalayas , Assam , Bhutan , Nepal , Indochina ( Vietnam , Myanmar , northern Thailand ) , and southwestern China ( Guangxi , Tibet , Yunnan ) ) .
Madysaurus is one of the most primitive cynodonts and is placed in its own family , Madysauridae .

Alangium griffithi is a species of plant in the Alangiaceae family .
Lomatium utriculatum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name common lomatium or spring gold .
Dolioletta gegenbauri is a species of tunicate in the family Doliolidae .
Conus diadema , common name the diadem cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Xylariales are an order of fungi within the class Sordariomycetes ( also known as Pyrenomycetes ) , subdivision Pezizomycotina , division Ascomycota .
Clanculus ormophorus is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Aconitum violaceum is a perennial species distributed in the Himalayan region of India , Pakistan and Nepal .
The Trichocephalida ( Trichinellida or Trichurida in other classifications ) is an order of parasitic Nematodes .
Legionella anisa is a Gram - negative bacterium , one of more than 40 species in the family Legionellaceae .

Acropyga is a genus of small formicine ants .
Conus lividus , common name the livid cone , is a species of sophisticated predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Peristichia toreta , common name the tower pyram , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .

Osteobrama is a genus of cyprinid fish found in southern Asia consisting of eight species .

Allium heteronema is a plant species endemic to Sichuan in China .
Characium marinum is a species of green algae ( Chlorophyta ) .
Rhododendron decorum ( 大白杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Myanmar and Guizhou , Sichuan , Xizang , and Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 1000 - -3300 meters .
Micromonospora is a genus of bacteria of the family Micromonosporaceae .

Rhagoletis batava ( seabuckthorn fruit fly ) is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Rhagoletis of the family Tephritidae .

Boa constrictor imperator is a nonvenomous boa constrictor subspecies found in Central America .
Origanum laevigatum ( oregano ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to Cyprus , Syria , and Turkey .
Traditionally , all figbirds have been considered part of a single species , S. viridis , but all recent major authorities recognize three species , the Australasian figbird ( S. viieilloti ) , the Timor figbird ( S. viridis ) and the Wetar figbird .
Oreostemma peirsonii ( formerly Aster peirsonii ) is a species of aster known by the common names Peirson 's aster and Peirson 's mountaincrown .
Oreopithecus has been claimed to exhibit features that are adaptations to upright walking , such as the presence of a lumbar curve , in distinction to otherwise similar species known from the same period .
A family Anurognathidae was named in 1928 by Franz Nopcsa von Felső - Szilvás ( as the subfamily Anurognathinae ) with Anurognathus as the type genus .

Brighamia rockii , known as the Molokai ohaha or Pua ʻala in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family , Campanulaceae , that is endemic to the island of Molokaʻi in Hawaii .
Peridiniales is an order of Dinoflagellates .
Though the species Lactobacillus reuteri has been recognized for some time , knowledge of its probiotic properties did not come until much later .
Trichocentrum carthagenense is a species of orchid found from the Caribbean and Mexico to northern Brazil .
Allosauridae was a family of medium to large sized carnivorous theropod dinosaurs .
Canalipalpata , also known as bristle - footed annelids or fan - head worms , is an infraclass of polychaete worms , with 31 families in it including the Sabellida ( tubeworms , fanworms , and feather duster worms ) and the Alvinellidae , a family of deep - sea worms associated with hydrothermal vents .
Ophiacodontidae is an extinct family of early synapsids from the Carboniferous and Permian .
Ecnomiohyla echinata ( common name : Oaxacan fringe - limbed treefrog ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Trogosus is an extinct genus of tillodont mammal .
Vaccinium membranaceum is a species within the group of Vaccinium commonly referred to as huckleberry .
Cydia deshaisiana or jumping bean moth is a moth from Mexico that is most widely known as its larva , where it inhabits the carpels of seeds from several species of the shrub genus Sebastiania ( S. pavoniana or S. palmeri ) .
Bombacaceae were long recognised as a family of flowering plants or Angiospermae .
Ficus papyratia is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ficidae , the fig shells .
Bufo dodsoni , commonly known as Dodson 's toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Calocybe is a small genus of about 40 species of mushroom , including St. George 's mushroom , which is edible , and milky mushroom , which is edible and is cultivated in India .
Alidus biplagiatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Alidus .
Codophila is a genus of ' shield bugs ' belonging to the Pentatomidae family Pentatomidae subfamily .
Batrachedra amydraula , the lesser date moth , is a species of moth of the Batrachedridae family found from Bangladesh to western Saudi Arabia , Yemen , Israel , Iraq , and Iran , as well as most of North Africa .
Anelsonia is a monotypic genus in the mustard family containing the single species Anelsonia eurycarpa , which is known by the common name daggerpod .
Divaricella quadrisulcata , or the cross - hatched lucine , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Lucinidae .
Chimonobambusa tumidissinoda ( 筇竹 , walking stick bamboo ) is a bamboo species , endemic to southwest Sichuan and northeast Yunnan , China , that has been used for walking sticks since the Han Dynasty .

Acrocoelus is a genus of alveolate .
Technomyrmex elatior is a species of dolichoderine ant which is a widespread species that can be found in many Indo - Australian , Oriental , and Palaearctic regions .
Triteleia grandiflora is a species of flowering plant known by the common names largeflower triteleia , largeflower tripletlily and wild hyacinth .
Gentianella amarella ( the autumn gentian or autumn felwort ) is a species of the genus Gentianella .
Albertadromeus is an extinct genus of orodromine thescelosaurid ornithopod dinosaur known from the upper part of the Late Cretaceous Oldman Formation ( middle Campanian stage ) of Alberta , Canada .
Barbus ciscaucasicus ( Terek barbel ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pachythyrium parasiticum .
Chaenactis glabriuscula , with the common name Yellow pincushion , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Baliesthes alboguttatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Baliesthes .
Brentidae is a cosmopolitan family of primarily xylophagous beetles also known as straight - snouted weevils .
It contains the single species Bryantia caudata , which is found on Java .
Allotoca meeki , commonly known as the Zirahuen allotica or the tiro de Zirahuén , is a species of fish endemic to Lake Zirahuén , a small endorheic mountain lake in Michoacán state of central Mexico .
Olivella biplicata , common names the `` purple dwarf olive '' `` purple olive shell '' or `` purple olivella '' is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Olivellidae , the dwarf olives .
Adrastus rachifer is a species of beetle from a family of elateridae in a genus of Adrastus .
Philydrosaurus is an extinct genus of choristoderan which existed in China during the Early Cretaceous .
Charpentiera densiflora is a rare species of tree in the amaranth family known by the common names dense - flowered pāpala and Nā Pali Coast pāpala .
Species There is only one known species , Monogereion carajensis , native to the State of Pará in northeastern Brazil .

Amurosaurus ( /əˌmʊəroʊˈsɔːrəs/ ; `` Amur lizard '' ) is a genus of lambeosaurine hadrosaurid dinosaur found in the latest Cretaceous period ( 66 million years ago ) of eastern Asia .
Limosella aquatica is a widespread species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common name water mudwort .
Charpentiera is a flowering plant genus in the pigweed family , Amaranthaceae .
Bacillariaceae is a family of diatoms in the phylum Heterokontophyta .
Bulbostylis neglecta was first collected by William John Burchell in 1806 , although the specimen was not described as a new species until 1884 .
Stellerina xyosterna , the Pricklebreast poacher , is a species of poacher native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from Canada to northern Mexico .
The only described species is Parathitarodes changi , which is found in Taiwan .
Cerithiopsis atalaya is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from European oceans .
Neocollyris schillhammeri is a species of ground beetle in the genus Neocollyris in the family Carabidae .
Ixalotriton parva , the dwarf false brook salamander , is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Rafflesia baletei is a parasitic plant species of the genus Rafflesia .
Bothriolepis ( Greek ; meaning `` pitted scale '' or `` trench scale '' ) is a widespread , abundant and diverse genus of antiarch placoderms , that was present during the Middle to Late Devonian period of the Paleozoic Era .
Aphaenogaster mayri is an extinct species of ant in formicid subfamily Myrmicinae known from a series of Late Eocene fossils found in North America .
Georissa laevigata is a species of a land snail , a minute cave snail , gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrocenidae .
Caseidae is an extinct family of synapsids from the Carboniferous and Permian period .
Thiseltonia is a genus of Australian plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Cinerocaris is an extinct genus of crustacean which existed in the United Kingdom .

Merrillanthus is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1941 .

Euchiloglanis kishinouyei is a species of sisorid catfish native to Asia .

Rhinanthus angustifolius or Greater Yellow - rattle is a Lamiales plant species of the genus Rhinanthus .

Euchilichthys royauxi is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Congo Basin of Angola , Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia .
Extra extra or Marginella extra is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Cystiscidae .
Lechriaspis is an extinct genus of poraspid heterostracan agnathan known from the Early Devonian of northern Utah , western United States .
Caviomorpha is the rodent infraorder or parvorder that unites all New World hystricognaths .
Mammillaria hahniana ( old lady cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cactaceae , native to central Mexico .
Lepetopsidae is an extinct family of gastropods in the clade Patellogastropoda .
Octomeria chamaeleptotes is a species of orchid occurring from Brazil to Argentina ( Misiones ) .
Cotaena mediana is a species of sedge moths , and for a long time the only species in the genus Cotaena .

Taxitheliella is a genus of moss in family Sematophyllaceae .
Hymenoxys brachyactis is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names East View rubberweed and tall bitterweed .
The genus ( Ziapelta ) was named after the Zia sun symbol , a religious image for the Zia people and an element of the flag of New Mexico , and the Latin word pelta ( `` shield '' ) , referring to ankylosaurids ' osteoderms .
Megacephala martii is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Perty in 1830 .
Hydrophis melanocephalus , commonly known as the slender - necked sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Dendroctonus frontalis , the southern pine beetle , is a species of bark beetle native to the forests of southern United States , Mexico and Central America .
Senna socotrana is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Yemen .
Anthocercis , commonly known as tailflower , is a genus of shrubs which are endemic in southern temperate Australia with the center of distribution in the South West Botanical Province of Western Australia .
Stictoleptura rubra , the Red - brown Longhorn Beetle , is a species of beetles belonging to the family Cerambycidae .
Jatropha costaricensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the euphorb family known by the common name Costa Rican jatropha .
Heterophyidae is a family of intestinal flukes of the class trematoda .
Stromatopelma fumigatum is a species of spider , in the theraphosidae family , currently contained within the Stromatopelminae subfamily .
Proteromonas is a genus of heterokont .
Ciliopagurus babai is a species of hermit crab native to Wakayama .
The genus Pentacosmodon , named by Jepsen in 1940 , is known from the species Pentacosmodon pronus .
Heterosperma is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to North and South America .
Davidaster is a genus of crinoids .
Calochortus tolmiei is a North American species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Tolmie star - tulip and pussy ears .
Thalassia testudinum , commonly known as turtlegrass , is a species of marine seagrass .
Galium sterneri or limestone bedstraw is a plant species of the Rubiaceae .
Odontorchilus is a small genus of South American birds in the Troglodytidae family .
The relationship of this taxon to other taxa within the Sordariomycetes class is unknown ( incertae sedis ) , and it has not yet been placed with certainty into any order . This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Teracosphaeria petroica .
The Rock firefinch ( Lagonosticta sanguinodorsalis ) is a species of estrildid finch found in northern Nigeria .
Latrodectus mactans , known as the southern black widow or simply black widow , is a highly venomous species of spider in the genus Latrodectus .
Gibasis is genus of flowering plants within the Commelinaceae family , first described in 1837 .
Hypancistrus is a genus of loricariid catfish originating from the Amazon basin in South America .
Empis stercorea is a large species of dance fly , in the fly family Empididae .
The holotrichous lady 's mantle ( Alchemilla jaroschenkoi ) is a species of lady 's mantle that is endemic to Azerbaijan , where it is only known from near Kiçik Cheurly .
Armadillidium pictum is a species of woodlouse which occurs over most of Europe , except the Mediterranean Basin and Southeast Europe .
Euthynnus lineatus , the black skipjack or black skipjack tuna , is a species of ray - finned bony fish in the family Scombridae .
Palaeomystella is a genus of moths in the Agonoxenidae family .
Luscosmodicum beaveri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Luscosmodicum .
The spider species Nephila senegalensis is commonly known as the banded - legged golden orb - web spider .
Enchelyurus brunneolus is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern central Pacific ocean , around Hawaii .
Suuwassea ( meaning `` ancient thunder '' ) is a genus of dicraeosaurid sauropod dinosaur found in the Upper Jurassic strata of the Morrison Formation , located in southern Carbon County , Montana , USA .
Iris boissieri ( also known as the ' Yellowbeard Iris ' ) , is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Xiphium .
Chlorobium ( also known as Chlorochromatium ) is a genus of green sulfur bacteria .
Elaeophora sagitta is a parasitic nematode found in the heart , coronary arteries and pulmonary arteries of several ruminant species and African buffaloes in Africa .
Allium sanbornii is a North American species of wild onion known by the common name Sanborn 's onion .
Novopsocus is a genus in the Pseudocaeciliidae family , with , until 2008 , one described species endemic to New Guinea .
Cedrela odorata is a commercially important species of tree in the chinaberry family , Meliaceae , commonly known as Spanish cedar or Cuban cedar .
Annamia is a small genus of gastromyzontid loaches native to Southeast Asia , with these species , though one of them is of doubtful validity and identity :
Dolicholatirus cayohuesonicus is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , tulip snails and their allies .
Kuszholia ( meaning `` Milky Way bird '' after the Kazakh term for the Milky Way , kus zholi ) is the name given to a genus of primitive birds or bird - like dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous .
Xylorhiza tortifolia is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Mojave - aster and Mojave woodyaster .
The Gobionellinae are a subfamily of fish in the family Gobiidae , the gobies .
Chlamys swifti , common name Swift 's scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
It was first discovered by western scientists only in October 1999 and was shortly thereafter described as a new genus and species , namely Xanthocyparis vietnamensis , closely related to Nootka cypress ( Xanthocyparis nootkatensis ) , which was also transferred to this new genus .
Zodarion maculatum is a spider species found in Portugal , Spain , Sicily and Morocco .
Bouliachelys is an extinct genus of sea turtle from Cretaceous .
Tritonioidea is a superfamily of small sea slugs , nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Dendronotida .
Myosotella myosotis , common name the mouse ear snail , is a European species of small , salt marsh snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ellobiidae .
Microstomatichthyoborus is a genus of distichodontid fishes endemic to the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Camissonia strigulosa is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name sandysoil suncup .
Gerbera ( /ˈdʒɜːrbərə/ or /ˈɡɜːrbərə/ ) L. is a genus of plants in the Asteraceae ( daisy family ) .
Laetesia is a genus of sheet weavers that was described by Simon in 1908 .
Epiphyllum phyllanthus , commonly known as the climbing cactus is a species of epiphytic cacti .
Pterichthyodes is a genus of antiarch placoderm fishes from the Devonian period .
Mesorhizobium tianshanense , formerly known as Rhizobium tianshanense , is a Gram negative species of bacteria found in the root nodules of many plant species .
The Indomalayan pencil - tailed tree mouse ( Chiropodomys gliroides ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Oenanthe pimpinelloides is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name corky - fruited water - dropwort .
Zodarion emarginatum is a spider species found in France , Corsica , Malta and Greece .
Cherentes niveilateris is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cherentes .
Hemimeridae is a family of earwigs , the only family in the suborder Hemimerina , one of the four suborders in the order Dermaptera .
Neblinichthys yaravi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Kukenan River basin .
The Calabozoidae are a family of isopod crustaceans , placed in its own order , Calabozoida or Calabozoidea .
Macropodanthus cootesii , known as Cootes ' Macropodanthus , is a species from the family Orchidaceae that is endemic to the Philippines .
The suborder Sciuromorpha contains 307 living species in 61 genera and seven families .
Bulinus hightoni is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Astrosarkus idipi is a species of sea star in the family Oreasteridae .
Dischidia diphylla was described by Adolph Daniel Edward Elmer but never validly published since Elmer failed to include Latin diagnoses or descriptions for the species he described after 1934 .
Saponaria ocymoides ( rock soapwort or tumbling Ted ) is a species of semi - evergreen perennial flowering plant belonging to the family Caryophyllaceae , native to south western and southern central Europe .
Ancylus is a genus of very small , freshwater , air - breathing limpets .
Cyperus acuminatus is a common species of sedge known by several common names , including tapertip flatsedge and pale umbrella - sedge .
Echinocystis is a monotypic genus in the gourd / melon / cucumber family Cucurbitaceae , with the sole species Echinocystis lobata , commonly called wild cucumber , prickly cucumber , or balsam apple .
Sycon faulkneri is a species of calcareous sponge belonging to the family Sycettidae .
Arthuria dubia is a species of calcareous sponge in the genus Arthuria from Australia .
Restrepia aspasicensium is a species of orchid occurring from Colombia to northwestern Venezuela .
Parcoblatta americana , the western wood cockroach , is a species of wood cockroach that occurs in Mexico and the western United States .
Terminalia petiolaris , commonly known as blackberry tree or billygoat plum , or marool in the local Bardi language , is a species of plant in the Combretaceae family .
Cyrtandra viridiflora is a rare species of flowering plant in the African violet family .
Gonepteryx maderensis , the Madeira Brimstone , is a species of butterfly in the Pieridae family .
Hakea epiglottis is a species of shrub in the family Proteaceae , endemic to Tasmania .
The apple humble - bee or apple bumblebee ( Bombus pomorum ) is a species of bumblebee .
Apolania is a monotypic genus of wandering spider , containing the species Apolania segmentata .
Omoglymmius hamatus is a species of beetle in the family Rhysodidae .
Neophygas microcephalus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neophygas .
Ochropyge is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
Mesoclemmys perplexa is a species of turtle from Northeast Brazil .
Conus augur , common name the auger cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Batrachedra arenosella , the coconut moth , is a species of moth of the Batrachedridae family found in India , Indonesia , Malaya , and La Réunion , as well as New Zealand and Australia , from the Northern Territory and northern Queensland to New South Wales and South Australia .
Sthenurus ( `` strong tail '' ) is an extinct genus of kangaroo .
Tartarocreagris texana is a species of arachnid in family Neobisiidae .
Delphinium gracilentum is a species of larkspur known by the common name pine forest larkspur .
Allium plurifoliatum is a Chinese species of wild onion .
Completoria is a fungal genus in the monotypic family Completoriaceae , of the order Entomophthorales .
Eremina desertorum ( formerly Helix desertorum ) is a species of land snail in the genus Eremina .
Typhlonus nasus is a species of cusk - eel found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans at depths from 3,935 to 5,100 m ( 12,910 to 16,732 ft ) .
Guapira is a genus of Neotropical shrubs in Four O'Clock Family .
Zodarion scutatum is a spider species found in Slovenia and Croatia .
Yersinia bercovieri is a Gram - negative species of enteric bacteria .
Sassafras randaiense is a species of deciduous tree in the Lauraceae family belonging to the genus Sassafras .
Bromus berteroanus , commonly known as Chilean chess , is a species of flowering plant in the Poaceae family native to drier areas of North and South America .
Houlletia brocklehurstiana is a species of orchid native to Brazil ( from Rio de Janeiro to Paraná ) .
Allium nevadense is a species of wild onion known by the common name Nevada onion .
Acaena emittens is a species of perennial plant limited to scrubland and forest clearings at an altitude of 450 - 1500 m in central North Island , New Zealand .
Astroloma conostephioides , commonly known as Flame Heath , is small shrub species in the family Ericaceae .
Jianghanichthys is an extinct genus of is a bony fishes or Osteichthyes , belonging to the order Cypriniformes .
Astragalus tennesseensis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Tennessee milkvetch .
Hesperocorixa castanea is a species of water boatman in the family Corixidae in the order Hemiptera .

Anisus calculiformis is a very small species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
A morpho butterfly is one of over 29 accepted species and 147 accepted subspecies of butterflies in the genus Morpho .
Clathrina coriacea is a species of calcareous sponge belonging to the family Clathrinidae .
Mimulus breviflorus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name shortflower monkeyflower .
Plionarctos is an extinct genus of mammals of the family Ursidae ( bears ) endemic to North America and Europe during Miocene through Pleistocene , living from ~10.3 - -3.3 Mya , existing for about 7 million years .
Diplodocoidea is a superfamily of sauropod dinosaurs , which included some of the longest animals of all time , including slender giants like Supersaurus , Diplodocus , Apatosaurus , and Amphicoelias .
Vitis rotundifolia , or muscadine , is a grapevine species native to the southeastern and south - central United States from Florida to Delaware , west to eastern Texas and Oklahoma .
Phrynobatrachus gutturosus , the Chabanaud 's river frog or guttural puddle frog , is a species of frog in the Petropedetidae family .
Hulkepholis is an extinct genus of goniopholidid mesoeucrocodylian from the Early Cretaceous of southern England and eastern Spain .
Thysanophoridae is a family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Bulbophyllum trichorhachis is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum , which is native to the island of Sulawesi in Indonesia .
Haplochromis welcommei is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria though it is possible that this species may be extinct .
Chondrinouvina is an extinct genus from a well - known class of fossil marine arthropods ; the trilobites .
Auzakia is a genus of brush - footed butterflies containing a single species , Auzakia danava , which is found from Tibet to Sumatra .
Draba howellii is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names rosette draba and Howell 's draba .
Erigeron hyperboreus is a rare Arctic species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Tundra fleabane .
Polysphondylium is a genus of cellular slime mould , including the species Polysphondylium pallidum .
Acacia tomentosa is a species of Acacia described by Willd .
Morpho aega is a species group which may be composed of several species .
Pecten excavatus is a species of scallop , marine bivalve molluscs in the taxonomic family Pectinidae .
Zostera tasmanica is a species of eelgrass native to the seacoasts of Tasmania , New South Wales , Victoria , South Australia , and Western Australia .
Tillandsia pruinosa , the fuzzywuzzy airplant , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Glossopteris ( Ancient Greek : γλώσσα glossa , meaning `` tongue '' , because the leaves were tongue - shaped ) is the largest and best - known genus of the extinct order of seed ferns known as Glossopteridales ( or in some cases as Arberiales or Dictyopteridiales ) .
Epioblasma triquetra , common name the Snuffbox , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Phacelia grandiflora is a species of phacelia known by the common name largeflower phacelia .
Otiorhynchus armadillo is a species of broad - nosed weevil belonging to the family Curculionidae , subfamily Entiminae .
Epidendrum macrocarpum , commonly known as Epidendrum schomburgkii , is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum , and the largest - flowering crucifix orchid species .
Symphysodon discus , the red discus or Heckel discus , is a species of cichlid native to the Amazon Basin , where found near the mouth of the Rio Negro , in the lower Abacaxis River and lower Trombetas River .
Thespesia is a genus of 18 flowering shrubs and trees in the Hibiscus family , Malvaceae , although within the family they are more closely related to cotton plants ( Gossypium ) .
It consists of only one species , Rubroxena rubra , which is found in Ecuador ( Azuay Province ) .
Erigeron eatonii is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name Eaton 's fleabane .
Acacia adoxa , commonly known as the grey - whorled wattle , is a species of plant in the legume family that is native to northern Australia .
Nibea soldado , commonly known as the soldier croaker , is a species of fish native to the northern Indian and western Pacific Oceans , and found in estuaries of south and southeast Asia , Indochina and northern Australia .
It contains only one species , Endeixis exalata , which is found in the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Bertolonia is a genus consisting of 14 species of pretty , dwarf , creeping , tender perennials , native to tropical South America .
Gonyosoma frenatum is a species of colubrid snake found in Southeast Asia .
Hymenoxys jamesii is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name James 's rubberweed .
The genus contains only one species , Pericallia matronula , which can be found in central and eastern Europe , Kazakhstan , southern Siberia , northern Mongolia , Amur Region , Primorye , Sakhalin , Kunashir , northern and northeastern China , Korea and Japan .

Centronycteris is a genus of sac - winged bats .
Festuca glauca , commonly known as blue fescue , is a species of flowering plant in the grass family , Poaceae .
Nebria crassicornis is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in such US states as Montana and Washington .
Townsendia scapigera is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name tufted Townsend daisy .
Jocara cacalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Jocara It was described by C. Felder , R. Felder and Rogenhofer in 1875 .
Oileides is a Neotropical genus of Spread - winged skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
Ichthyomyzon is a genus of northern lampreys in the sub - family Petromyzontinae , native to North America .
Pristimantis bacchus is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family , sometimes known as the wine robber frog .
Heteroteuthinae is a subfamily of bobtail squid encompassing five genera and around ten species .
Chromosera cyanophylla is a species of fungus in the genus Chromosera .
Aparallactus turneri , or the Malindi centipede - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .

Helianthus smithii is a rare North American species of sunflower known by the common name Smith 's sunflower .
Dolichoderus luridivenosus is an extinct species of Miocene ant in the genus Dolichoderus .

Diazonidae is a family of sea squirts belonging to the suborder Phlebobranchia .
Orthotylus virescens is a species of dark green coloured bug from the Miridae family that can be found on Crete and in such countries as Andorra , Bulgaria , Hungary , Poland , Romania , all states of former Yugoslavia , and Western Europe ( except Iceland ) and was introduced to North America .
Ashfordia granulata , common name the `` silky snail '' , is a species of medium - sized air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Atherinella is a genus of Neotropical silversides from freshwater , brackish and marine habitats in Mexico , Central America and South America .
Glisachaemus is an extinct monotypic genus of planthopper in the Cixiidae subfamily Cixiinae and at present , it contains the single species Glisachaemus jonasdamzeni .
Acanthobunocephalus nicoi is the only species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Acanthobunocephalus of the family Aspredinidae .
Alexandrinia is an extinct genus of mayflies which existed in what is now Russia and the United States during the Permian period .

Sonchus acaulis is a plant species in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family .
The Neoscopelidae ( blackchins or neoscopelids ) are a small family of deep - sea fish closely related to the lanternfish .
Lavandula stoechas ( French lavender , Spanish lavender , or topped lavender ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , occurring naturally in Mediterranean countries .

Mastotermes is a genus of termites found living only in northern Australia .
Hoplestigma is a genus of flowering plants in the family Hoplestigmataceae .
Leucophaeus is a small genus of medium - sized New World gulls , most of which are dark in plumage , usually with white crescents above and below the eyes .

Vanda wightii is a species of orchid from southern India and Sri Lanka .
Chroogomphus vinicolor , commonly known as the wine - cap Chroogomphus or the pine spike , is a species of mushroom in the family Gomphidiaceae .

Pladaroxylon is a genus of trees in the groundsel tribe within the sunflower family .
Diospyros crassiflora , commonly known as Gabon ebony , African ebony , West African ebony , and Benin ebony , is a species of lowland - rainforest tree in the family Ebenaceae that is endemic to Western Africa .

Hemicycla pouchet is a species of land snail in the family Helicidae .
Indoreonectes keralensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Indoreonectes .
Frankia is a genus of nitrogen fixing , filamentous bacteria that live in symbiosis with actinorhizal plants , similar to the Rhizobia bacteria that are found in the root nodules of legumes in the Fabaceae family .
Tornatellinops ponapensis is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Lupinus nipomensis is a species of lupine known by the common name Nipomo Mesa lupine .
Sphodromantis kersteni is a species of praying mantis found in Kenya , Tanzania , and Sudan .
Scheuchzeria palustris ( Rannoch - rush , or pod grass ) , is a flowering plant , the only species in the genus Scheuchzeria , itself the only genus in the family Scheuchzeriaceae .
Lomanotus genei is a species of a sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lomanotidae .
Hutias are moderately large cavy - like rodents of the family Capromyidae that inhabit the Caribbean Islands .
Medinilla cummingii ( Chandelier Tree ) , often spelled Medinilla cumingii , is a species of flowering plants in the family Melastomataceae , native to mossy forest of the Philippines at 700 - 1000 m altitude .
†Carelia mirabilis was a species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Orthotylus flavosparsus is a species of plant - eating bug in the Miridae family , which is found everywhere in Europe except for Albania and Iceland .
Neolamprologus cylindricus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known to occur in the southeastern part of the lake .
Monardella candicans is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Sierra monardella .
Nebria femoralis is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to northwestern part of Russia .
Punica protopunica , commonly known as the pomegranate tree or Socotran pomegranate , is a species of flowering plant in the family Lythraceae .
Electrographa thiolychna is a species of sedge moths , and the only species in the genus Electrographa .
Phacelia inundata is a species of phacelia known by the common names playa yellow phacelia and playa phacelia .
Rhacophorus chenfui ( Chinese whipping frog , Chenfu 's treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to China where it is found in Sichuan , Guizhou , Hubei , and Fujian provinces .
Drepanocaryum is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1954 .
Chrysopaa sternosignata is the only species in the monotypic genus Chrysopaa of the Dicroglossidae family .
Campanula piperi ( Olympic bellflower , Olympic harebell , Piper 's bellflower ) is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family , Campanulaceae .
Sternocera orissa , common name Giant jewel beetle , is a species of beetles belonging to the Buprestidae family .
Ophioglossolambis violacea is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae family , the true conchs and their allies .
Stalix is a genus of jawfishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Kennedia nigricans ( Black Kennedia or Black Coral Pea ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Corylus maxima , the filbert , is a species of hazel native to southeastern Europe and southwestern Asia , from the Balkans to Ordu in Turkey .
Calliostoma nepheloide , common name the Nephelo top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Magiriopsis denticosella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Magiriopsis .
Ceradenia melanopus is a species of fern in the Grammitidaceae family .
Majungaichthys is a genus of viviparous brotulas native to the western Indian Ocean .
Drosera yutajensis is a rare species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Carabus exiguus wudumontanus is a bronze - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Gansu , China .
Acanthosaura coronata is a species of agamid lizard commonly known as the crowned spiny lizard .
Powelliphanta augusta , previously provisionally known as Powelliphanta `` Augustus '' , is a species of amber snail , a large , carnivorous land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Trachischium is a genus of colubrid snakes commonly known as worm - eating snakes .
Eresus walckenaerius is a species of ladybird spider from the eastern Mediterranean .
Mimaderpas anteaureus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimaderpas .
Cephaloleia immaculata is a species of rolled - leaf beetle in the family Chrysomelidae , first found in Costa Rica .
Coelopa frigida is a species of seaweed fly or kelp fly .
Phrynobatrachus pakenhami is a frog species in the true frog subfamily Petropedetinae .
The Ulvophyceae or ulvophytes are a class of green algae , distinguished mainly on the basis of ultrastructural morphology , life cycle and molecular phylogenetic data .
Nebria tetungi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Gansu , Qinghai , and Sichuan provinces of China .
Gollumjapyx smeagol is a species of dipluran , named after Gollum , a fictional character from J. R. R. Tolkien 's legendarium .
The Iron Cross Beetle is a species of blister beetle that is often detrimental to humans and their livestock and is in general a pest .
Fosterella robertreadii is a species of the genus Fosterella .
Sauromalus klauberi , commonly called the Santa Catalina chuckwalla or the spotted chuckwalla , is a species of chuckwalla first identified in 1941 .
Hylarana latouchii ( Kuatun frog , LaTouche 's frog , broad - folded frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
It belongs to the monotypic genus Ameloctopus .
Koanophyllon palmeri , called Palmer 's umbrella thoroughwort , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Ceratoichthys pinnatiformis is an extinct species of lookdown - like prehistoric jackfish that lived during the Lutetian epoch , of the Middle Eocene of Monte Bolca , Italy .
Perciformes , also called the Percomorphi or Acanthopteri , are the largest order of vertebrates , containing about 41 % of all bony fish .
Pterocladiophila is a genus of red algae , parasite of other red algae .
Menticirrhus saxatilis , the northern kingfish or northern kingcroaker , is a species of marine fish in the family Sciaenidae ( commonly known as the `` drum '' or `` croaker '' family ) .
Eurygnathohippus is an extinct genus of hipparionine horse .
Dracovenator ( /ˌdræ.koʊ.vɛˈneɪ.tər/ ) is an extinct genus of dilophosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 201 to 199 million years ago during the early part of the Jurassic Period in what is now South Africa .
Octopus mercatoris , the Caribbean dwarf octopus , is a small octopus species native to the Caribbean Sea region of the Atlantic Ocean .
Junodia strigipennis is a species of praying mantis found Ethiopia , Mozambique , Natal , Tanzania , and Zimbabwe .
Oberea formosana is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Pic in 1911 .
Campanula patula or spreading bellflower is a plant species of the genus Campanula .
Gygis is a genus of birds in the tern family .
Brevioleria is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Lamas in 2004 .
Sitticus wuae is a species of jumping spider , named after the collector Hai - Yin Wu .
It contains only one species , Nonischnoscia umbraticostella , which is found in the West Indies .
The Noctuidae or owlet moths are a family of robustly built moths that includes more than 35,000 known species out of possibly 100,000 total , in more than 4,200 genera .
Bromus maritimus is a species of brome ( or chess ) grass known by the common names maritime brome and seaside brome .
Gerrothorax ( `` wicker chest '' ) is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Triassic period of Greenland , Germany , Sweden , and possibly Thailand .
Uropeltis liura , commonly known as Günther 's earth snake , is a species of snake in the family Uropeltidae .

Puffins are any of three small species of alcids ( auks ) in the bird genus Fratercula with a brightly coloured beak during the breeding season .

Chromis margaritifer , known commonly as the Bicolor chromis , is a species of marine fish in the family Pomacentridae .
Packera pseudaurea is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name falsegold groundsel .
Doleromyrma darwiniana is a species of ant in the genus Doleromyrma .
Bactrocera is a large genus of tephritid fruit flies , with more than 500 species currently described .
Entoloma bloxamii belongs to the large genus Entoloma , which contains around 1500 species worldwide .
Dasyceps is an extinct genus of an unusual temnospondyl from Early Permian of England .
Chaetopogon is a genus of European plants in the grass family .
Chlorociboria aeruginascens is a saprobic species of mushroom , commonly known as the green elfcup or the green wood cup because of its characteristic small , green , saucer - shaped fruit bodies .
Gastrochilus acutifolius is a species of orchid found in Assam ( India ) , eastern Himalayas , Nepal , Myanmar and Vietnam .
Pisaurina brevipes is a species of `` nursery web spider '' that is found in the eastern half of the North American continent , from Ontario down to Florida and west to Kansas .
Monodonta canalifera , common name the canal monodont , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Galium lanceolatum ( lanceleaf wild licorice ) is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Sphenacodontidae ( Greek : `` wedge point tooth family '' ) is an extinct family of small to large , advanced , carnivorous , Late Pennsylvanian to middle Permian pelycosaurs .
†Incerticyclus cinereus was a species of tropical land snail with gills and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Neocyclotidae .
Rubus ursinus is a North American species of blackberry or dewberry , known by the common names California blackberry , California dewberry , Douglas berry , Pacific blackberry , Pacific dewberry and trailing blackberry .
Coreopsis lanceolata , the Lance - leaved coreopsis , is a North American species of Tickseed in the sunflower family .
Anthia sexmaculata is a species of beetles of the family Carabidae .
Rheum maximowiczii is a plant species in the genus Rheum .
Methylobacillus flagellatus is a species of aerobic bacteria .
Phidiana hiltoni is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aeolidiidae .
Coriocella hibyae , common name the Hiby 's coriocella or the velvet snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Velutinidae .
Maxacteon hancocki is a species of small sea snail , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Acteonidae , the barrel bubble snails .
Ludwigia octovalvis is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Mexican primrose - willow .
Hyla arboricola ( common name : arboreal treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to the Sierra Madre del Sur in Guerrero state , Mexico .
Crangon crangon is a commercially important species of caridean shrimp fished mainly in the southern North Sea , although also found in the Irish Sea , Baltic Sea , Mediterranean Sea and Black Sea , as well as off much of Scandinavia and parts of Morocco 's Atlantic coast .
Chrysiptera rollandi is a species of damselfish known by the common name Rolland 's demoiselle .
Phrynella pulchra is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family , in the monotypic genus Phrynella .
Amphiesma modestum , commonly known as the modest keelback , is a species of natricine snake endemic to Asia .

Iomys is a small genus of rodent in the family Sciuridae .

Spiraea virginiana is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family ( Rosaceae ) known by the common names Virginia meadowsweet and Virginia spiraea .
Lewisia oppositifolia is a rare species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name opposite - leaf lewisia .
Pollicaria , commonly known as the elephant pupinid snails , is a genus of land snails with a gill and an operculum .
Pachyiulus humicola is a species of millipede from Julidae family that is endemic to Italy .

Bothrocara brunneum , the twoline eelpout , is a benthic species of fish of the Zoarcidae family .

The snipefishes ( genus Macroramphosus ) are species of fishes found in tropical and subtropical oceans at depths down to 600 metres ( 2,000 ft ) .

Stanhopea connata is a species of orchid found from Ecuador to Peru .
Aplanodema lomii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aplanodema .

Crassocephalum is a genus the common names of whose members include ragleaf , thickhead , and bologi .

Asterophora parasitica , commonly known as the parasitic Asterophora or the Russula parasite , is a species of fungus that grows as a parasite on other mushrooms .
