Bagheera prosper is a species of jumping spiders of the family Salticidae .
Cymbidiella , abbreviated as Cymla in horticultural trade , is a genus of 3 species of epiphytic orchids native to the moist forests of Madagascar .
Thelymitra cyanea , commonly known as the swamp sun orchid , is a species of orchid which is native to New Zealand and south - east Australia in South Australia , Victoria , New South Wales , the Australian Capital Territory , and Tasmania .
Odontopteryx is a genus of the prehistoric pseudotooth birds or pelagornithids .
Campynema is a plant genus in the Campynemataceae family first described in 1805 .
Allium thunbergii is an East Asian species of wild onion native to Japan ( incl Bonin + Ryukyu Islands ) , Korea , and China ( incl . Taiwan ) .
Ayapana is a genus of perennial herbs in the sunflower family .
The Ulodidae are a family of beetles in the large suborder Polyphaga .
Myripristis is a genus of soldierfishes .
Salsola stocksii is a shrub species of the family Amaranthaceae .
Tenebrio obscurus is a species of darkling beetle , whose larvae , when used as feeder insects for reptile and amphibian pets , are known as mini mealworms .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Columnomyces ptomaphagi .
Tantilla tritaeniata , commonly known as the three - banded centipede snake , is a species of small colubrid snake .
Xanthosia pilosa , known as the Woolly Xanthosia is a species of the plant family Mackinlayaceae , but sometimes also placed in Araliaceae or Apiaceae .
Euphorbia pubentissima , known by the common names false flowering spurge and southeastern flowering spurge , is a species of plant in the spurge family .
Houstonia correllii , the Zapata County bluet , or Correll 's bluet , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Lewisia disepala is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name Yosemite lewisia .
Alsodes is a genus of alsodid frogs found in Chile and Argentina .
Xylodromus affinis is a species of beetle in the Staphylinidae family , that can be found in Europe .
Garra gotyla is a species of ray - finned fish in the cyprinid family from freshwater in South Asia .
Pachymatisma johnstonia is a species of demosponge belonging to the family Geodiidae .
Rodriguezia lanceolata is a species of orchid found from the St. Vincent , Trinidad , Panama , Colombia , Venezuela , the Guianas , Peru , Ecuador , and Brazil .
The Tetrapediini are a tribe of apid bees .
Hedychium coccineum , also known as orange gingerlily , scarlet gingerlily , and orange bottlebrush ginger ) , is a species of flowering ginger .
Meganoplium imbelle is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Meganoplium .
Myxodes ornatus is a species of clinid native to the Pacific coast of Chile , South America .
Afrolittorina knysnaensis , common name the southern periwinkle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Anthoxanthum , the vernal grasses or vernalgrasses , is a genus of plants in the grass family . Jepson Manual Treatment The members of Anthoxanthum are widespread in temperate and subtropical parts of Africa and Eurasia , with a few species in tropical mountains .
Calliostoma granti , common name the multibeaded maurea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Oncidium raniferum is a species of orchid endemic to eastern Brazil .
Myrceugenia leptospermoides is a species of small evergreen tree or large shrub in the genus Myrceugenia of the family Myrtaceae .
Tilefishes are mostly small perciform marine fish comprising the family Malacanthidae .
Hyalopsocus morio is a black coloured species of Psocoptera from Stenopsocidae family that can be found in Great Britain , Ireland , Poland , Romania , and in every country of Western Europe ( except for Finland , Luxembourg and Scandinavia ) .
Carex neurophora is a species of sedge known by the common name alpine nerve sedge .
Vespadelus is a genus of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Odontobutis yaluensis is a species of freshwater sleeper endemic to China .
Francoa sonchifolia , commonly known as bridalwreath , is a plant species in the family Melianthaceae .
Acrochaetiales is an order of red algae .
Aradus is a genus of true bugs in the family Aradidae , the flat bugs .
Phlox stansburyi is a species of phlox known by the common names cold - desert phlox and pink phlox .
Laminaria agardhii is a species of brown kelp , noted by a strong holdfast and finger - like blades .
Ovalipes ocellatus is a species of crab from eastern North America , known as the lady crab , calico crab ( not to be confused with Hepatus epheliticus ) or ocellated crab .
Anomaloglossus lacrimosus is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Megasyrphus erratica is a Eurasian species of hoverfly associated with mature conifer woodlands and plantations .
Gongora galeata is a species of orchid found in Mexico .
Rheobates palmatus is a species of frog in the family Aromobatidae ; it is the type species of genus Rheobates erected in 2006 .
Hemidactylus brookii , commonly known as Brooke 's house gecko , is a widespread species of gecko .
Abraxas membranacea is a species of moth belonging to the family Geometridae .
Isocoma pluriflora , commonly called Southern jimmyweed , is a North American species of flowering perennial herbs in the sunflower family .
Oliva reticularis , common name the netted olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Eleutherococcus senticosus is a species of small , woody shrub in the family Araliaceae native to Northeastern Asia .
Anisopodus latus is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Monné & Martins in 1976 .
Pinus dabeshanensis , Dabieshan white pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Cochlespira cedonulli is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cochlespiridae , .
Rhagio tringarius , common name Marsh Snipefly , is a species of flies from the family Rhagionidae .
Hechtia gayorum is a species in the genus Hechtia and is the only monoecious species within the genus .
Typhlodessus monteithi is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Typhlodessus .
Rauvolfia sandwicensis , the devil's - pepper , also known as hao in the Hawaiian language , is a species of flowering plant in the milkweed family , Apocynaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Carex otrubae , the false fox - sedge , is a species of flowering plant in the Cyperaceae family which can be found in Central Asia , Europe , West Siberia , and Xinjiang , China at the elevation of 1,800 millimetres ( 71 in ) .
Geckoella is a genus of Gekkonidae endemic to India and Sri Lanka .
Leccinum rugosiceps , commonly known as the wrinkled Leccinum , is a species of bolete fungus .
Vulpia microstachys is a species of grass known by the common names small fescue and small sixweeks grass .
Xyris isoetifolia , the quillwort yelloweyed grass , is a plant species native to southern Alabama and to the Florida panhandle , where it is found in coastal plains , Sphagnum bogs , and the edges of sinkholes .
Incisoscutum is a genus of arthrodire placoderm from the Late Frasnian Gogo Reef , from Late Devonian Australia .
The Neriidae are a family of true flies ( Diptera ) closely related to the Micropezidae .
Rhacophorus hoanglienensis is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in Vietnam and possibly China .
Prionus californicus , commonly known as the California root borer , is a species of insect in the longhorn beetle family ( Cerambycidae ) .
Lethocerus americanus is a giant water bug in the family Belostomatidae , native to southern Canada and the United States ( north of 35 ° N ; other Lethocerus species are found southwards ) .
Nebria kabakovi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Afghanistan .
Austrochloritis ascensa is a species of gastropod in the Camaenidae family .
Gyrinoides limbatus is a species of beetle in the family Gyrinidae , the only species in the genus Gyrinoides .
Pomatoceros triqueter is a species of tube - building annelid worm in the class Polychaeta .
Curculio elephas is a species of beetle in the family Curculionidae , the true weevils .
Nemanthus annamensis , commonly known as the gorgonian wrapper , is a species of sea anemone found in central Indo - Pacific waters .
Anoplocapros is a genus of deepwater boxfishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans where they are found mostly around Australia .
Xylorhiza cronquistii , common name Cronquist 's woody - aster , is a plant species endemic to the Kaiparowits Plateau in Grand Staircase - Escalante National Monument in Kane County , Utah at elevations of 1900 - 2100 m. Xylorhiza cronquistii is a subshrub up to 30 cm tall .
Modiolus albicostus is a species of `` horse mussel '' , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae , the mussels .
Monolopia major is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name cupped monolopia .
The Anomphalidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks .
Cerambycinus dubius is an extinct species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cerambycinus .
The Dark Knob - tipped shadowdamsel , ( Drepanosticta montana ) is a species of damselfly in the family Platystictidae .
The Cochabamba mountain finch ( Compsospiza garleppi ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
Catasigerpes mortuifolia is a species of praying mantis in the genus Catasigerpes in the order Mantodea .
Quercus pontica , the Pontine oak or Armenian oak , is a species of oak native to the western Caucasus mountains of Georgia and northeastern Turkey and Armenia , where it grows at altitudes of 1,300 - 2,100 m.
Chondrinidae is a family of mostly minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the order Pulmonata .
Meadowlarks are New World grassland birds belonging to the genus Sturnella .
Menegazzia capitata is a species of lichen from Southeast Asia .
Bothrops moojeni , commonly known in English as the Brazilian lancehead , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Stenorynchoacrum xijiangensis is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to China where it is only known from Guangxi Province .
Homo gautengensis is a hominin species proposed by biological anthropologist Darren Curnoe in 2010 .
Chiloglanis emarginatus , the Phongolo suckermout , is a species of upside - down catfish native to Mozambique , South Africa , Swaziland and Zimbabwe where it occurs in the Pongola , Komati , Pungwe and the middle to lower Zambezi Rivers .
Sphenosuchia is a suborder of basal crocodylomorphs that first appeared in the Triassic and occurred into the Late Jurassic .
Boletus auripes , commonly known as the butter - foot bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Hemidactylus robustus is a species of geckota order of geckos .
Cyclostomatida , or cyclostomes , are an ancient order of stenolaemate bryozoans which first appeared in the Lower Ordovician .
Elysia pusilla is a species of small sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Plakobranchidae .
Bacilladnavirus is a genus of single stranded DNA viruses .
Stokesia vernalis is a species of single - celled ciliate protozoa of the genus Stokesia .
Micrelaps tchernovi , commonly known as Tchernov 's chainling , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Patagonykus is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Upper Cretaceous of Argentina .
It was described by Wedekind in 1914 , and the type species is Denckmannites volborthi , which was originally described under the genus Phacops by Barrande in 1852 .
Penicillium novae - zelandiae is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the plant Festuca novae - zelandiae . Penicillium novae - zelandiae produces patulin , 3-hydroxybenzyl alcohol and gentisyl alcohol
The Japanese red - backed vole or Wakayama red - backed vole or Anderson 's red - backed vole ( Myodes andersoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Heliconia latispatha ( expanded lobsterclaw ) is a plant species native to southern Mexico ( Tabasco , Oaxaca , Chiapas , Campeche ) , Central America and northern South America ( Colombia , Venezuela , Ecuador and Peru ) and naturalized in Florida and Jamaica .
Lankascincus greeri , commonly known as Greer 's Lanka skink , is a species of skink endemic to the island of Sri Lanka .
Hyperolius tuberilinguis ( commonly known as tinker reed frog ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Argyresthiinae is a subfamily of moths of the Yponomeutidae family , although it is treated as a full family Argyresthiidae by some authors .
Mountain labordia ( Labordia hirtella ) is a species of flowering plant in the Loganiaceae family .
Tanymastix is a genus of anostracan crustaceans , characterised by their lenticular ( lentil - shaped ) eggs .
Othonna is a genus of African plants in the sunflower family .
Phengaris is a genus of gossamer - winged butterflies in the subfamily Polyommatinae .
The Uranoceratidae is a family of Silurian barrandeoceroids that tend to become uncoiled with age and in which siphuncle segments tend to be expanded into the camerae .
The Littorinidae are a taxonomic family of over 200 species of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha , commonly known as periwinkles and found worldwide .
Cyathea gregaria is a species of tree fern endemic to eastern New Guinea , where it grows in lowland forest and coastal rain forest , often forming clumps , at an elevation of up to 100 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and usually 4 - -5 m tall and about 10 cm in diameter .
Oceanodroma is a genus of storm petrels .
The Acanthizidae , also known as the Australasian warblers , are a family of passerine birds which include gerygones , thornbills , and scrubwrens .
Mentzelia torreyi is a species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common name Torrey 's blazingstar .
Graptopsaltria nigrofuscata , the large brown cicada , is a species of cicada in the genus Graptopsaltria of the family Cicadidae found across East Asia , including Japan , the Korean Peninsula , and China .
The Pediciidae or hairy - eyed craneflies are a family of flies closely related to true crane flies , with about 500 species worldwide .
Cyclopsis tentacularis is a species of lumpfish native to the Sea of Okhotsk .
In his original description of the genus , Lang described the sporangia as flattened , `` with terminal sporangia that are short and wide '' , and in the species Cooksonia pertoni `` considerably wider than high '' .
Drosera tomentosa , is a species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera that is endemic to Brazil .
Iris arenaria ( Sand Iris ) is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Iris and in the Psammiris section .
Dipterocarpus obtusifolius is a common species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae found throughout Southeast Asia , including Andaman Islands , Myanmar , Thailand , Cambodia , Laos and Vietnam .
It contains only one species , Scintillithex glaucisparsa , which is found on Borneo and Peninsular Malaysia .
Streptococcus cristatus is a species of viridans Streptococcus with tufted fibrils , first isolated from the human oral cavity and throat .
Megistolepis is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Carboniferous period .
Brodiaea minor is a species of flowering plant in the cluster - lily genus known by the common names dwarf brodiaea and vernalpool brodiaea .
Marginellona gigas is a species of very large deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae .
Pachyphytum hookeri is a species of the genus Pachyphytum in the family of Crassulaceae .
Eurydice pulchra , the speckled sea louse , is a species of isopod crustacean found in the northeast Atlantic Ocean .
Ribes sericeum is a species of currant known by the common name Lucia gooseberry , or Santa Lucia gooseberry ; its Latin epithet of sericeum means `` of silk '' .
Davidaster discoideus or the beaded crinoid is a species of feather star in the family Comasteridae .
Buergerocaris is an extinct genus of shrimp , containing only one species , Buergerocaris psittacoides .
Meroctenus crenulatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Meroctenus .
Microgale grandidieri , also known as Grandidier 's shrew tenrec , is a species of shrew tenrec occurring in the dry forests of western and southwestern Madagascar .
Pilotrochus is a genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Pilotrochus besmerus .
Edmontosaurini are a tribe of saurolophine hadrosaurs that lived in the Northern Hemisphere during the Late Cretaceous period .
Hostuviroid is a genus of viroids that includes the hop stunt viroids , a group of viroids that infects many different types of plants , including the common hop plant .
Mikrogeophagus is a genus of small cichlids native to the Amazon and Orinoco basins in South America .
Dysoxylum pettigrewianum , commonly known as the Spurwood , is a species of large tropical rainforest tree in the Mahogany family .
Ceranthia tristella is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Ceranthia of the family Tachinidae .
Artemisia norvegica is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names alpine sagewort , boreal sagewort , mountain sagewort , Norwegian mugwort , arctic wormwood , and spruce wormwood .
Tectisumen clypidellaeformis is a species of small deepwater limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Lepetellidae .
Rubus tomentosus is a European and Middle Eastern species of brambles in the rose family .
Ludodactylus was a genus of pterodactyloid pterosaurs from the Aptian - age Lower Cretaceous Crato Formation of Ceará , Brazil .
Artemisia glacialis ( Glacier Wormwood ) is a species of plant in the Asteraceae family .
Potamon fluviatile is edible , as indicated by its alternative specific epithet edulis , and was known to the ancient Greeks ; it is probably this species which they depicted on medals found at Agrigento , Sicily .
Epaphrodita lobivertex is a species of praying mantis , native to Hispaniola , that was discovered in 2004 .
Oreochromis leucostictus is a species of cichlid originally native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Uganda .
Asterropteryx striata , known commonly as the Striped Goby , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
Mauritia mauritiana , common names the humpback cowry , chocolate cowry , mourning cowry and Mauritius cowry , is a species of tropical sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Papilio nubilus is a rare species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that can be found in Borneo .
Acroncosa similella is a species of snout moth in the genus Acroncosa .
Chiromantis doriae ( common names : Doria 's Asian treefrog , Doria 's bush frog , Doria 's bushfrog , Doria 's tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Pallidohecyra pallida is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pallidohecyra .
Pyropelta bohlei is a species of small sea snail , a deep - water limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyropeltidae .
Archaeonycteridae ( formerly spelled Archaeonycterididae ) is a family of extinct bats .
Elaeodendron melanocarpum is a species of shrubs or small trees endemic to northern Australia .
Papilio euterpinus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
Nephelomys meridensis , also known as the Mérida oryzomys , is a species of rodent in the genus Nephelomys of family Cricetidae .
Pinjalo is a genus of snappers native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean , with these currently recognized species :
Chrysochroa vittata is a species of beetle in the Buprestidae family .
Monardella arizonica is a plant species endemic to Arizona in the USA , known by the common name Arizona monardella .
Spermacoce ovalifolia , the broadleaf false buttonweed , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Lomatia dentata , commonly known as piñol or avellanillo , is a species of tree in the family Proteaceae .
Allium roborowskianum is an Asian species of wild onion native to Xinjiang and Mongolia .
Cerion chrysalis is a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Cerionidae , the peanut snails .
Arubolana aruboides is a species of crustacean in the family Cirolanidae .
Billbergia pyramidalis , commonly known as the Flaming torch , is a species of bromeliad that is native to Brazil , Venezuela , French Guiana , the Lesser Antilles and Cuba .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Gloeocorticium cinerascens , found in Argentina .
Oscinella frit is a European species of fly and member of the family Chloropidae .
Lathyrus splendens is a species of wild pea known by the common names pride of California and Campo pea .
Heliamphora purpurascens is a species of marsh pitcher plant known only from the summit area of Ptari Tepui in Venezuela , where it grows at elevations of 2400 - -2500 m.
The Dryomyzidae are a small family of flies ranging from 4 - 18 mm long , with prominent bristles , and yellow to brown or rust - yellow coloring .
Paragomphus alluaudi is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Philaenus spumarius , the ' Meadow Froghopper ' , is a species belonging to the family Aphrophoridae .
Rolandra is a genus of flowering plants in the Vernonieae within the daisy family .
Quercus basaseachicensis is a species of oak tree in the Fagaceae ( beech ) family .
Pseudopezus binigromaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudopezus .
Acheilognathus melanogaster ( Japanese bitterling ) is a species of brackish , freshwater ray - finned fish in the genus Acheilognathus .
Pseudohaetera hypaesia is a butterfly species from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Daphoenodon is an extinct genus of terrestrial carnivore , which belonged to the family Amphicyonidae ( `` bear dogs '' ) of the suborder Caniformia .
Chorizanthe diffusa is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name diffuse spineflower .
Rhenopteridae are an extinct family of prehistoric eurypterids that lived in the Lower Devonian period in Europe and possibly North America .
Potamotrygonocotyle is a genus of flatworms that parasitise stingrays of the genus Potamotrygon .
Anochetus goodmani is a species of ant in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Storckiella australiensis is a species of large rainforest legume trees up to 35 m ( 115 ft ) tall , constituting part of the plant family Fabaceae .
Sahyadria chalakkudiensis is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Chalakkudy River , Kerala , India in the Western Ghats where it can be found in well - vegetated upper reaches of rivers .
Pseudacteon formicarum is a kind of parasitic species of fly from the family of Phoridae of the subfamily Metopininae .
Disa stairsii is a species of Disa of the family Orchidaceae that can be found growing with the giant heathers on the Rwenzori Mountains of mountains in East tropical Africa .
Veterupristisaurus is an extinct genus of carcharodontosaurid theropod dinosaur known from the Jurassic of Tendaguru , southeastern Tanzania .
Anisus natalensis is a species of a freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Dwarf cypress ( Callitris monticola ) is a species of conifer in the Cupressaceae family .
Haplochromis petronius is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake George , Uganda .
Neottia bifolia ( syn . Listera australis ) , common name southern twayblade , is a species of terrestrial orchid found in eastern Canada ( from Nova Scotia to Ontario ) and the eastern United States ( from Florida west to eastern Texas and north to Vermont ) .
Mastax brittoni is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that can be found in Taiwan .
Tillandsia setacea , the southern needleleaf , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Paraclinus ditrichus , the Leastfoot blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Mexico at depths of from near the surface to 6 metres ( 20 ft ) .
Clematis microphylla ( Small - leaved Clematis ) is one of 8 Clematis species native to Australia .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Gelatinodiscus flavidus .
Hydnellum conigenum , commonly known as the funnel hydnum , is a species of tooth fungus in the family Bankeraceae found in North America .
Cornus peruviana is a species of tree in the family Cornaceae native to montane forests of southern Central America and western South America , from Costa Rica and Venezuela south to Bolivia .
Tilia is a genus of about 30 species of trees native throughout most of the temperate Northern Hemisphere .
Epipremnum ceramense is a plant species of family Araceae .
Seraphsidae is a family of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Coffea is a genus of flowering plants whose seeds , called coffee beans , are used to make coffee .
Prunus microcarpa ( small - fruited cherry , كرز صغير الثمر ) is a species of Prunus native to Western Asia and the Caucasus .
The hymenopteran family Scelionidae is a very large cosmopolitan group ( over 3000 described species in some 160 genera ) of exclusively parasitoid wasps , mostly small ( 0.5 - -10 mm ) , often black , often highly sculptured , with ( typically ) elbowed antennae that have a 9- or 10-segmented flagellum .
Cyanea procera is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Molokai cyanea .
Houstonia ouachitana ( Ouachita bluet ) is a species of plants in the coffee family .
Pupisoma orcula is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc or micromollusks in the family Valloniidae .
Chlamydomonas is a genus of green algae consisting of unicellular flagellates , found in stagnant water and on damp soil , in freshwater , seawater , and even in snow as `` snow algae '' .
Quasicaecilia is an extinct genus of microsaur .
It contains the single species Rimanella arcana .
Acacia pervillei is a species of Acacia that is endemic to Madagascar . The species was first formally described by English botanist George Bentham in 1875 in Transactions of the Linnean Society of London .
Pleurobema riddellii is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Cupiennius foliatus is a banana spider species found in Costa Rica and Panama .
Hintonella is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae . It contains only one known species , Hintonella mexicana , native to central and southern Mexico ( Jalisco , Guerrero , Mexico State , Morelos , Michoacán , Oaxaca ) .
Semiotus insignis is a species of beetle belonging to the family Elateridae .
Orchestina is a spider genus in the family Oonopidae .
Proportionately , the Mary River turtle has the smallest head and largest hind feet of all the species within the catchment , which contributes to its distinction of being the fastest swimmer .
Branchinella lithaca , the Stone Mountain fairy shrimp , is a species of crustacean in the family Thamnocephalidae .
Nymphargus puyoensis ( common name : Puyo giant glass frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Eucalyptus oreades , commonly known as the Blue Mountains Ash , is a species of eucalyptus native to eastern Australia .
Jasus lalandii ( also called the Cape rock lobster or West Coast rock lobster ) is a species of spiny lobster found off the coast of Southern Africa .
Morelia spilota is a large species of python in the genus , reaching between 2 to 4 metres ( 6.6 to 13.1 ft ) in length and weighing up to 15 kilograms ( 33 lb ) .
Haasiasaurus is an extinct genus of early mosasaur , originally named `` Haasia '' by M. J. Polcyn et al . , in honour of the palaeontologist Georg Haas .
Coffea liberica ( or Liberian coffee ) is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Hieracium carneum , common name Huachuca hawkweed , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family , native to Arizona , New Mexico , Texas and Chihuahua .
Mordacia mordax , known as the short - headed lamprey , Australian lamprey or Murray lamprey , is a species of southern topeyed lamprey that lives in south - eastern Australia .
Alatiliparis is a genus of orchids native to Java and Sumatra in Indonesia .
Damon diadema is a species of arachnid , sometimes known as the tailless whip scorpion .
Cycas calcicola is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to northern Australia in the northwest of Northern Territory .
Espostoopsis is a monotypic genus of cactus containing the single species Espostoopsis dybowskii .
The Flores warty pig ( Sus heureni ) , is a species of in the pig genus ( Sus ) found in southern Asia .
Sartilmania is a genus of extinct vascular plants of the Early Devonian ( Emsian stage , around 410 to 390 million years ago ) .
Togocetus ( `` Togo whale '' ) is a genus of extinct cetacean from the Lutetian ( lower Eocene ) of Togo , known from a fossilized skeleton discovered few kilometers north - east of Lomé .
Diamella kaszabi is a species of ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that is endemic to the Taiwan ( Formosa ) .
Donacia tomentosa is a species of leaf beetle , that is distributed throughout Palearctic region , and from Southern France to Central Siberia .
Bertrana is a spider genus that occurs from Central to South America .
Phoberocyon is a large extinct genus of carnivorous Hemicyonid , found primarily in North America during the Miocene living from 20.6 - -16.3 mya , existing for approximately 4.3 million years .
Booponus is a genus of blow flies in the family Calliphoridae .
Pterocerdale insolita is a species of freshwater dartfish known only from Weipa , Queensland , Australia .
Harpachne schimperi is a species of grass in the true grass family ( Poaceae ) , found from Ethiopia and Sudan south to Zambia .
Xenophora neozelanica , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Xenophoridae , the carrier snails or carrier shells .
Ethopia gigantea is a species of snout moth in the genus Ethopia .
Conus rolani , common name Rolan 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Ivesia kingii , reclassified as Potentilla kingii , is a species of flowering plant known by the common name King 's mousetail .
Azorella gummifera is a species of Azorella flowering plant .
Brachyachne is a genus of African , Australian , and Southeast Asian plants in the grass family .
Only one species is recorded , Niaftasuchus zekkeli , from Nyafta , basin of the Mezen ' River , Arkhangelsk Oblast , Russia .
Pallasina barbata , the Tubenose poacher , is a species of poacher native to the northern Pacific Ocean .
Lespedeza bicolor is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names shrubby bushclover , shrub lespedeza , and bicolor lespedeza .
Lernaea ( also incorrectly spelled Lernea ) is a genus of copepod crustaceans commonly called anchor worms , parasitic on freshwater fishes .
Noteosuchus is an extinct genus of basal rhynchosaur known from the earliest Triassic deposits of Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
Filago pyramidata , common name Broadleaf cottonrose , is a European plant species in the sunflower family .
Brickellia eupatorioides ( false boneset ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Chthonerpeton braestrupi is a species of amphibian in the Typhlonectidae family .
Linhenykus is an extinct genus of alvarezsaurid theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Inner Mongolia , China .
Peloroplites ( from Greek pelor `` monster '' , and hoplites , `` armoured soldier '' ) is a genus of nodosaurid armored dinosaur from Lower Cretaceous rocks of Utah .
Tragulina is an infraorder of even - toed ungulates .
Acemyini is a small but cosmopolitan tribe of flies in the family Tachinidae .
Iris latifolia , the English iris , also known as I. xiphiodes and I. anglica , is a hardy flowering bulbous species of the iris genus , in the family Iridaceae .
The Gobryidae are a family of five species in the genus Gobrya .
Posticobia norfolkensis is an extinct species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .

Ceanothus americanus is a species of shrub native to North America .
Galium humifusum ( spreading bedstraw ) is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Helmholtzia is a small genus of flowering plants described in 1866 .
Melaleuca orophila was first named in 2006 by Lyndley Craven in Novon when he transferred the species from Callistemon .
Cyanea asarifolia is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name gingerleaf cyanea .
Aquamarina is a fungal genus in the class Dothideomycetes .
Stratesaurus is an extinct genus of small - bodied rhomaleosaurid plesiosaur known from the Early Jurassic period ( most likely earliest Hettangian stage ) of the United Kingdom .
Stilifer is a genus of small ectoparasitic sea snails that used to belong in the family Stiliferidae .
Nebria bissenica is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Romania .
Zygosaccharomyces bailii is a species in the genus Zygosaccharomyces .
Sphaerolichus armipes is a mite species in the genus Sphaerolichus .
Ficus pumila ( creeping fig or climbing fig ) is a species of flowering plant in the mulberry family , native to East Asia ( China , Japan , Vietnam ) and naturalized in parts of the southeastern and south - central United States .
Citrullus ecirrhosus , commonly known as Namib tsamma , is a species of perennial desert vine in the Cucurbitaceae ( gourd ) family , and a distant relative of the widely consumed watermelon ( Citrullus lanatus ) .
Coreopsis stillmanii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Stillman 's tickseed .
Acropora verweyi is a species of acroporid coral found in the southwest and northern Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Australia , southeast Asia , Japan , the East China Sea and the oceanic western Pacific Ocean .
Iridoteuthis is a genus of bobtail squid comprising two species .
The Japanese clawed salamander ( Onychodactylus japonicus ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Japan .
Procoptodon was a genus of giant short - faced kangaroo living in Australia during the Pleistocene epoch .
Petrosavia sakuraii , one of three species in the genus Petrosavia , is a monocotyledonous plant first described by Tomitaro Makino in 1903 ( see illustration ) , distributed in eastern and south - eastern Asia .
Gonospira nevilli is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Magiria imparella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Magiria .
Parastylonurus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid from the Silurian period .
Descurainia paradisa is a plant species native to eastern and northern California , southeastern Oregon , Box Elder County in northwestern Utah , and most of Nevada .
Mariosousa is a genus of 13 species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Tylocephale ( meaning `` swollen head '' , from the Greek τυλη meaning ' callus ' or ' hard swelling ' and κεφαλη meaning ' head ' ) is a genus of pachycephalosaurid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous period .
The Tibetan snowfinch , black - winged snowfinch , or Adams 's snowfinch ( Montifringilla adamsi ) is a species of bird in the sparrow family .
Discotrema is a genus of clingfishes found on reefs in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Scilla buekkensis ( syn . Scilla drunensis subsp . buekkensis ( Speta ) Kereszty ) is a species of Scilla native to some beech and hornbeam forests in Hungary and Slovakia in Central Europe .
Pareiorhina rudolphi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Paraíba do Sul River near Lorena , São Paulo State , Brazil .
Linaria vulgaris ( common toadflax , yellow toadflax , or butter - and - eggs ) is a species of toadflax ( Linaria ) , native to most of Europe , northern Asia , the United Kingdom , Spain , east to eastern Siberia , and western China .
Neocalamobius clavatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neocalamobius .
Xenentodon is a genus of needlefishes native to Asia .
Lasthenia maritima is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names maritime goldfields and seaside goldfieds .
Notogibbula lehmanni , common name the many - coloured top shell , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top shells .
Cambridgea elegans is a species of spider in the genus Cambridgea found in New Zealand .
Tarachodes minor is a species of praying mantis in the genus Tarachodes .
Changmaornis is an extinct genus of basal ornithuromorph dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous Xiagou Formation of Changma Basin , Gansu Province of northwestern China .
Coomanum singulare is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Coomanum .
Helianthus agrestis is a species of sunflower known by the common name Southeastern sunflower .
Acer platanoides ( Norway maple ) is a species of maple native to eastern and central Europe and western Asia , from France east to Russia , north to southern Scandinavia and southeast to northern Iran .
Duttaphrynus atukoralei ( common names : Yala toad , Atukorale 's dwarf toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The Marasmiaceae are a family of basidiomycete fungi which have white spores .
†Partula atilis was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Jobaria was a genus of sauropod dinosaur that lived in the current - day Niger during the middle Jurassic Period , between 164 - -161 million years ago .
The Nepeidae are a family of trilobites , that lived during the late Middle Cambrian - earliest Upper Cambrian in what are today Australia , Antarctica , China and New Zealand .
Orobanche pinorum is a species of broomrape known by the common name conifer broomrape .
Pseudomys is a genus of rodent that contains a wide variety of mice native to Australia and New Guinea .
Rhynchospora megaplumosa , the Manatee beaksedge , is a plant species endemic to a small region in central Florida .
Myrrhinitis sporeuta is a moth in the Elachistidae family , and the only species in the genus Myrrhinitis .
Stanulus talboti , Talbot 's blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific Ocean .
Niuksenitia is an extinct genus of biarmosuchian therapsid from the Late Permian of Russia .
Physopyxis cristata is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Rio Negro basin .
Zanclodon is an extinct genus of archosaurian reptile endemic to what would have been Europe during the Middle Triassic - Late Triassic epochs ( 245 - -199.6 mya ) .
Spintherobolus is a genus of characins endemic to Brazil , with four currently recognized species :
The Scombridae family of the mackerels , tunas , and bonitos includes many of the most important and familiar food fishes .
Pinanga crassipes is a species of palm tree in the Arecaceae family .
Cosmoclopius nigroannulatus is a species of assassin bug family ( Reduviidae ) , in the subfamily Harpactorinae .
Ctenogobius is a genus of gobies with a wide distribution in fresh , brackish and marine waters .
Huedepohlia pisciformis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Huedepohlia .
Quercus castanea is a Mexican species of oak tree in the family beech family .
Hypselodoris imperialis is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chromodorididae .
Enchelyurus petersi is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean , in the Red Sea .
Amanita austroviridis , commonly known as the Australian verdigris lepidella , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Amanitaceae native to Australia .
Apateona hispanicum is a moth of the Autostichidae family and only species in the Apateona genus .
Capoeta baliki , `` the fourbarbel scraper '' , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Turkey .
Zyras collaris is a species of aleocharinae rove beetle in the genus Zyras .
Psorothamnus schottii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Schott 's dalea .
Ostrya chisosensis , common name `` Big Bend hop - hornbeam '' or `` Chisos hop - hornbeam , '' is a plant species endemic to Texas .
Calomera aulica is a species of tiger beetle in the genus Calomera .
Perideridia bolanderi is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Bolander 's yampah .
Asaccus is a genus of geckos commonly known as Southwest Asian leaf - toed geckos .
Onchidiidae are a family of small , air - breathing sea ( and land ) slugs .
Senticaudata was split off from the traditional suborder Gammaridea by Lowry & Myers in 2013 , as a part of a process of reorganising the higher taxonomy of amphipods .
Duriatitan is a genus of titanosauriform sauropod dinosaur that lived in the Late Jurassic in what is now the United Kingdom .
Pyramidellidae , common name the pyram family , or pyramid shells , is a voluminous taxonomic family of mostly small and minute ectoparasitic sea snails , marine heterobranch gastropod molluscs .
Ctenopoma is a genus of climbing gouramies native to Africa .
Amorphoscelis pantherina is a species of praying mantis native to Iraq .
Thyreus surniculus , is a species of bees belonging to the family Apidae subfamily Apinae .
Neogobius is a genus of goby native to Black Sea and the Caspian Sea basins .
Lasiopetalum floribundum , commonly known as the free flowering lasiopetalum , is a species of shrub which is endemic to Western Australia .
Nahangbagrus songamensis is a species of torrent catfish endemic to Vietnam .
Salarias patzneri , Patzner 's blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western central Pacific ocean .
Brymela is a genus of moss in family Pilotrichaceae .
Amaranthus cruentus is a flowering plant species that yields the nutritious staple amaranth grain .
Ceratites ( `` Horn Stone '' ) is an extinct genus of ammonite cephalopod .
The Nadkarnii caecilian , Gegeneophis nadkarnii , is a species of caecilian found in India .
Allium aciphyllum , cammon name 针叶韭 zhen ye jiu , is a plant species native to Sichuan Province in China .
Orcula fuchsi is a species of land snail in the family Orculidae .
Australopithecus deyiremeda is a proposed species of early hominin among those who lived about 3.3 - -3.5 million years ago in northern Ethiopia , around the same time and place as several discovered specimens of Australopithecus afarensis , including the well - known `` Lucy '' , a juvenile specimen .
Ecklonia maxima , sea bamboo , is a species of kelp native to the southern oceans .

Amphibola crenata ( titiko in the Māori language or mud - flat snail in English ) is a species of air breathing snail with an operculum , a pulmonate gastropod mollusc which lives in a habitat that is intermediate between the land and the sea , not entirely terrestrial and not entirely marine .
The Transcaucasian mole vole ( Ellobius lutescens ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Zerotulidae comprise a taxonomic family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Dysidea arenaria is a species of marine sponge ( poriferan ) found in the Pacific Ocean .
Paratheresina papuana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paratheresina .
Miridius quadrivirgatus , is a species of bug from the Miridae family which can be found in Suffolk and Pembrokeshire provinces of the United Kingdom .
Burnupia stenochorias is a species of small freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Canavalia rosea is a species of flowering plant of the genus Canavalia in the pea family , Fabaceae , that has a pantropical distribution .
Abananote is a genus of butterflies from north - western South America of the subfamily Heliconiinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Callionymus hainanensis is a species of dragonet native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Penstemon hartwegii , Hartweg 's beardtongue , is a species of flowering perennial herb in the plantain family .
Hymenodora is a genus of shrimp , containing four species , which collectively have a southern circumpolar distribution .
Givarbela steinbachi is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Givarbela .

Aerides quinquevulnera is a species of orchid found in the Philippines and in New Guinea .

Sinobambusa tootsik , is a species of bamboo .
Viola lobata is a species of violet known by the common name pine violet .
Agama lionotus is a species of lizard from the Agamidae family , found in Tanzania , Uganda , Kenya and Ethiopia .
Icichthys is a genus of medusafishes native to the eastern Indian Ocean and the northern Pacific Ocean .
Cyclorana is a genus of frogs in the family Hylidae ( tree frogs ) , whose members are found in most of Australia .
Leptathamas is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) with one described species , which occurs only in New Guinea .
Amantis biroi is a species of praying mantis native to India , the Maluku Islands , Sulawesi , and the Sunda Islands .
Ichthyosauridae is an extinct family of thunnosaur ichthyosaurs from the latest Triassic and Early Jurassic ( Rhaetian to Pliensbachian stages ) of Europe , and possibly also from the middle Early Cretaceous ( Hauterivian or Barremian stage ) of Iraq .
Mallinella fulvipes is a species of spider in the family Zodariidae .
Lunularia cruciata , the crescent - cup liverwort , is a liverwort of order Marchantiales , and the only species in the genus Lunularia and family Lunulariaceae .
Megalaemyia albostriata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Megalaemyia of the family Ulidiidae .
The Lance 's Brassia ( Brassia lanceana ) is a species of orchid .
Acropora indonesia is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Dr Carden Wallace in 1997 .
Ramphotyphlops broomi is a species of nonvenomous snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Canalisporium is a fungus genus of uncertain placement in the Sordariomycetes .
Melieria turcomanica is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Melieria of the family Ulidiidae .
Phallotorynus is a genus of poeciliids native to southern Brazil , northern Argentina , and Paraguay .
Leptoscyphus azoricus is a species of liverwort in the Geocalycaceae family .
Erythrina abyssinica is a tree species of the genus Erythrina belonging to the plant family of the Fabaceae ( or Leguminosae ) described by Augustin Pyramus de Candolle in 1825 .
Eciton vagans is a species of New World army ant in the genus Eciton .
The genus is monotypic , with only type species Cearachelys placidoi known .
Oncidium praetextum is a species of orchid endemic to southern and southeastern Brazil .
Cotoneaster cashmiriensis , the Kashmir cotoneaster , is a plant species in the Rosaceae family .
Striomecyna bimaculicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Striomecyna .
Drosera erythrogyne is a scrambling or climbing perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Portunus trituberculatus , the gazami crab , Japanese blue crab or horse crab , is the most widely fished species of crab in the world .
Platycodon grandiflorus ( from Greek `` πλατυκώδων '' , meaning a broad bell ) is a species of herbaceous flowering perennial plant of the family Campanulaceae , and the only member of the genus Platycodon .
The Japanese pygmy woodpecker ( Picoides kizuki ) is a species of woodpecker found in Russia , China , North Korea , South Korea and Japan .
Astragalus californicus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Klamath Basin milkvetch .
Carinonautilus is a genus of extinct , Middle Cretaceous nautilid with a very involute , compressed shell in which the whorl section is higher than wide , umbilicus is small and shallow , or flanks converge on a narrow venter that has a rounded keel .
Arrhyton is a genus of New World colubrid snakes , with 8 described species , commonly known as island racers or racerlets .
Hyperia galba is a species of zooplankton , an amphipod in the family Hyperiidae .
Andricus quercuscalifornicus ( occasionally . A. californicus ) , or the California Gall Wasp , is a small wasp species that induces oak apple galls on white oaks , primarily the Valley Oak ( Quercus lobata ) but also other species such as Quercus berberidifolia .
Segnosaurus ( ' slow lizard ' ) is a genus of herbivorous theropod dinosaur belonging to the Therizinosauridae from the Cretaceous of Mongolia .
Anemone riparia ( Thimble weed ) is an upright growing herbaceous plant species in the genus Anemone and family Ranunculaceae .
Pterolophosoma otiliae is an extinct species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pterolophosoma .
Skenea carmelensis , common name the Carmel skenea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Conus furvus , common name the dark cone , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Cycas ferruginea is a plant species native to Vietnam and to the Guangxi region of China .
Katepensaurus is an extinct genus of rebbachisaurid sauropod dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous of south - central Chubut Province of central Patagonia , Argentina .
Calochortus lyallii ( Lyall 's mariposa lily ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family .
Ecthoea quadricornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ecthoea .
Smalleyus is a genus of crabs in the family Pseudothelphusidae , containing the single species Smalleyus tricristatus .
Paphiopedilum godefroyae is a species of orchid endemic to peninsular Thailand , Vietnam and Malaysia .
Only a single species , Macrodontopteryx oweni , is known to date .
Guibourtia is a flowering plant genus in the family Fabaceae ( legume family ) .
Haliplus furcatus is a species of water beetle from Haliplidae family that can be found in Central Europe ( except Switzerland ) and Northwestern Europe ( except for Faroe Islands , Iceland , and Ireland ) .
The Ruatan Island agouti ( Dasyprocta ruatanica ) , also called the Roatán Island agouti , is a species of agouti in the family Dasyproctidae .
Echinopsis mamillosa is a species of cactus from Bolivia .
Nothobranchius rachovii , or the bluefin notho , is a species of freshwater annual killifish from Mozambique and South Africa .
Olinia emarginata , the mountain hard pear or berghardepeer in Afrikaans language , is a tree species in the genus Olinia native to South Africa .
