Scyphanthus is a genus of ornamental plants in the family Loasaceae .
Deuterosminthurus bisetosus is a species of springtail discovered recently living on the broom Genista hispanica in the autonomous community of Navarre in Spain .
The four - armed frogfish , Tetrabrachium ocellatum , is a species of anglerfish , closely related to the true frogfishes .
Tachina ursinoidea is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found in Burma , China , Nepal , Taiwan , Thailand , and Indian provinces like Assam , Uttar Pradesh , and Western Bengal .
Cassida bergeali is a species of beetle in the leaf beetle family , that can be found in Austria , the Czech Republic , France , Germany , Poland and Slovakia .
Lallemantia canescens is a species of flowering plant in the mint family .
Luzula forsteri , commonly known as southern wood - rush , is a species of perennial plant in Juncaceae family that is native to Europe , north Africa and western Asia .
The Ellesmerocerida is an order of primitive cephalopods belonging to the subclass Nautiloidea with a widespread distribution that lived during the Late Cambrian and Ordovician .
Macroplea appendiculata is a species of leaf beetle of the subfamily Donaciinae which can be found in Northern and Central Europe .
Pisidium amnicum is a species of very small freshwater clam .
Oxychilus basajauna is a species of land snail in the family Oxychilidae .
Corumbataia cuestae is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in small streams of the Tietê River ( upper Paraná River basin ) .
Streptomyces chlorus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from hay meadow soil from the Cockle Park Experimental Farm in Northumberland in the United Kingdom .
Stangeria eriopus is a cycad endemic to southern Africa It is the sole species in the genus Stangeria , most closely related to the Australian genus Bowenia , with which it forms the family Stangeriaceae .
Deinandra is a genus of tarweeds in the daisy family .
The genus , distributed in the former USSR , is monotypic , containing the single species Sphinctrinopsis pertusariae .
Atriplex spinifera is a species of saltbush , known by the common names spiny saltbush and spinescale saltbush .
Peraceras is an extinct genus of rhinoceros endemic to North America during the Miocene , living from 20.6 - -10.3 mya and existing for approximately 10.3 million years .
Dorippe frascone , the urchin crab or carrier crab , is a small species of crab in the family Dorippidae that was first described scientifically by J.F.W. Herbst , in 1785 .
Passiflora , known also as the passion flowers or passion vines , is a genus of about 500 species of flowering plants , the namesakes of the family Passifloraceae .
Hatzegopteryx ( `` Hațeg basin wing '' ) is a genus of azhdarchid pterosaur , known from incomplete remains found in Hunedoara County , Transylvania , Romania .
Calopteryx syriaca is a species of damselfly in the family Calopterygidae known commonly as the Syrian demoiselle .
Clytra bodemeyeri is a species of leaf beetles in the subfamily Cryptocephalinae that can be found in Asia Minor and Iraq .
Lascoria cristata is a species of litter moth of the Erebidae family .
Bergia texana is a species of flowering plant in the waterwort family known by the common name Texas bergia .
Laurencia is a genus of red algae that mostly occurs in the sea near islands .
Bunium is a genus of flowering plants in the Apiaceae , with 45 to 50 species .
Phacelia breweri is a species of phacelia known by the common name Brewer 's phacelia .
Bryobia is a genus of mites in the spider mite family , Tetranychidae .
Vagrans is monotypic genus with the species Vagrant ( Vagrans egista ) a species of nymphalid butterfly found in forested areas of tropical South Asia and Southeast Asia .
Gulella ludwigi is a species of very small aerobic land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Marshallia grandiflora , the Monongahela Barbara 's buttons , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Marshallia within the sunflower family .
Hoffmannius is a genus of scorpions in the family Vaejovidae .
Hypleurochilus fissicornis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the northeast and southwest Atlantic ocean .
Ponthieva racemosa , commonly called the hairy shadow witch or racemose ponthieva , is a species of orchid found from the southeastern United States ( from Texas to Virginia ) , Mexico , Central America , the West Indies and northern South America as far south as Bolivia .
Nothobranchius furzeri , the turquoise killifish , is a species of African ruvuline native to Africa where it is only known from Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
Helicia lamingtoniana , also named Lamington 's silky oak , is a species of rainforest trees , of north -- eastern Queensland , Australia , and constitutes part of the flowering plant family Proteaceae .
Synodontis cuangoanus is a species of upside - down catfish native to Angola and the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it occurs in the Kwango River drainage .
Capillaria hepatica is a parasitic nematode which causes hepatic capillariasis in rodents and numerous other mammal species , including humans .
Delphinium barbeyi is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common names subalpine larkspur , tall larkspur , and Barbey 's larkspur .
Babelomurex lischkeanus , otherwise known as the Australian Coral Shell is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Platylophus trifoliatus is a species of trees in the Cunoniaceae family .
Arisaema flavum ( Konso litota or panshalla ) is a species of flowering plant widespread across eastern Africa and southern Asia .
Myrothamnus flabellifolius is a plant species in the genus Myrothamnus found in Southern Africa .
Pseudotephritis inaequalis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pseudotephritis of the family Tephritidae .
Chirocephalidae is a family of fairy shrimp , characterised by a reduced or vestigial maxilla , more than two setae on the fifth endite , divided pre - epipodites and widely separated seminal vesicles .
Ganoderma is a genus of polypore mushrooms that grow on wood , and include about 80 species , many from tropical regions .
Solidago gigantea is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Callianthemum is a genus that consists of 24 species of little rhizomatous herbs from high mountains in Europe , Central Asia and East Asia .
Aerides maculosa is a species of orchid endemic to India .
Geastrum fornicatum , commonly known as the acrobatic earthstar or the arched earthstar , is an inedible species of mushroom in the family Geastraceae .
Salvia viridis was known as Salvia horminum for many years , as Carl Linnaeus described S. viridis and S. horminum as separate species in 1753 .
Craspedophysa monteithi is a moss bug , the only confirmed , extant species in the genus Craspedophysa .
Cirsium ochrocentrum is a species of thistle known by the common name yellowspine thistle .
Alaninema ngata is a species of nematode .
Auriculella ambusta is a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Aarabia is a genus of extinct vascular plants found in central Morocco in outcrops of Early Devonian age ( Emsian , around 408 to 393 million years ago ) .
Truncatella scalarina is a species of very small land snail that lives next to seawater , a gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Truncatellidae .
The Cayenne slender - legged tree frog ( Osteocephalus leprieurii ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , French Guiana , Guyana , Peru , Suriname , and Venezuela .
Bifidobacterium longum is a Gram - positive , catalase - negative , rod - shaped bacterium present in the human gastrointestinal tract and one of the 32 species that belong to the genus Bifidobacterium .
Rutiodon ( `` Wrinkle tooth '' ) is an extinct genus of archosaur belonging to the family Phytosauridae .
Manihot pentaphylla is a crotonoid species in the spurge family .
Bernardia trelawniensis is a species of flowering plant in the euphorb family , Euphorbiaceae .
Chlorolestes fasciatus , the mountain malachite or mountain sylph is a species of damselfly in the family Synlestidae .
Cyathea imbricata is a species of tree fern endemic to Western New Guinea , where it grows in open forest at an altitude of 3240 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and approximately 2 m tall .
Caustis is a genus of rhizotamous sedges .
Dagasuchus is an extinct genus of pseudosuchian archosaur from the Middle Triassic of Rio Grande do Sul , Brazil , represented by the type species Dagasuchus santacruzensis .
Urvillea ulmacea is a plant species in the genus Urvillea found in French Guiana and in the Caatinga region of Brazil .
Araucaria cunninghamii is a species of Araucaria known as hoop pine .
Pseudostellaria sierrae is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Sierra starwort .
Chorus giganteus is a species of sea snail in the family Muricidae .
Bolboschoenus maritimus is a species of flowering plant from family Cyperaceae .
Astragalus agnicidus is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common name Humboldt County milkvetch .
Chelidonura electra is a species of sea slug , a `` headshield slug '' , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aglajidae .
Navarretia is a genus of about 30 species of flowering plants related to the phloxes and the gilias .
Horkelia cuneata is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name wedgeleaf horkelia .
Osakia lineolella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Osakia .
Homonotus is a genus of spider hunting wasps with an old world distribution , mainly in Africa .
Priscakoala is an extinct genus of koala from the Early Miocene of Riversleigh , Australia .
Zygophyllum billardierei , commonly known as Coast Twin - leaf , is a species of plant in the Zygophyllaceae family which is found in temperate regions of Australia .
Aethes seriatana , the seriated aethes moth , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Aciotis oliveriana is a plant species native to Colombia , Venezuela , Brazil , Ecuador and Perú .
Cellana strigilis redimiculum is a subspecies of large limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae .
Duvalia is a plant genus in the tribe Stapeliae , milkweed subfamily Asclepiadoideae , in the family Apocynaceae ( dogbane ) .
Gaza rathbuni , common name Rathbun 's gaza , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Megalocoelacanthus is an extinct genus of lobe - finned fish which lived during the Cretaceous period in the Western Interior Seaway .
Snakes are elongated , legless , carnivorous reptiles of the suborder Serpentes that can be distinguished from legless lizards by their lack of eyelids and external ears .
Schwenckfeldina archoica is an extinct species of dark winged fungus gnat in the family Sciaridae known from a solitary Late Oligocene to Early Miocene fossil found in Mexico .
The order Symphypleona is one of the three main groups of springtails ( Collembola ) , tiny hexapods related to insects .
Phalacroseris is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the daisy family containing the single species Phalacroseris bolanderi , which is known by the common name Bolander 's mock dandelion .
Quercus xanthotricha is an Asian species of trees in the beech family .
Mahajangasuchidae is an extinct family of neosuchian crocodyliforms .
Marginella nebulosa , common name the cloudy marginella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Leptographium microsporum is a species of fungus in the family Ophiostomataceae .
Neoclinus is a genus of chaenopsid blennies found in the North Pacific ocean along the coasts of California , Baja California , Japan , Korea and Taiwan .
Phorcus punctulatus , common name the punctate monodont , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Pariolius armillatus is a species of three - barbeled catfish native to the upper Amazon basin of Brazil and Peru .
Potamonautes lirrangensis , the Malawi blue crab , is a species of freshwater crab in the family Potamonautidae .
Pomatoschistus montenegrensis is a species of goby endemic to Montenegro where it is known to occur in the Morača River and the Zeta and also in a natural channel in Lake Skadar which connects it with Lake Malo Blato .
The Lulworthiaceae are a family of marine fungi in the Ascomycota , class Sordariomycetes .
Bursaphelenchus xylophilus , commonly known as pine wood nematode or pine wilt nematode ( PWN ) , is a species of nematode that infects pine trees and causes the disease pine wilt .
Bisporella citrina , commonly known as yellow fairy cups or lemon discos , is a species of fungus in the family Helotiaceae .
Cratosoma pictum is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cratosoma .
Microbulbifer is a genus of Proteobacteria found in sea water .
Triplophysa grahami is a small species of stone loach from China .
Odontopleurida is an order of very spinose trilobites closely related to the trilobites of the order Lichida .
Lauridromia intermedia is a species of crab in the family Dromiidae and is native to the western Indo - Pacific .
It is the only species in the monotypic genus Madecorformica .
Nannothrissa is a genus of very small fish in the herring family , Clupeidae , endemic to the Congo River system in Africa .
Intelcystiscus is a genus of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Cystiscidae .
In the taxonomy of microorganisms , the Methanocella are a genus of the Euryarchaeota .
Hypocreopsis is a genus of ascomycete fungi that form stromata on the stems of trees and shrubs .
Acratocnus is an extinct genus of ground sloth found in Cuba , Hispaniola and Puerto Rico .
Cryptoplax striata , commonly known as the Striate Leathery Chiton is a species of chiton in the cryptoplax genus that lives under rocks and in crevices in the intertidal and subtidal waters of southern Australia .
The Metacapnodiaceae are a family of fungi in the Ascomycota , class Dothideomycetes .
Allium tardiflorum is a plant species found in Israel .
Xenobrachyops is an extinct genus of labyrinthodont amphibian from the Triassic of Australia .
Papilio ptolychus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found on Guadalcanal and Florida Island .
Funambulus is a genus of rodents in the Sciuridae ( squirrel ) family .
Prolecithophora is an order consisting of an estimated 300 species of small ( typically 0.2 -- 12 mm , one species up to 50 mm ) , active , aquatic flatworms .
Batoidea is a superorder of cartilaginous fish commonly known as batoids or rays , but it also includes the skates and sawfishes .
Jablonskia congesta is a species of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae .
Echeveria agavoides is a species of flowering plant in the Crassulaceae family , native to rocky areas of Mexico , notably the states of San Luis Potosí , Hidalgo , Guanajuato and Durango .
Herpetopoma aspersum , common name the speckled trop shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae .
Accara elegans is the sole species of the monotypic genus Accara in the botanical family Myrtaceae .
Heloecius cordiformis is a species of semiterrestrial crab found in mangrove swamps and mudflats along the east coast of Australia .
Neochloris terrestris is a microalga species in the genus Neochloris .
Banksia armata var . armata is a variety of shrub endemic to Western Australia .
Rostraria cristata , the Mediterranean hairgrass , is an annual grass species which is native to Eurasia and widely naturalised elsewhere .
Makalata is a genus of rodents in the family Echimyidae .
Carex chordorrhiza , commonly called creeping sedge or string sedge , is a species of perennial plant in the family Cyperaceae with Holarctic distribution growing in acidic bogs .
Eburia quadrigeminata , the ivory - marked beetle or ivory - marked borer , is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Ludwigia decurrens is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names willow primrose and wingleaf primrose - willow .
Pylaecephalidae is a family of dicynodont therapsids that includes Diictodon , Robertia , and Prosictodon from the Permian of South Africa .
Polydactylus plebeius , commonly known as the striped threadfin , is a species of marine fish native to the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
Trifolium subterraneum , the subterranean clover ( often shortened to sub clover ) , is a species of clover native to northwestern Europe , from Ireland east to Belgium .
Cyclopogon elegans is a species of terrestrial orchids in the genus Cyclopogon native to Brazil and Argentina .
Sturisoma frenatum is a species of armored catfish endemic to Ecuador where it occurs in high - altitude rivers .
Campyloneurum is a genus of ferns in family Polypodiaceae .
Parmenolamia unifasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parmenolamia .
Isoberlinia is a genus in the family Fabaceae ( legume family ) of five species of tree native to the hotter parts of tropical Africa .
Renschia is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described as a genus in 1888 .
Ranunculus nivalis , the snow buttercup , is a species of plant in the family Ranunculaceae .
Neoodax balteatus , the Little weed whiting , is a species of weed whiting endemic to Australia where it occurs along the Indian Ocean coast from Cockburn Sound to north of the city of Sydney .
Myrmecia rowlandi is a species of bull ant native to Australia .
Alopecosa cronebergi is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found in Hungary , Russia and Ukraine .
The Alwis ' day gecko ( Cnemaspis alwisi ) is a species of diurnal gecko endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Prionocerataceae is a superfamily in the goniatitid suborder , Tornoceratatina that was extant during the latter Paleozoic .
Phenacolepas is a genus of small sea snails that have a limpet - like or patelliform shell .
Conanthera is a genus of small bulbous plants with small panicles of blue , purple or white and purple flowers .
Penstemon clevelandii is a species of penstemon known by the common name Cleveland 's beardtongue .
Fragaria nubicola is a species of strawberry native to the Himalaya .
Cortodera pseudomophlus is a species of beetle in the Lepturinae subfamily , that can be found in Armenia , North Iran and Talysh .
Jeholosaurus is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous Period .
Conus philippii , common name Philppi 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Leptotyphlops macrurus , or Boulenger 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Hexaplex trunculus ( also known as Murex trunculus , Phyllonotus trunculus , or the banded dye - murex ) is a medium - sized species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex shells or rock snails .
Arthrobacter ( from the Greek , `` jointed small stick '' ) is a genus of bacteria that is commonly found in soil .
Dimorphocalyx glabellus is a species of family Euphorbiaceae .
Ceanothus velutinus , with the common names Snowbrush ceanothus , Red root , and Tobacco brush , is a species of shrub in the family Rhamnaceae .
Californiconus californicus , common name the Californian cone , is a species of small , predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails .
Parecbasis cyclolepis is a species of characin fish found in Bolivia , Brazil and Peru .
Tabebuia aurea is a species of Tabebuia native to South America in Suriname , Brazil , eastern Bolivia , Peru , Paraguay , and northern Argentina .
Hypericum hypericoides , commonly called St. Andrew 's Cross , is a species of flowering plant in the St. John 's Wort family .
Harpella forficella is a species of the concealer moth family ( Oecophoridae ) , wherein it belongs to subfamily Oecophorinae .
Cotinis ibarrai is a species of the Cotinis scarab subgenus Liberocera .
Demequinaceae is a monotypic Actinomycete family .
Anisogomphus solitaris is a species of dragonfly in the Gomphidae family .
Crepis pulchra is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family with the common name smallflower hawksbeard .
Paraloricaria vetula is a species of armored catfish found in the La Plata Basin of Argentina , Brazil and Uruguay .
Notharctinae is an extinct subfamily of primates that were common in North America during the early and middle Eocene ( 55 - 34 million years ago ) .
It was described by Salter in 1865 , and the type species is Burmeisteria herschelii , which was originally described under the genus Homalonotus by Murchison in 1839 .
Osteopelta praeceps is a species of small , deep water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Osteopeltidae .
Leptolalax pelodytoides ( Thao Asian toad , Karin metacarpal - tubercled toad , and many other common names ) is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Colognathus is a genus of extinct reptile from Late Triassic rocks of the southwestern United States .
Acacia ausfeldii , commonly known as Ausfeld 's wattle or whipstick cinnamon wattle , is a shrub species that is endemic to south - eastern Australia .
Hydnum umbilicatum , commonly known as the depressed hedgehog , is a species of tooth fungus in the family Hydnaceae .
Philodromus pinetorum is a spider species found from Portugal to Turkey .
Prunus myrtifolia , called the West Indies cherry or myrtle laurel cherry , is a New World species of shrubs in the rose family .
Enneanectes altivelis , known commonly as the Lofty triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny .
Torreya californica is species of conifer endemic to California , occurring in the Pacific Coast Ranges and the foothills of the Sierra Nevada .
Solanum pimpinellifolium , commonly known as the currant tomato , is a wild species of tomato native to Ecuador and Peru but naturalized elsewhere , such as the Galápagos Islands .
Galium austriacum , the Austrian bedstraw , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Nesoryzomys is a genus of rodent in the tribe Oryzomyini of family Cricetidae , endemic to the Galápagos Islands .
Eleotris pellegrini is a species of sleeper goby endemic to Madagascar where it can be found in mangrove swamps .
Neocomitidae is a family of Lower Cretaceous ammonitids comprising genera with strongly ribbed evolute ( all whorls exposed ) to smooth , fairly involute ( inner whorls mostly hidden ) shells .
Clanculus limbatus , common name the keeled clanculus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Prunus salicina should not be confused with the Prunus mume , a related species of plum also grown in China , Japan , and Korea .
For a long time the South Island piopio was considered conspecific with the North Island piopio that dwelt on New Zealand 's North Island , but later they were recognised as two distinct species due to pronounced differences in external appearance and osteology ( Olson et al . , 1983 ) .
The Western Andes toad , Rhaebo atelopoides , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae endemic to Colombia , where it is only known from the type locality in the Munchique National Natural Park , on the western slope of the Cordillera Occidental , Cauca .
Rubidgeinae is an extinct subfamily of gorgonopsid therapsids .
Agyneta mossica is a species of sheet weaver found in Europe .
Polyrhachis curvispina is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae , found in Sri Lanka .
Penicillium ochrosalmoneum is an anamorph , ascosporic species of the genus of Penicillium which produces citreoviridin .
Ankarapithecus is a genus of extinct ape .
Zalipais bruniense is a species of microscopic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Skeneidae .
Amblypomacentrus breviceps , known commonly as the Black - banded demoiselle , is a species of marine fish in the family Pomacentridae , the damselfishes and the clownfishes .
Namibicola barrettae is a species of snout moth in the genus Namibicola .
Chirostenotes ( /ˌkaɪəroʊstᵻˈnoʊtiːz/ KY - ro - sti - NOH - teez ; named from Greek ' narrow - handed ' ) is a genus of oviraptorosaurian dinosaur from the late Cretaceous ( about 76.5 million years ago ) of Alberta , Canada .
Thalictrum cooleyi is a rare species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Cooley 's meadow - rue .
Euryale ferox ( also known as Makhana in Hindi and Punjabi , fox nut , foxnut , ' thangjing ' in Meeteilon i.e. Manipuri , makhana , nikori ( in Assamese ) , Onibas ( Onibasu ) in Japanese or gorgon nut ) is the only extant species in the genus Euryale .
Hepatocystis is a genus of parasitic protozoa transmitted by midges of the Culicoides genus .
Acetothermus is a genus in the phylum Bacteroidetes ( Bacteria ) .
Elaeocarpus is a genus of tropical and subtropical evergreen trees and shrubs .
Acentrogobius viridipunctatus , or the Spotted green goby , is a species of goby found in brackish and salt water in the lower Chao Phraya River .
Americardia media , common name the Atlantic strawberry cockle , is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Ceratozamia latifolia is a species of cycad in the Zamiaceae family that is endemic to Querétaro , Hidalgo and San Luis Potosí in Mexico .
Thalassiosira pseudonana is a species of marine centric diatom .
Himerometra robustipinna is a species of crinoids belonging to the family Himerometridae .
Scabiosa stellata is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common name starflower pincushions .
Excoecaria oppositifolia , an understory and evergreen tree species , belongs to the genus Excoecaria of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Knemodynerus is a genus of potter wasps distributed through the Palearctic , Afrotropical , Indomalayan and Australasian regions .
Brachytritus hieroglyphicus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Brachytritus .
Tordylium maximum is a species of south and south central Europe , probably not native in the northern parts of its range .
Linckia columbiae is a species of starfish in the family Ophidiasteridae .
Onchidella campbelli is a species of small , air - breathing sea slug , a shell - less marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Onchidiidae .
Sargocentron is a genus of squirrelfish found in tropical parts of the Indian , Pacific and Atlantic Oceans , with the greatest species diversity near reefs in the Indo - Pacific .
Litoporus aerius is a cellar spider species found in Venezuela .
Dermatobotrys is a rare plant genus endemic to coastal scarp forests in Madagascar and from southern Zululand to the Transkei in South Africa .
Xylomyidae is a family of flies known commonly as the wood soldier flies .
The Arabian babbler is one of the 26 species of the genus Turdoides that constitutes together with several other genera the family Leiothrichidae .
Myscelia is a genus of nymphalid butterflies found in southern North America , Central America , and northern South America .
Patelloida corticata is a species of sea snail or true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Lottiidae , the lottia limpets .
Barbus figuiguensis is a doubtfully distinct ray - finned fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Macrotus is a genus of bats in the Neotropical family Phyllostomidae .
Cyclograpsus is a genus of crabs , containing the following species :
Malerisaurus is an extinct genus of prolacertiform archosauromorph known from Andhra Pradesh of India and Texas of the USA .
Salix lemmonii is a species of willow known by the common name Lemmon 's willow , named after J.G. Lemmon .
Tachina apicalis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found in China and Germany .
Neoeuxesta fumicosta is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Neoeuxesta of the family Ulidiidae .
Austrogomphus atratus ( black vicetail ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Amolops panhai is a species of true frog that can be found in western and peninsular Thailand and in eastern Myanmar .
Dillenia indica ( elephant apple , chulta / chalta or ouu ) is a species of Dillenia native to southeastern Asia , from India , Bangladesh and Sri Lanka east to southwestern China ( Yunnan ) and Vietnam , and south through Thailand to Malaysia and Indonesia .
Acanthus hirsutus is a plant species in the genus Acanthus .
Anisolabella braueri is a species of earwig in the genus Anisolabella , the family Anisolabididae , the suborder Forficulina , and the order Dermaptera .
Amblyeleotris yanoi is a marine benthic species of goby native to reef environments of the western Pacific Ocean .
Scaphiopus holbrookii , commonly known as the eastern spadefoot , is a species of American spadefoot toad ( family Scaphiopodidae ) endemic to the United States .
Dicya is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Neotropical ecozone .
Ostracion rhinorhynchos is a species of boxfish commonly known as the horn - nosed boxfish or trunkfish .
Harpaphe is a genus of flat - backed millipedes native to the Pacific Northwest of North America .
Hemerocallis fulva , the orange day - lily , tawny daylily , tiger daylily , fulvous daylily or ditch lily ( also railroad daylily , roadside daylily , outhouse lily , tiger lily , and wash - house lily ) , is a species of daylily native to Asia .
Cirsium wrightii , Wright 's marsh thistle , is an endangered species of North American plants in the sunflower family .
Pisaurina mira is a species of spider in the family Pisauridae , the members of which are commonly called `` nursery web spiders . ''
Labicymbium montanum is a species of sheet weaver found in Venezuela .
Hypericum gentianoides is a species of St. John 's wort native to eastern North America .
Mordellistena aegea is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the Mordellistena genus that is endemic to Dodecanese islands .
Taxus × media , more commonly known as the Anglojap yew or simply Taxus media , is a conifer ( more specifically , a yew ) created by the hybridization of yew species Taxus baccata and Taxus cuspidata .
Lobatus galeatus , commonly known as the Eastern Pacific giant conch , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs and their allies .
Denticetopsis royeroi is a species of whale catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is only known from the holotype collected in a tributary to the upper Rio Negro .
Leiodidae is a family of beetles with around 3800 described species found worldwide .
The Bushveld gerbil , Gerbilliscus leucogaster , is a species of gerbil found in Angola , Botswana , Democratic Republic of the Congo , Kenya , Malawi , Mozambique , Namibia , South Africa , Swaziland , Tanzania , Uganda , Zambia , and Zimbabwe .
The African rock pipit ( Anthus crenatus ) , also known as the yellow - tufted pipit , is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Drosophila falleni is a species of fly found in northeastern North America .
Angelica venenosa is a species of plant known as hairy angelica .
Ipomoea purpurea , the common morning - glory , tall morning - glory , or purple morning glory , is a species in the genus Ipomoea , native to Mexico and Central America .
Teuthowenia maculata is a species of glass squid in the genus Teuthowenia .
Ariamnes waikula is a species of spider from the Theridiidae family .
Emesaya brevipennis is a New World species of assassin bug in the subfamily Emesinae .
Morotopithecus bishopi is a species of fossil ape discovered in Moroto , Uganda .
Tanystrosuchus is a dubious genus of theropod dinosaur from the late Triassic period ( middle Norian stage , around 208 million years ago ) .
Conus lienardi or Lienard 's cone is a species of sophisticated predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Osmunda regalis , or royal fern , is a species of deciduous fern , native to Europe , Africa and Asia , growing in woodland bogs and on the banks of streams .
The Pluteaceae are a family of small to medium - sized mushrooms which have free gill attachment and pink spores .
Dorstenia fawcettii is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Jamaica and Haiti .
Sturisoma lyra is a species of armored catfish native to Brazil and Peru where it is found in the Juruá River basin .
Okenia felis is a species of very small sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae .
Ochagavia litoralis is a species of flowering plant in the bromeliad family , Bromeliaceae .
Nyctemera coleta , commonly known as the White tiger moth , is a species of moth found from India to the Philippines , and from Japan to Papua New Guinea .
Eucalyptus amygdalina , or black peppermint , is a species of Eucalyptus which is endemic to Tasmania , Australia .
Cladiella krempfi is a species of soft coral in the Alcyoniidae family .
Glomeris is largely European genus of pill millipedes .
Malus domestica ' Bramley 's Seedling ' ( commonly known as the Bramley apple , or simply Bramley , Bramleys or Bramley 's ) is a cultivar of apple which is usually eaten cooked due to its sourness .
Calochortus concolor , also known by the common name goldenbowl Mariposa lily , is a species of flowering plant in the lily family .
Hyperolius benguellensis ( common name : Benguella long reed frog , Benguella reed frog , Bocage 's sharp - nosed reed frog ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Attalia philbyi , common name Yemen mantis is a species of praying mantis native to Yemen and Saudi Arabia .
Microhyla borneensis ( junior synonym Microhyla nepenthicola ) , also known as the Matang narrow - mouthed frog , is a species of microhylid frog found in the Matang Range in Sarawak , Borneo .
Stellaria borealis is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name boreal starwort .
The genus Pseudobolodon ( `` false Bolodon '' ) was named by Hahn G. in 1977 based on two species .
Melanonus is a genus of gadiform fishes containing just two species of cod - like marine fishes .
Cheilophlebium is a fungal genus in the order Agaricales .
Mammillaria mainiae is a species of cactus in the subfamily Cactoideae , with the common name counterclockwise nipple cactus .
Penthimia nigra is a species of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae subfamily Deltocephalinae .
Isozoanthus sulcatus , is a species of zoanthid in the family Parazoanthidae .
Laetesia nornalupiensis is a species of sheet weaver spider found in Western Australia .
Cyclodium is a plant genus in the fern family Dryopteridaceae .
Clinostigma savoryanum ( pacific beauty palm , arrack tree , noyashi ( Japanese ノヤシ ) ) , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Melicerona felina , common name the kitten cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Vitis acerifolia is a species of grape native to the south - central part of the Great Plains of the United States ( Kansas , Oklahoma , northern Texas , eastern Colorado , and northeastern New Mexico ) .
Sceloporus occidentalis taylori is a subspecies of the western fence lizard , commonly called the Sierra fence lizard .
Pristimantis chiastonotus ( French name : `` eleutherodactyle porte - x '' ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Pardalinops testudinaria , common name : the tortoise dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Heuchera hirsutissima is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name shaggy - haired alumroot .
The Red Grasshawk , also known as Common Parasol , and Grasshawk dragonfly , ( Neurothemis fluctuans ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Sphodros is a genus of mygalomorph spiders that occurs in the USA and Mexico .
Cryptocentrus leptocephalus , the Pink - speckled shrimpgoby , is a species of goby native to the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs on silty substrates in coastal reefs , lagoons , mangrove swamps and tide pools .
Triportheus is a genus of characiform fishes from South America , including Trinidad .
It contains only one species , Micronyctemera fojaensis , which is found in Papua .
Coralliozetus rosenblatti , the Spikefin blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Musa nagensium is a species of the genus Musa , found in North - east India .
Tholymis tillarga , the coral - tailed cloudwing , is a species of dragonfly found from tropical West Africa to the Pacific Islands .
Acantholycosa paraplumalis is a species of wolf spider only known from the northern Altai Mountains , Russia .
North American river otters , like most predators , prey upon the most readily accessible species .
Tremella encephala is a species of fungus producing pink , brain - like , gelatinous basidiocarps ( fruit bodies ) .
Salacca is a genus of about 20 species of palms native to Southeast Asia and the eastern Himalayas .
Parakannemeyeria is an extinct genus of dicynodont .
Yukoniidae is a family of trilobites , belonging to the Eodiscina , small trilobites with headshield and tailshield of equal size and shape , and with two or three thorax segments .
Micrechites is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1857 .
Papilio appalachiensis , the Appalachian tiger swallowtail , is a species of swallowtail butterfly found in the eastern United States , particularly in the Appalachian Mountains .
Ceratophyllum demersum , commonly known as hornwort , rigid hornwort , coontail , or coon 's tail , is a species of Ceratophyllum .
Cotoneaster scandinavicus ( Scandinavian Cotoneaster ) is a species of Cotoneaster native to Scandinavia , in Norway , Sweden and Finland south of the Arctic Circle , the Danish island of Bornholm , and also the Baltic States of Estonia and Latvia .
Caenopedina pulchella is a species of sea urchins of the Family Pedinidae .
Platygillellus bussingi , Bussing 's stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of Costa Rica and Panama where it can be found on sandy bottoms at depths of from 1 to 15 metres ( 3.3 to 49.2 ft ) .
Sceloporus magister , also known as the desert spiny lizard , is a lizard species of the family Phrynosomatidae , native to the Chihuahuan Desert and Sonoran Desert of North America
Spermophorides baunei is a cellar spider species found in Sardinia .
Allium calamarophilon is a species of plant in the genus Allium .
Haplochromis rubripinnis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria .
Cipocereus is a genus of cacti from Brazil .
Cunninghamites elegans is an extinct conifer species in the family Cupressaceae .
The Anomoeotidae are a family of moths in the Lepidoptera order of about 40 species , with Afrotropical and Oriental distribution .
Drosera pallida , the pale rainbow , is a climbing or scrambling perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Molgula citrina is a species of solitary tunicate in the family Molgulidae .
Leptobrachium hasseltii ( Hasselt 's toad , Java spadefoot toad , Hasselt 's litter frog , Tschudi 's frog ) is a species of toad found in Southeast Asia .
Megacephala lucifera is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Erichson in 1847 , and can be found only in Bolivia and Peru .
Other species affected by this rust include Convallaria majalis , Dactylorhiza fuchsii , Dactylorhiza incarnata , Dactylorhiza majalis , Gymnadenia conopsea , Neottia ovata , Paris quadrifolia and Phalaris arundinacea A specialised form , Puccinia sessilis f.sp .

Tachina fera is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae .

Pyrgomantis ornatipes is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia .
Kirkia is a genus of plant in family Kirkiaceae .
Streptomyces canus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in the USA .
Megacephala cuprascens is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sumlin in 1997 , and can be found in Australia .
Acer browni is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a series of isolated fossil leaves and samaras .
Silene parishii is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Parish 's catchfly .
Pseudogastromyzon is a genus of gastromyzontid loaches from fast - flowing streams and rivers in China and Vietnam .
Cyathea ferruginea is a species of tree fern endemic to the Philippines .

Emblemaria nivipes , the Whiteback signal blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Costa Rica and Colombia , in the eastern central Pacific Ocean .
Scirpus flaccidifolius , the reclining bulrush , is an uncommon plant species endemic to a small region in Virginia and North Carolina .
Plectropygus mucoreus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Plectropygus .
Pilea napoana is a species of plant in the Urticaceae family .
Threskiornis is a genus of ibises , wading birds of the family Threskiornithidae .

Stegommata hesperias is a species of moths in the genus Stegommata .
Orostachys is a genus of Crassulaceae that contains 14 accepted species .
Spirobolellus praslinus is an extinct species of millipede in the family Spirobolidae .
Dendrocalamus giganteus , also known as dragon bamboo or one of several species called giant bamboo , is a giant tropical and subtropical , dense - clumping species native to Southeast Asia .
Octogomphus is a genus of club - tailed dragonflies found in North America , commonly called grappletail .
Prejanopterus is an extinct genus of pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Lower Cretaceous ( lower Aptian age ) layers of the Leza Formation of La Rioja , Spain .
Solanum cajanumense ( also known as casana ) is a species of plant in the Solanaceae family .
Keckiella ternata is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name scarlet keckiella .
Tachina turanica is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Russia .
Raffray 's bandicoot ( Peroryctes raffrayana ) is a species of marsupial in the family Peroryctidae .
Helianthus argophyllus is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name Silverleaf sunflower .
Echinoecus is a genus of crabs that live in association with sea urchins .
Platystictidae is a family of damselflies , commonly known as shadowdamsels .

Namurotypus is an extinct genus of griffenfly .
Polycladus is a genus of land planarians from South America , currently comprising a single species , Polycladus gayi .

Astragalus pseudiodanthus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Tonopah milkvetch .
Mixobrycon ribeiroi is a species of characin endemic to Paraguay , where it is found in the Paraguay River basin .

Turritella ligar , common name : the Ligar screw shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turritellidae .
Dircenna is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Doubleday in 1847 .
Ribes divaricatum is a species of in the genus Ribes found in the forests , woodlands , and coastal scrub of western North America from British Columbia to California .
Wollea is a genus of filamentous , heterocystous cyanobacterium that forms macroscopic colonies in freshwater habitats .
Mastax annulata is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that can be found in India .
Calliostoma bairdii , common name the Baird 's top shell , is a species of sea snail with an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae , the calliostoma top snails .

Bruciana pediger is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Bruciana .
Streptanthus insignis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names plumed jewelflower and San Benito jewelflower .
Odonteuxina is a subgenus of air - breathing land snails with a clausilium , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails .

Udea fulvalis is a species of moth of the family Crambidae found in Europe .
Lampranthus aurantiacus , the trailing ice plant , is a plant species in the genus Lampranthus native to South Africa and naturalized in gardens all around the world .
Metapolybia aztecoides is a species of vespid wasp .
Pristimantis adnus is a species of frog endemic to Panama ; it is only known from its type locality in Serranía del Sapo , Darién Province .

Calofulcinia is a praying mantis genus in the tribe Fulcinini .
Meroles is a genus of lizards , commonly known as desert lizards , in the family Lacertidae .
Nebria molendai is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Rolwaling valley , Nepal .
Kutorgina is a genus of Cambrian brachiopod and is one of the earliest of the articulates , known as rhynchonelliforms .
Gairdner 's shrewmouse ( Mus pahari ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in China , India , Laos , Myanmar , Thailand , and Vietnam .

Luzula divaricata is a species of flowering plant in the rush family known by the common name forked woodrush .

The Galatheoidea are a superfamily of decapod crustaceans comprising the porcelain crabs and some squat lobsters .
The eastern cherry fruit fly , Rhagoletis cingulata ( Loew ) , is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Rhagoletis of the family Tephritidae .

Conodonts ( Greek kōnos , `` cone '' , + odont , `` tooth '' ) are extinct chordates resembling eels , classified in the class Conodonta .
Hippolytia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family native to temperate Asia .

Cycas arnhemica is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to Australia , in the northwest of Northern Territory in Arnhem Land , after which it is named .

Due to the widespread distribution of the species , and doubts over its chances of undergoing a population decline caused by man - made pollution ( in lieu of its deep - water nature ) , the IUCN redlist currently lists Ariosoma selenops as Least Concern .

Tonella tenella is one of two herbaceous plant species in genus Tonella , which has been recently reclassified as a member of Plantaginaceae .
Aletris aurea , Golden Unicorn Root is a plant species native to the southeastern United States from eastern Texas and southeastern Oklahoma to Maryland .
Rhododendron ovatum is an elepidote rhododendron species native to China and Taiwan .
Uberabatitan ( meaning `` Uberaba titan '' , in reference to where it was found ) is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .

Elymus hoffmannii ( also , E. hoffmanni ) is a species of grass known by the common name RS wheatgrass .

Dalbergia bariensis ( Burmese Rosewood ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
The genus contains a single described species , Phasmagyps patritus which is possibly the oldest New World vulture known , though its placement in the Cathartidae family has been questioned .

Ancistrus claro is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Cuiabá River basin .
Pistius is a genus of crab spiders with nine described species .
Only one species has been described , Watongia meieri , from the Chickasha Formation .

Quercus michauxii , the swamp chestnut oak , is a species of oak in the white oak section Quercus section Quercus in the beech family .
Nebria pulchrior is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Yunnan province of China .
Tauschia parishii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Parish 's umbrellawort .
Eriogonum exilifolium is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name dropleaf buckwheat .
Ischnolepis is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1909 .
Pompilus cinereus , the Leaden Spider Wasp is the most widespread species of the Pompilus spider wasps and throughout a large proportion of its wide distribution is the only species of Pompilus .
Rubus argutus is a North American species of prickly bramble in the rose family .
Vermilacinia reptilioderma is classified in the subgenus Vermilacinia in which it is distinguished from related species by features of the cortex and secondary metabolites ( lichen substances ) .
Xanthophyllum korthalsianum is a rare species , growing naturally in Sumatra and Borneo .
Abrotanella is a genus in the family Asteraceae , of 20 species , native to Australia , New Zealand and southern South America .
Eburia blancaneaui is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Belize , El Salvador , Guatemala , Honduras and Mexico .
Spathoglottis plicata is a species of terrestrial orchid found from tropical and subtropical Asia to the western Pacific including Hawaiʻi , Tonga and Samoa .
Doodia aspera was one of the many species first described by the botanist Robert Brown in his 1810 work Prodromus Florae Novae Hollandiae et Insulae Van Diemen , and it still bears its original name .
Polystichum kruckebergii is a species of fern known by the common names Kruckeberg 's sword fern and Kruckeberg 's hollyfern .
The Aeglidae are a family of freshwater crustaceans currently restricted to South America .
Myoxanthus punctatus is a species of orchid occurring from Mexico to Guyana .
Xylosybra fasciculosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Xylosybra .
Oxyopes is a genus of lynx spiders found worldwide .
Pelargonium album is a species of flowering plant of the genus Pelargonium .
Saintpaulia teitensis is a species of Saintpaulia endemic to 1 square kilometer on Mbololo Hill in the Taita Hills of southern Kenya .
Advena campbelli was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicarionidae .
Pareutropius debauwi is a species of fish in the Schilbeidae , the schilbid catfishes .
Asperula virgata , the rod - shaped woodruff , is a species in the family Rubiaceae .
Platycheirus ambiguus is a small widespread species of hoverfly found across Eurasia from Ireland to Japan .
The Hawaiian flagtails are species of the genus of flagtail fishes found in the Hawaiian Islands .
Purpurellus gambiensis , common name : the Gambia Murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Leptolinea tardivitalis is a mesophilic , non - spore - forming , non - motile , Gram - negative , filamentous bacteria with type strain YMTK-2 T ( = JCM 12579 T = DSM 16556 T ) , the type species of its genus .
Encephalartos kisambo is a species of cycad in the family Zamiaceae .
Panulirus guttatus , the spotted spiny lobster or Guinea chick lobster , is a species of spiny lobster that lives on shallow rocky reefs in the tropical West Atlantic and Caribbean Sea .
The Caprimulgiformes is an order of birds that includes a number of birds with global distribution ( except Antarctica ) .
Garcinia hanburyi is a plant species in the genus Garcinia the gamboge trees .
Christensonella is a genus of orchids native to Mexico , South America and Central America .
Plantago cretica is a species of Plantago , family Plantaginaceae .
Neoxenicotela mausoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neoxenicotela .
Juxtastenopus spinulatus is a species of stenopodidean shrimp .
Phyllomedusa ecuatoriana is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to Ecuador .
Tarsoctenus corytus is a Neotropical species of butterfly in the family Hesperiidae ( Pyrginae ) .
Microphysula cookei , common name the Vancouver snail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Thysanophoridae .
Paurodon is an extinct genus of Late Jurassic mammal from the Morrison Formation of the western US .
Glycymeris pectinata , or the comb bittersweet , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Glycymerididae .
Antricola marginatus is a species of tick in the family Argasidae .
Swainsona is a large genus of flowering plants native to Australasia .
Hedyosmum mexicanum is a species of plant in the Chloranthaceae family .
Penicillium menonorum is a monoverticillate , non - vesiculate species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from rhizosphere soil in Korea .
Phacelia imbricata is a species of phacelia known by the common name imbricate phacelia .
Moehringia lateriflora ( bluntleaf sandwort ) is a plant species native to Europe , Asia , the northern United States and most of Canada .
Eurycephalella is an extinct genus of frog which existed in what is now Brazil during the lower Cretaceous period .
Loricariichthys is a genus of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Loricariidae .
Sternarchogiton nattereri is a species of weakly electric knifefish in the family Apteronotidae .
Muttaburrasaurus was a genus of herbivorous ornithopod dinosaur , which lived in what is now northeastern Australia sometime between 112 and 99.6 million years ago during the early Cretaceous Period .
Physarum aeneum is a slime mould species from the order Physarida .
The Cryptobranchoidea are a suborder of salamanders found in the eastern United States , China , Taiwan , and Japan .
Clione antarctica is a species of `` sea angel '' , a sea slug , a pelagic marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clionidae , the `` sea angels '' .
Cryptostylis , commonly known as the tongue orchid , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Nicomioides larvatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Nicomioides .
Lobelia gattingeri is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family commonly called Gattinger 's lobelia .
Anabaena circinalis is a species of Gram - negative , photosynthetic cyanobacteria common to freshwater environments throughout the world .
Lecanoromycetes is the largest class of lichenized fungi .
Lasaeola tristis is a tangle web spider species found from Europe to Central Asia .
Malacothamnus palmeri is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names Palmer 's bushmallow and Santa Lucia bushmallow .
It is the sole species of Heteromeles , but is closely related to the Asian genus Photinia .
Dermatias platynogaster is a species of dreamer ( type of deep - sea anglerfish ) found in the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of 549 to 1,342 metres ( 1,801 to 4,403 ft ) in the waters around the Philippines and in the area of the Magellan Seamounts .
Hylotelephium spectabile ( formerly called Sedum spectabile ) is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family Crassulaceae , native to China and Korea .
Sponges are animals of the phylum Porifera ( /pɒˈrɪfərə/ ; meaning `` pore bearer '' ) .
Aneilema is a genus of monocotyledonous plants of approximately 60 species .
Rhinotia haemoptera , the red weevil , is a beetle species in the genus Rhinotia found in Australia .
The Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus ( MERS - CoV ) , or EMC/2012 ( HCoV - EMC/2012 ) , is a novel positive - sense , single - stranded RNA virus of the genus Betacoronavirus .
Bazzania trilobata , the greater whipwort or threelobed bazzania , is a species of liverwort in the Lepidoziaceae family .
Diplotaxis erucoides , the white rocket or white wallrocket , is a species of annual herb of the family Brassicaceae native to West Mediterranean .
Atalaya capensis ( also called Cape Wing - nut ) is a species of plant in the Sapindaceae family .
The only species , Eleiodoxa conferta , is a dioecious , swamp - dwelling plant , commonly called kelubi or asam paya .
Pholiotina cyanopus is a species of fungus currently assigned to the genus Pholiotina that contains the psychoactive compound psilocybin .
Amara aeneopolita is a species of beetle of the genus Amara in the Carabidae family that is native to Asia .
Turfanosuchus is a genus of archosauriform reptile which lived during the Middle Triassic of northwestern China .
Clemmys is a genus of turtle , consisting of one North American species , the spotted turtle ( C. guttata ) .
Synchiropus lateralis is a species of dragonet native to the South China Sea .
Traubia is a genus of Chilean plants in the Amaryllis fammily .
Agave shawii , with the common names coastal agave or Shaw 's agave is a species in the genus Agave .
Roestes is a genus of dogtooth characins from tropical South America , where found in the Amazon Basin and various rivers in the Guianas .
Stefania oculosa ( common name in Spanish : rana stefania de ojos grandes ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Liatris ohlingerae is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Florida blazing star , Florida gayfeather , scrub blazing star , and sandtorch .
Herina nigrina is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in most of Western Europe .
The genus Basella is the type genus of the plant family Basellaceae .
Brachypleura novaezeelandiae , the yellow - dabbled flounder or yellow citharid , is a species of citharid flounder native to the western and central Indo - Pacific .
Hippocampus sarmaticus is an extinct species of seahorse , found in 2005 in the coprolitic horizon of the Tunjice hills Lagerstätte in Slovenia , along with the related Hippocampus slovenicus .
Cathetopteron amoena is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cathetopteron .
Lagophylla glandulosa is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family known by the common name glandular hareleaf .
Sphagesauridae is a Gondwanan family of mesoeucrocodylians that lived during the Late Cretaceous .
Cyrtotrachelus elegans is a beetle species belonging to the genus Cyrtotrachelus .
Wimania is an extinct genus of coelacanth that lived during the Triassic period of Svalbard .
Homalopoma luridum , common name Dall 's dwarf turban , is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
Passiflora includes 47 species , one of which is Passiflora mixta which can be found in Southern America .
Parahupehsuchus is an extinct genus of hupehsuchian marine reptile from the Early Triassic of China .
Dendromecon harfordii , known by the common names Channel Islands tree poppy and Harford 's tree poppy , is a species of flowering plant in the poppy family .
Allium alibile is a plant species native to Ethiopia , Sudan and Saudi Arabia .
Streptomyces abikoensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which produces the antibiotic abikoviromycin .
Neslia paniculata ( commonly called ball mustard ) is a plant species in the mustard family ( Brassicaceae ) .
Plectrurus canaricus , commonly known as the Karnataka shieldtail , is a species of uropeltid snake endemic to India .
The American red squirrel ( Tamiasciurus hudsonicus ) is one of three species of tree squirrel currently classified in the genus Tamiasciurus , known as the pine squirrels ( the others are the Douglas squirrel , T. douglasii and Mearns 's squirrel , T. mearnsi ) .
Cliona celata , occasionally called the Red Boring Sponge , is a species of demosponge belonging the family Clionaidae .
In New Zealand it is commonly known as the orange - fronted parakeet , a name it shares with a species from Central America , while in the rest of the world it 's known as Malherbe 's parakeet .
It is the only species of the Bradypodicola genus .
Fagonia laevis ( California fagonbush ) is a species of plant in the Zygophyllaceae , the caltrop family , specifically the fagonbushes .
Poyntonophrynus parkeri ( common name : Parker 's toad , Mangasini toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Artediellina antilope is a species of sculpin native to the Sea of Okhotsk where it occurs at depths of from 300 to 615 metres ( 984 to 2,018 ft ) .
Volvox globator is a species of green algae of the genus Volvox .
Costemilophus aurantius is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Costemilophus .
Lamprologus kungweensis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is known from the northwestern part of the lake in Kungwe Bay , Kigoma , Tanzania where it can be found living in shells .
Pelegrina galathea , commonly known as the peppered jumper , is a species of jumping spider .
Mycena aetites , commonly known as the drab bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .

Zeltnera venusta is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common names California centaury , charming centaury and canchalagua .

Allium tschimganicum is a Central Asian species of onion native to Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan .
Laquintasaura is a genus of Venezuelan dinosaur containing only the single species Laquintasaura venezuelae .
Iochroma is a genus of about 34 species of shrubs and small trees found in the forests of South America .
Pulmonaria ( lungwort ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Boraginaceae , native to Europe and western Asia , with one species ( P. mollissima ) east to central Asia .

Nemacladus gracilis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names slender threadplant or slender nemacladus .

Haplomacrourus nudirostris , the Naked snout rattail is a benthic species of rattail found in the southern oceans where it occurs on the continental slopes at depths of from 690 to 1,590 metres ( 2,260 to 5,220 ft ) This species grows to a length of 57.5 centimetres ( 22.6 in ) TL .

Dipterocarpus bourdilloni is a species of large tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae endemic to the Western Ghats principally in the state of Kerala in India .

Scinax x - signatus ( common name : Venezuela snouted treefrog or Venezuelan snouted treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Jarvikia is a genus of prehistoric lungfish which lived during the Devonian period .
Porcellio rufobrunneus is a species of woodlouse from the Porcellionidae family .
Triphysaria micrantha is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name purplebeak owl's - clover .
Neraudia angulata is a rare species of flowering plant in the nettle family known by the common name angularfruit ma'oloa .
Graptopetalum paraguayense is a species of succulent plant in the jade plant family , Crassulaceae , that is native to Tamaulipas , Mexico .
Pseudarctia nivea is a species of tussock moth in the Erebidae family .
Epirus minnow or tsima ( pelasgus epiroticus ) , is a species of freshwater minnow in the Cyprinidae family .
Zodarion pacificum is a spider species found in Croatia and Bosnia .
Eleutherodactylus nivicolimae ( Spanish : Rana - chirriadora Del Nevado De Colima ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Scaphella neptunia , commonly known as the Neptune volute is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Pseudotaranis is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pseudomelatomidae , the turrids .
Carpathica calophana is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oxychilidae .
Anchoa lyolepis , the shortfinger anchovy , is a species of anchovy native to the western Atlantic Ocean from New York to Brazil .
Myriophyllum variifolium is a species of water milfoil native to eastern Australia where it grows in aquatic habitat such as ponds and streams .
Anatemnus seychellesensis is a species of pseudoscorpion that is endemic to the Seychelles , and is known from a single specimen from Silhouette Island .
Campylobacter lanienae is a species of Campylobacter found in humans and other animals .
Haptoclinus is a genus of labrisomid blennies native to the western central Atlantic Ocean and Caribbean Sea .
Galium andrewsii is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names phloxleaf bedstraw , Andrews ' bedstraw , and Needlemat galium .
Kentrocapros is a genus of deepwater boxfishes native to coastal waters of the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Saicella is a genus of assassin bugs endemic to Hawaii .
Salix caprea ( goat willow , also known as the pussy willow or great sallow ) is a common species of willow native to Europe and western and central Asia .
Quercus turbinella is a North American species of oak known by the common names Sonoran scrub oak , shrub live oak , and grey oak .
Hackelia cronquistii is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Cronquist 's stickseed .
Tamolanica tamolana , common name New Guinea shield mantis , is a species of praying mantis native to New Guinea .
Phryganistria tamdaoensis is a species of stick insect belonging to the family of giant sticks .
Triplophysa alexandrae is a species of stone loach in the genus Triplophysa endemic to Sichuan , China .
Lerheimia is a genus of chironomid midges containing four described species found in Tanzania and the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Zabrus punctifrons is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Turkey .
†Partula crassilabris was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Chrysopelea , more commonly known as the flying snake or gliding snake , is a genus that belongs to the family Colubridae .
Ferdinand Frantz ( born February 8 , 1906 , Kassel - May 26 , 1959 , Munich ) , was a German operatic bass - baritone .
Carmen Giannattasio ( born 24 April 1975 Avellino ) is an Italian operatic soprano .
Betsy Norden ( born October 17 , 1945 ) is an American soprano who appeared with the Metropolitan Opera over 500 times .
Steven Dorian ( born November 15 , 1977 ) is an American singer best known as a tenor in the a cappella group Rockapella since January 2010 .
Olga Peretyatko ( Russian : Ольга Перетятько ; born 21 May 1980 in Leningrad , now Saint Petersburg ) is a Russian operatic soprano .
August Kindermann ( 6 February 1817 , Potsdam -- 6 March 1891 , Munich ) was a German bass - baritone singer and regisseur , particularly noted for his performances in the operas of Richard Wagner .
Elizabeth Masson ( 1806 -- 9 January 1865 ) was an English mezzo - soprano singer and composer .
Mary Dunleavy ( born 1966 ) is an American soprano who has performed with major opera companies and orchestras around the world .
Gordon Wry ( 1910 - 1985 ) was a Canadian tenor and conductor .
Maria Fontosh ( born 5 June 1976 ) is a Ukrainian born Russian soprano residing in Sweden .
( Maria ) Josepha Weber ( later Josepha Hofer , Josepha Meier ; 1758 -- December 29 , 1819 ) was a German soprano of the classical era .
Anna Bonitatibus ( born in Potenza ) is an Italian mezzo - soprano .
Mary Rawcliffe is an American soprano .
Cecilia Gasdia ( tʃeˈtʃiːlja ɡaˈzdiːa ) ( born August 14 , 1960 , Verona ) is an Italian operatic soprano .
Francesco Demuro ( born 6 January 1978 ) , is an Italian operatic tenor .
Andreas Scholl ( born 10 November 1967 ) is a German countertenor , a male classical singer in the alto vocal range , specialising in Baroque music .
Gerhard Unger ( November 26 , 1916 -- July 4 , 2011 ) was a German lyric tenor .
Felice Varesi ( born Calais , 1813 -- died Milan , 13 March 1889 ) was a French - born Italian baritone with an illustrious singing career that began in the 1830s and extended into the 1860s .
Tiffany Claus ( born July 14 , 1980 ) is an American actress , model , classically trained mezzo - soprano vocalist , and professional oil painter .
Elise Stevenson ( February 9 , 1878 -- November 18 , 1967 ) was a British - born American soprano singer who recorded commercially successful popular songs in the early years of the 20th century .
Gregory Reinhart ( born 18 June 1951 in Pavilion , New York ) is an American bass opera singer .
Jean Elleviou ( 14 June 1769 , Rennes - 5 May 1842 , Paris ) was a French operatic tenor , one of the most celebrated French singers of his time .
Marie - Nicole Lemieux ( born June 26 , 1975 ) is a Canadian coloratura contralto .
Josepha Duschek ( 1754 - -1824 ) was an outstanding soprano singer of the Classical era .
Franz Vitzthum is a German countertenor , a male classical singer in the alto vocal range , specialising in Baroque music .
Adalbert Kraus ( born 27 April 1937 in Aschaffenburg ) is a German tenor in opera and concert , known for singing the works of Johann Sebastian Bach .
Gabriele Schreckenbach ( born in Berlin ) is a German contralto singer in opera and concert and an academic voice teacher .
Margaret Nisbett , MBE , ( born 9 January 1929 ) is an Australian coloratura soprano .
Arnold Matters ( 11 April 1904 -- 21 September 1990 ) was an Australian operatic baritone whose career was made mostly in England during the 1930s and 1940s .
Beatriz Michelena ( February 22 , 1890 -- October 10 , 1942 ) was an American actress during the silent film era , known at the time for her operatic soprano voice and appearances in musical theatre .
Friedrich Plaschke ( 7 January 1875 -- 4 February 1952 ) was a Czech operatic bass - baritone .
Oksana Dyka ( Ukrainian : Оксана Дика , ( ɔkˈsana ˈdɪka ) , also spelled Oksana Dika , born 1978 in Zhytomyr ) is a Ukrainian operatic soprano .
Giuseppe Sabbatini ( born May 11 , 1957 , Rome , Italy ) is a lyric tenor .
Carlo Meliciani ( born 1929 ) is an Italian operatic baritone who had an active international career from the mid-1950s through the late 1970s .
Teresa Brambilla ( 23 October 1813 -- 15 July 1895 ) was a celebrated Italian soprano most remembered today for having created the role of Gilda in Verdi 's opera , Rigoletto .
Alice Cucini ( 1870 - -1949 ) was an Italian contralto who had a prolific opera career in Europe and South America between 1891 and 1915 .
Natalia Troitskaya ( 1951 -- 9 April 2006 ) was a Russian operatic soprano who had a major international career during the 1980s and early 1990s .
Marie Le Rochois ( c. 1658 -- 8 October 1728 ) was a French operatic soprano who belonged to the Académie Royale de Musique .
Pretty Yende , OIS ( born 6 March 1985 ) is a South African soprano opera singer .
Christian Gerhaher ( born 1969 in Straubing ) is a noted German baritone and bass singer in opera and concert , particularly celebrated as a Lied singer .
Dianne van Giersbergen ( born 3 June 1985 in Liempde ) is a Dutch dramatic soprano singer , songwriter , and vocal coach who is well - known for being the frontwoman and founder of the progressive metal band Ex Libris and German symphonic metal band Xandria .
Friederike Sailer ( 20 February 1920 -- ? June 1994 ) was a German soprano in opera and concert .
Maria Ivogün ( 18 November 1891 , Budapest - 3 October 1987 , Beatenberg , Switzerland ) was a distinguished soprano singer of Hungarian origin .
Daniel Sans ( born 1975 ) is a German tenor .
Luana DeVol ( born 1943 in San Mateo , California ) is an American operatic soprano who made her Metropolitan Opera debut as Ortrud in April 2007 in Wagner 's Lohengrin .
Hervé Niquet ( born on October 28 , 1957 ) is a French conductor , harpsichordist , tenor , and the director of Le Concert Spirituel , specializing in French Baroque music .
Elisabeth Schumann ( 13 June 1888 -- 23 April 1952 ) was a German soprano who sang in opera , operetta , oratorio , and lieder .
Eugène Dufriche ( born 1848 , date of death unknown ) was a French baritone , who had a career on the operatic stage from the 1870s in Paris through to the 1900s in New York .
Frederick Bovill was an operatic baritone of the late Victorian era best known for his work in the Savoy Operas of Gilbert and Sullivan .
Anna Fitziu ( April 1 , 1887 -- April 20 , 1967 ) was an American soprano who had a prolific international opera career during the early part of the 20th century .
Birgit Nordin ( born 22 February 1934 in Sangis , Sweden ) is a Swedish opera soprano .
Mario Petri ( 21 January 1922 , Perugia - 26 January 1985 , Città della Pieve ) was an Italian operatic bass particularly associated with Mozart and Rossini roles .
Antonio Montagnana ( fl . 1730 - -50 , born in Venice ) was an Italian bass of the 18th - century who is best remembered for his association with the composer George Frideric Handel , whose operas Montagnana sang in .
Elaine Malbin ( born May 24 , 1932 , New York City ) is an American soprano who had a prolific international career singing in operas , musicals , and concerts from 1949 through 1967 .
Lili Chookasian ( August 1 , 1921 -- April 9 , 2012 ) was an American contralto who appeared with many of the world 's major symphony orchestras and opera houses .
Mignon Dunn ( born June 17 , 1928 in Memphis , Tennessee ) is a leading American dramatic mezzo - soprano and voice teacher .
Jean de Reszke ( 14 January 1850 -- 3 April 1925 ) , was a Polish tenor who was a major male opera star of the late 19th century .
Mindaugas Rojus ( born January 24 , 1981 in Darbėnai , Kretinga district , Lithuania ) is a Lithuanian opera singer ( tenor / baritone ) , a soloist of Klaipėda State Music Theatre , and a member of a stage duo Žemaitijos perlai ( Samogitia 's Pearls ) .
John Langstaff ( December 24 , 1920 -- December 13 , 2005 ) , a concert baritone , and early music revivalist was the founder of the Northeast United States tradition of the Christmas Revels , as well as a respected musician and educator .
Eugene Conley ( March 12 , 1908 -- December 18 , 1981 ) was a celebrated American operatic tenor .
Raimo Sirkiä ( born February 7 , 1951 in Finland ) is a Finnish operatic tenor whose repertoire ranges from spinto to dramatic .
Giuliano Ciannella ( 25 October 1943 -- 13 January 2008 ) was an Italian operatic tenor who had a major international career from the mid-1970s through the late 1990s .
Alice Verlet ( 1873 - -1934 ) was a Belgian - born operatic coloratura soprano active primarily in France .
Ghena Dimitrova ( Bulgarian : Гeна Димитpова ) ( 6 May 1941 -- 11 June 2005 ) was a Bulgarian operatic soprano .
Berle Sanford Rosenberg ( December 15 , 1951 ) is an American operatic tenor and vocal coach .
Andriana Yordanova is a Bulgarian - born soprano who started her career as a soloist in the school choir and the Children 's opera in her home town of Varna .
Marie Ismaël - Garcin ( 1858 - 1946 ) , was a French opera singer who specialised in light soprano roles and sang leading roles in several French opera houses during the 1880s .
Gloria Criscione Pineda , known artistically as `` Gloria del Paraguay '' is a Paraguayan soprano , recognized for her versatile voice .
Libuše Márová ( born 24 December 1943 ) is a Czech operatic mezzo - soprano who has been a principal artist at the National Theatre in Prague since 1969 .
Polly Young ( also known as Mary Young , Maria Young , Polly Barthélemon and Maria Barthélemon ) ( 7 July 1749 -- 20 September 1799 ) was an English soprano , composer and keyboard player .
Emmy Loose ( January 22 , 1914 in Ústí nad Labem -- October 14 , 1987 in Vienna ) was an Austrian operatic soprano of Czech birth , particularly associated with soubrette roles .
Edson Cordeiro ( born February 9 , 1967 ) is a sopranist countertenor and pop and jazz singer .
Liam Bonner ( born March 18 , 1981 ) is a professional opera singer ( baritone ) based in Houston , Texas .
Beyhan Demirdağ Alkan is a Turkish Cypriot mezzo - soprano .
Monika Frimmer ( born 1955 in Marburg ) is a German soprano in opera and concert .
Gino Vanelli ( 26 March 1896 , Bergamo - 9 April 1969 , Monza ) was an Italian operatic baritone who had an active international career from 1917 until his retirement in 1955 .
Dorothea Röschmann ( born 17 June 1967 ) is a German opera soprano from Flensburg .
Cyrena van Gordon was the stage name of an American operatic contralto born Cyrena Sue Pocock .
Rosina Brandram ( 2 July 1845 -- 28 February 1907 ) was an English opera singer and actress primarily known for creating many of the contralto roles in the Savoy operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Sonya Yoncheva ( Bulgarian : Соня Йончева , born 25 December 1981 ) is a Bulgarian operatic soprano .
Massimo Giordano ( born 19 February 1971 ) is an Italian - born operatic tenor who is known for his bel canto repertoire .
Harry Theyard ( né Harry L. Theard , Jr , on 28 September 1929 , in New Orleans ) is an American operatic tenor .
Rolando Villazón Mauleón ( born February 22 , 1972 ) is a French / Mexican tenor .
Sir Stig Fogh Andersen ( February 24 , 1950 in Hørsholm ) is a Danish operatic tenor .
Teresa Stratas , OC ( born May 26 , 1938 , Toronto , Ontario ) , is a retired Canadian operatic soprano of Greek descent .
Denise Scharley ( born Neuilly - en - Thelle , 15 February 1917 -- died Versailles , 26 July 2011 ) was a French contralto who made her debut in 1942 , singing Pelléas et Mélisande at the Opéra - Comique .
Elena Cernei ( 1 March 1924 -- 27 November 2000 ) was a Romanian operatic mezzo - soprano , musicologist , and voice teacher .
Barbara Kemp ( 12 December 1881 --17 April 1959 ) was a German soprano and opera singer .
José Oxilia , also known in Italy as Giuseppe Oxilia ( Montevideo , 3 June 1861 - 18 May 1919 ) was a Uruguayan operatic tenor .
Claes - Håkan Ahnsjö ( born 1 August 1942 ) is a Swedish operatic tenor particularly associated with the baroque repertoire and Mozart works .
